{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781764129613,"sessionID":"ses_126960be2ffewGSaH1Z0io46OH","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Z4JgI4f5Tz6zpgFewu7fdzLO","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","offset":1,"limit":2200},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n2: # DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n3: # в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n4: # DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n5: # в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n6: role: Deep Review Loop Manager\n7: purpose: Iterative code/spec review with convergence detection across review dimensions\n8: action: Run deep-review loop from initialization through synthesis\n9: operating_mode:\n10:   workflow: iterative_loop\n11:   workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n12:   workflow_execution: autonomous\n13:   approvals: none\n14:   tracking: progressive_review_state\n15:   validation: convergence_detection\n16: \n17: # в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n18: # OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n19: # в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n20: operating_principles:\n21:   core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n22:   approach: \"Dispatch focused review agent per dimension, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n23:   mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files. Review target is READ-ONLY.\"\n24: \n25: # в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n26: # USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n27: # в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n28: user_inputs:\n29:   review_target: \"[REVIEW_TARGET] - What to review. REQUIRED.\"\n30:   review_target_type: \"[spec-folder|skill|agent|track|files] - Target type for scope derivation. REQUIRED.\"\n31:   review_dimensions: \"[all|correctness,security,traceability,maintainability] - Dimensions to check. Default: all.\"\n32:   spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path for state files. REQUIRED.\"\n33:   lineage_mode: \"[auto|resume|restart] - Session lifecycle intent. Default: auto. The runtime only persists lineage events for `resume` (same sessionId, no archive) and `restart` (new sessionId, generation+1, prior review/ archived). `fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred and no longer accepted вҖ” see deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md В§Lifecycle Branches.\"\n34:   max_iterations: 7\n35:   convergence_threshold: 0.10\n36: \n37: # в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n38: # CONTEXT LOADING\n39: # в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n40: context_loading:\n41:   trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n42:   purpose: \"Load prior review context for the target and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n43:   mcp_integration:\n44:     tool: memory_context\n45:     note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n46:     parameters: { input: \"{review_target}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n47:   when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n48:   behavior:\n49:     if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n50:     if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n51: \n52: # в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n53: # SKILL REFERENCE\n54: # в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n55: skill_reference:\n56:   skill: deep-loop-workflows\n57:   skill_md: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md\n58:   references:\n59:     loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n60:     state_format: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md\n61:     convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md\n62:   templates:\n63:     config: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json\n64:     strategy: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md\n65: \n66: # в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n67: # AGENT CONFIGURATION\n68: # в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n69: agent_config:\n70:   agent: deep-review\n71:   agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-review.md\"\n72:   # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n73:   mode: subagent\n74:   model: opus\n75:   leaf_only: true\n76:   tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob]\n77:   mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n78:   tool_call_budget: { target: 9, soft_max: 12, hard_max: 13 }\n79: \n80: # в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n81: # STATE FILE PATHS\n82: # в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n83: state_paths:\n84:   # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n85:   # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep\n86:   # root-local review/ and child phases keep local review/ packet dirs.\n87:   # Canonical root-spec write targets remain review/deep-review-config.json,\n88:   # review/deep-review-state.jsonl, and review/deep-review-findings-registry.json.\n89:   packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n90:   local_packet_dir: \"{spec_folder}/review\"\n91:   legacy_root_report: \"{spec_folder}/review-report.md\"\n92:   config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json\"\n93:   state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl\"\n94:   findings_registry: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json\"\n95:   strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n96:   dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n97:   pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\"\n98:   lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review.lock\"\n99:   prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n100:   iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n101:   iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n102:   # Per-iteration structured delta stream вҖ” complement to the canonical state_log\n103:   # append. MUST contain at least one record with `type === \"iteration\"`; variants\n104:   # like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer.\n105:   delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n106:   delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n107:   review_output: \"{artifact_dir}/review-report.md\"\n108:   resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n109:   archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n110: \n111: # в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n112: # WORKFLOW\n113: # в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n114: workflow:\n115: \n116:   step_resolve_artifact_root:\n117:     description: \"Resolve artifact directory вҖ” use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n118:     note: \"Root specs keep review artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/review/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/review/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/review_archive/{packet}/.\"\n119:     branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n120:     if_present:\n121:       bind:\n122:         artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n123:         artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n124:         artifact_subfolder: null\n125:         artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n126:     if_absent:\n127:       command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'review')));\\\"\"\n128:       outputs:\n129:         - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local review owner directory\"\n130:         - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n131:         - artifact_dir: \"Resolved review packet directory for this target\"\n132:         - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local review archive directory for this target\"\n133: \n134:   step_fanout_spawn:\n135:     description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n136:     skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n137:     instructions: |\n138:       Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n139:       isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n140:       After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis вҖ” skip phase_init and\n141:       phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n142:       phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n143:     sub_steps:\n144:       step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n145:         description: \"Spawn all CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n146:         skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind != 'native'\"\n147:         command: |\n148:           node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n149:             --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n150:             --loop-type review \\\n151:             --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n152:             --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n153:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n154:         wait_for_completion: true\n155:       step_fanout_spawn_native:\n156:         description: \"Dispatch each native lineage as a sequential deep-review sub-agent\"\n157:         skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind == 'native'\"\n158:         for_each: \"lineage in expanded native entries of config.fanout\"\n159:         dispatch:\n160:           agent: deep-review\n161:           model: opus\n162:           context: |\n163:             Execute the deep-review loop with these parameters:\n164:               spec_folder: {spec_folder}\n165:               config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: {artifact_dir}/lineages/{lineage.label}\n166:               session_id: fanout-{lineage.label}-{fanout_run_id}\n167:               executor: native\n168:             Run to convergence. Write all outputs to the override directory.\n169:         wait_for_completion: true\n170: \n171:   # в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ\n172:   # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n173:   # в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ\n174:   phase_init:\n175:     purpose: Create all state files for the review session and resolve review scope\n176:     steps:\n177: \n178:       step_preflight_contract:\n179:         action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n180:         verify:\n181:           - required_values_present: [review_target, review_target_type, review_dimensions, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold]\n182:           - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n183:           - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n184:           - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n185:         on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n186: \n187:       step_create_directories:\n188:         action: \"Create spec folder and canonical review packet directories if they don't exist\"\n189:         command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n190: \n191:       step_detect_resource_map:\n192:         action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist coverage-gate state\"\n193:         inspect:\n194:           - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n195:         classify:\n196:           present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n197:           absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n198:         outputs:\n199:           - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n200:           - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: concise resource-map snapshot for Known Context and charter framing. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n201: \n202:       step_migrate_legacy_review_state:\n203:         action: \"Rehome legacy review artifacts into review/iterations before session classification\"\n204:         detect:\n205:           canonical_review_state:\n206:             - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n207:             - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n208:             - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n209:             - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n210:           legacy_review_state:\n211:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json\"\n212:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n213:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n214:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n215:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/iteration-*.md\"\n216:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause\"\n217:             - \"{state_paths.local_packet_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n218:             - \"{state_paths.legacy_root_report}\"\n219:           legacy_review_markers:\n220:             - \"scratch/deep-review-strategy.md exists\"\n221:             - \"scratch/deep-research-config.json declares mode == 'review' OR scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl contains mode == 'review'\"\n222:         migrate_only:\n223:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json -> {state_paths.config}\"\n224:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl -> {state_paths.state_log}\"\n225:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md -> {state_paths.strategy}\"\n226:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md -> {state_paths.dashboard}\"\n227:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/iteration-*.md -> {state_paths.iteration_dir}/\"\n228:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause -> {state_paths.pause_sentinel}\"\n229:           - \"{state_paths.local_packet_dir}/iteration-*.md -> {state_paths.iteration_dir}/\"\n230:           - \"{state_paths.legacy_root_report} -> {state_paths.review_output}\"\n231:         on_canonical_present: \"Leave canonical review/ state untouched and do not overwrite it with legacy scratch artifacts.\"\n232:         on_legacy_detected: \"Move only the review-specific whitelist, append a migration event to the canonical JSONL, and leave unrelated scratch files untouched.\"\n233:         on_conflict: \"If canonical review/ state and legacy scratch review state both exist but disagree, halt for operator repair instead of merging contradictory state.\"\n234:         command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.iteration_dir} && if [ ! -e {state_paths.config} ] && [ ! -e {state_paths.state_log} ] && [ ! -e {state_paths.strategy} ] && [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md ] && ( [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json ] || [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl ] ); then [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json {state_paths.config}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl {state_paths.state_log}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md {state_paths.strategy}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md {state_paths.dashboard}; find {spec_folder}/scratch -maxdepth 1 -name 'iteration-*.md' -exec mv {} {state_paths.iteration_dir}/ \\\\; ; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause {state_paths.pause_sentinel}; [ -e {state_paths.legacy_root_report} ] && mv {state_paths.legacy_root_report} {state_paths.review_output}; if [ -e {state_paths.state_log} ]; then printf '%s\\n' '{\\\"type\\\":\\\"event\\\",\\\"event\\\":\\\"migration\\\",\\\"mode\\\":\\\"review\\\",\\\"legacyArtifacts\\\":[\\\"deep-research-config.json\\\",\\\"deep-research-state.jsonl\\\",\\\".deep-research-pause\\\"],\\\"canonicalArtifacts\\\":[\\\"deep-review-config.json\\\",\\\"deep-review-state.jsonl\\\",\\\".deep-review-pause\\\"],\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\\\"}' >> {state_paths.state_log}; fi; fi; find {state_paths.local_packet_dir} -maxdepth 1 -name 'iteration-*.md' -exec mv {} {state_paths.iteration_dir}/ \\\\; 2>/dev/null || true\"\n235: \n236:       step_acquire_lock:\n237:         action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n238:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n239:         on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed вҖ” another deep-review run already holds this packet.\"\n240:         note: \"Uses the promoted deep-loop-runtime loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory вҖ” best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n241:         # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n242:         # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n243:         on_halt:\n244:           action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n245:           applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\"]\n246:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n247:         on_cancel:\n248:           action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n249:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n250:         on_workflow_exit:\n251:           action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n252:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent вҖ” safe to invoke when already released\"\n253: \n254:       step_classify_session:\n255:         action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n256:         inspect:\n257:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n258:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n259:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n260:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n261:         classify:\n262:           fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n263:           resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and config.mode == 'review' and agree on target/spec folder\"\n264:           completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n265:           invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n266:         outputs:\n267:           - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n268:         on_resume:\n269:           log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n270:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n271:           skip_to: phase_loop\n272:         on_restart:\n273:           action: \"Archive the current review packet under the root-level review_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n274:           command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n275:           set:\n276:             lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n277:             parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n278:             generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n279:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n280:           skip_to: step_create_config\n281:         note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md В§Lifecycle Branches for the one-session contract.\"\n282:         on_completed_session:\n283:           log: \"Prior session already completed. Either archive the completed review/ tree and start a fresh session, or jump straight to synthesis with the existing artifacts.\"\n284:           skip_to: phase_synthesis\n285:         on_invalid_state:\n286:           halt: true\n287:           message: \"Existing deep-review state in review/ is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid review packet before continuing.\"\n288:         on_fresh:\n289:           action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n290: \n291:       step_scope_discovery:\n292:         action: \"Resolve review target to a concrete file list based on target type\"\n293:         resolve:\n294:           spec-folder: |\n295:             1. Read spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md, checklist.md, implementation-summary.md\n296:             2. Discover implementation files referenced in spec artifacts\n297:             3. Discover test files associated with implementation\n298:             4. Set scope = all discovered files\n299:           skill: |\n300:             1. Read SKILL.md from .opencode/skills/{skill_name}/\n301:             2. Discover references/, assets/, scripts/ contents\n302:             3. Find agent definitions referencing this skill across runtimes\n303:             4. Find command entry points referencing this skill\n304:             5. Set scope = all discovered files\n305:           agent: |\n306:             1. Find agent definition across repo-managed runtimes (.claude/agents/, .opencode/agents/, .codex/agents/, .agents/)\n307:             2. Compare agent definitions for consistency\n308:             3. Set scope = all discovered agent files\n309:           track: |\n310:             1. List all child spec folders under specs/{track}/ or .opencode/specs/{track}/\n311:             2. For each: read spec.md + checklist.md\n312:             3. Set scope = all child spec artifacts\n313:           files: |\n314:             1. Expand glob patterns from review_target\n315:             2. Validate all files exist\n316:             3. Discover immediate cross-references (imports, links)\n317:             4. Set scope = expanded file list + cross-references\n318:         outputs:\n319:           - review_scope_files: \"List of all files in review scope\"\n320:           - cross_reference_targets: \"{ spec_paths: [...], code_paths: [...], test_paths: [...] }\"\n321: \n322:       step_order_dimensions:\n323:         action: \"Order review dimensions based on risk priority\"\n324:         algorithm: |\n325:           1. Iteration 0 (inventory pass): Build artifact map, identify file types, estimate complexity\n326:           2. Subsequent iterations follow risk-ordered deep passes:\n327:              correctness вҶ’ security вҶ’ traceability вҶ’ maintainability\n328:           3. If review_dimensions != \"all\", filter to only requested dimensions\n329:           4. Derive traceability protocol plan:\n330:              - core: spec_code, checklist_evidence\n331:              - overlay: skill_agent, agent_cross_runtime, feature_catalog_code, playbook_capability\n332:           5. If resource_map_present, reserve at least one traceability-oriented pass to cross-check target_files from applied/T-*.md against resource-map.md and classify touched / expected-by-scope / gap / absent-from-map outcomes\n333:           6. Store ordered list as dimension_queue\n334:         outputs:\n335:           - dimension_queue: \"Ordered list of dimensions to review\"\n336:           - inventory_pass: true\n337: \n338:       step_normalize_review_dimensions:\n339:         action: \"Normalize reviewDimensions once during init for config + JSONL reuse\"\n340:         outputs:\n341:           - review_dimensions_normalized: \"Canonical string[] for deep-review-config.json\"\n342:           - review_dimensions_json: \"JSON.stringify(review_dimensions_normalized) for JSONL config record\"\n343:         normalize: |\n344:           Accept {review_dimensions} in any of these shapes and convert once:\n345:             - \"all\" вҶ’ [\"correctness\",\"security\",\"traceability\",\"maintainability\"]\n346:             - \"correctness,security\" вҶ’ [\"correctness\",\"security\"]\n347:             - [\"correctness\"] вҶ’ [\"correctness\"]\n348:           Every element MUST be one of the four canonical dimension names.\n349: \n350:       step_create_config:\n351:         action: \"Create deep-review-config.json from template with review-specific fields\"\n352:         template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json\n353:         populate:\n354:           topic: \"Review: {review_target}\"\n355:           mode: \"review\"\n356:           sessionId: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n357:           parentSessionId: null\n358:           lineageMode: \"new\"\n359:           generation: 1\n360:           continuedFromRun: null\n361:           reviewTarget: \"{review_target}\"\n362:           reviewTargetType: \"{review_target_type}\"\n363:           # Reuse the single normalized init-time value from step_normalize_review_dimensions.\n364:           reviewDimensions: \"{review_dimensions_normalized}\"\n365:           resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n366:           reviewScopeFiles: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n367:           severityThreshold: \"P2\"\n368:           crossReference:\n369:             core: [\"spec_code\", \"checklist_evidence\"]\n370:             overlay: [\"skill_agent\", \"agent_cross_runtime\", \"feature_catalog_code\", \"playbook_capability\"]\n371:           maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n372:           # Semantic: weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio. See SKILL.md В§\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n373:           convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n374:           stuckThreshold: 2\n375:           maxDurationMinutes: 120\n376:           specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n377:           # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n378:           # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-review.md:71 (default true; false when flag is set).\n379:           # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n380:           resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n381:           createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n382:           status: \"initialized\"\n383:           releaseReadinessState: \"in-progress\"\n384:           executionMode: \"auto\"\n385:         output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n386: \n387:       step_create_state_log:\n388:         action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record including review fields and lineage metadata\"\n389:         note: \"Reuse review_dimensions_json from step_normalize_review_dimensions. Never re-normalize or wrap the raw template value.\"\n390:         # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n391:         # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n392:         content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"reviewTarget\":\"{review_target}\",\"reviewTargetType\":\"{review_target_type}\",\"reviewDimensions\":{review_dimensions_json},\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"sessionId\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"parentSessionId\":null,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"generation\":1,\"continuedFromRun\":null,\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\"}'\n393:         output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n394: \n395:       step_create_findings_registry:\n396:         action: \"Initialize reducer-owned review findings registry\"\n397:         content: '{\"sessionId\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"generation\":1,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"openFindings\":[],\"resolvedFindings\":[],\"repeatedFindings\":[],\"dimensionCoverage\":{\"correctness\":false,\"security\":false,\"traceability\":false,\"maintainability\":false},\"findingsBySeverity\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"openFindingsCount\":0,\"resolvedFindingsCount\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0.0}'\n398:         output: \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n399: \n400:       step_create_strategy:\n401:         action: \"Create review strategy file from deep_review_strategy.md template\"\n402:         template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md\n403:         populate:\n404:           review_target: \"{review_target}\"\n405:           review_target_type: \"{review_target_type}\"\n406:           dimensions: \"{dimension_queue}\"\n407:           scope_files: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n408:           cross_reference_targets: \"{cross_reference_targets}\"\n409:           max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n410:           convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n411:         output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n412: \n413:       step_enrich_strategy_context:\n414:         action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n415:         condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n416:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n417:         note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n418: \n419:       step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n420:         action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n421:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n422:         note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot and add Resource Map Coverage to the Review Charter. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n423: \n424:       step_init_complete:\n425:         log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, and strategy files created. Review scope: {review_scope_files_count} files, {dimension_queue_count} dimensions.\"\n426:         set: { current_iteration: 1, stuck_count: 0, p0_count: 0, p1_count: 0, p2_count: 0 }\n427: \n428:   # в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ\n429:   # PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n430:   # в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ\n431:   phase_loop:\n432:     purpose: Dispatch review agent iterations until convergence\n433:     repeat: true\n434:     max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n435:     steps:\n436: \n437:       step_read_state:\n438:         action: \"Read current state from JSONL, strategy, and config\"\n439:         read:\n440:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n441:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n442:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n443:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n444:         extract:\n445:           - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n446:           - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n447:           - last_newFindingsRatio: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from last iteration record\"\n448:           - last_focus: \"Extract focus/dimension from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n449:           - ratio_prev: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n450:           - ratio_latest: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n451:           - next_dimension: \"Next uncovered dimension from dimension_queue in strategy.md\"\n452:           - dimensions_covered: \"List of dimensions already reviewed\"\n453:           - dimensions_remaining: \"List of dimensions not yet reviewed\"\n454:           - dimension_coverage: \"covered / total dimensions\"\n455:           - coverage_age: \"Iterations since dimension coverage last changed; require >= 1 before STOP\"\n456:           - p0_count: \"Count P0 findings across all iterations\"\n457:           - p1_count: \"Count P1 findings across all iterations\"\n458:           - p2_count: \"Count P2 findings across all iterations\"\n459:           - resource_map_present: \"Extract boolean from deep-review-config.json, default false\"\n460:           - resource_map_prompt_line: \"If resource_map_present is true, return 'Resource Map Coverage: cross-check target_files from {spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md against {spec_folder}/resource-map.md and classify only missed coverage as gaps.' Else return 'Resource Map Coverage: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.'\"\n461:           - session_id: \"Extract sessionId from deep-review-config.json\"\n462:           - generation: \"Extract generation from deep-review-config.json, else 1\"\n463:           - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: dimension (ratio, P0/P1/P2)'\"\n464:           - latest_status: \"Extract status from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n465:           - last_claim_adjudication_passed: \"Scan state.jsonl for the most recent `claim_adjudication` event; use its `passed` boolean. Default true when no event exists or when activeP0 + activeP1 == 0 (gate is vacuous without adjudicable findings).\"\n466:           - claim_adjudication_active_count: \"Count of active P0/P1 findings at the time of the last claim_adjudication event; 0 when none exist\"\n467:           - security_sensitive_fix_scope: \"Boolean true when the current review is a rerun after fixes involving security, path disclosure, auth/authz, sandboxing, env precedence, public schemas, persistence, or user-visible error payloads; derive from the latest review report, remediation notes, or planning packet when present, else false.\"\n468:           - fix_completeness_replay_required_rows: \"Count prior active or remediated P0/P1 findings, plus any prior security/path P2 findings, that require closed-gate replay before STOP.\"\n469:           - fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows: \"Count required replay rows marked PASS with file:line or command evidence and producer/consumer/matrix coverage.\"\n470: \n471:       step_check_pause_sentinel:\n472:         action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n473:         check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n474:         if_exists:\n475:           set:\n476:             pending_stop_event: \"paused\"\n477:             pending_stop_reason: \"userPaused\"\n478:             pending_stop_detail: \"sentinel file detected\"\n479:           skip_to: step_normalize_pause_events\n480:         if_not_exists:\n481:           proceed: true\n482: \n483:       step_graph_convergence:\n484:         action: \"Evaluate coverage-graph convergence before the inline review convergence vote\"\n485:         inspect:\n486:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n487:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n488:         transform: |\n489:           1. Call graph convergence on the current review lineage before the inline 3-signal vote.\n490:           2. Record the decision as one of CONTINUE, STOP_ALLOWED, STOP_BLOCKED.\n491:           3. Preserve raw graph signals and blockers for reducer rollup and blocked-stop evidence.\n492:           4. Normalize blockers to both JSON array and CSV forms for downstream stop handling.\n493:           5. Set graph_stop_blocked = true only when graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\".\n494:         bash: 'node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"review\" --session-id \"{session_id}\"'\n495:         note: \"Invoke the runtime script directly. Review-side graph convergence must run before the inline review stop vote.\"\n496:         append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"graph_convergence\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"decision\":\"{graph_decision}\",\"signals\":{graph_signals_json},\"blockers\":{graph_blockers_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n497:         outputs:\n498:           - graph_decision: \"CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED\"\n499:           - graph_signals_json: \"JSON object returned by convergence.cjs\"\n500:           - graph_blockers_json: \"JSON array of graph blockers when present, else []\"\n501:           - graph_blockers_csv: \"Comma-separated blocker summary when graph blocks STOP, else empty string\"\n502:           - graph_stop_blocked: \"Boolean true when graph_decision == STOP_BLOCKED\"\n503: \n504:       step_check_convergence:\n505:         action: \"Evaluate graph-assisted review stop conditions and the legal-stop decision tree\"\n506:         algorithm: |\n507:           0. CLAIM-ADJUDICATION PRE-CHECK (universal STOP veto; runs before hard stops and composite convergence):\n508:              claim_adjudication_gate_pass = (last_claim_adjudication_passed != false) OR (p0_count + p1_count == 0)\n509:              If claim_adjudication_gate_pass == false:\n510:                candidate_decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n511:                stop_blocked = true\n512:                stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n513:                blocked_gates = [\"claimAdjudicationGate\"]\n514:                recovery_strategy = \"Reviewer must add typed claim-adjudication packets (claim, evidenceRefs, counterevidenceSought, alternativeExplanation, finalSeverity, confidence, downgradeTrigger) for every active P0/P1 finding before STOP is allowed.\"\n515:                Skip hard stops (1) and composite convergence (4); proceed directly to step 5 legal-stop decision-tree assembly so blocked_by_json, gate outputs, and the blocked_stop event still populate consistently.\n516:           1. HARD STOPS:\n517:              a) if iteration_count >= max_iterations: set decision = \"STOP\", stopReason = \"maxIterationsReached\", hard_stop_reason = \"max_iterations_reached\", preserve any failed legal-stop gates as terminal evidence, and proceed to synthesis without legal-stop veto\n518:              b) if all dimensions clean AND required traceability protocols are covered AND p0_count == 0 AND p1_count == 0 AND coverage_age >= 1 AND all quality gates pass (evidence: every P0/P1 has file:line; scope: all findings within target; coverage: all dimensions reviewed): mark hard_stop_reason = \"all_dimensions_clean\" and promote to STOP candidate\n519:              Operator stop reasons (`maxIterationsReached`, `manualStop`, `userPaused`, unrecoverable `error`) are terminal ceilings. They do not hide failed gates; they record them in synthesis and stop dispatch.\n520:           2. STUCK DETECTION (threshold 2):\n521:              if stuck_count >= 2: STUCK_RECOVERY\n522:           3. GRAPH CONVERGENCE PREREQUISITE:\n523:                graph_decision, graph_signals_json, and graph_blockers_json are already populated by step_graph_convergence.\n524:                Final STOP is never legal unless the inline review vote says STOP AND graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\".\n525:                If graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\", set stop_blocked = true and route through blocked_stop emission instead of stopping.\n526:           4. COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE (3-signal weighted vote with split thresholds):\n527:                signals = []\n528:                a) Rolling average (w=0.30, window=2, needs 2+ iterations):\n529:                   avg = mean(last 2 newFindingsRatios)\n530:                   stop if avg <= 0.08\n531:                b) MAD noise floor (w=0.25, needs 3+ iterations):\n532:                   noiseFloor = MAD(all ratios) * 1.4826\n533:                   stop if latest ratio <= noiseFloor\n534:                c) Dimension coverage (w=0.45):\n535:                   coverage = dimensions_covered / total_dimensions\n536:                   stop if coverage >= 1.0 AND required traceability protocols are covered AND coverage_age >= 1\n537:                Redistribute weights for unavailable signals.\n538:                if latest ratio <= 0.05: mark no_progress_threshold_reached\n539:                if weighted_stop_score >= 0.60: inline STOP becomes a candidate and binary gates must run\n540:           5. LEGAL-STOP DECISION TREE (review-specific gates; runs whenever step 0, all-dimensions-clean, or the composite vote promotes STOP to a candidate; terminal max-iteration/manual/error stops bypass veto and record failed gates as evidence):\n541:                a) convergenceGate: pass when a hard-stop condition is met OR weighted_stop_score >= 0.60; record score\n542:                b) dimensionCoverageGate: pass when configured dimensions and required traceability coverage are complete and coverage_age >= 1; record covered and missing dimensions\n543:                c) p0ResolutionGate: pass when activeP0 == 0; record activeP0\n544:                d) evidenceDensityGate: pass when every active P0/P1 has concrete file:line evidence and no active P0/P1 relies only on inference; record avgEvidencePerFinding\n545:                e) hotspotSaturationGate: pass when review hotspots have been revisited enough times to satisfy the saturation heuristic\n546:                f) claimAdjudicationGate: pass when claim_adjudication_gate_pass == true (i.e. last_claim_adjudication_passed != false OR there are no active P0/P1 findings to adjudicate); record last_claim_adjudication_passed and claim_adjudication_active_count\n547:                g) fixCompletenessReplayGate: pass when security_sensitive_fix_scope == false OR every required closed-gate replay row passes with file:line or command evidence and producer/consumer/matrix coverage; record security_sensitive_fix_scope, fix_completeness_replay_required_rows, and fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows\n548:                h) candidateCoverageGate: skip entirely when `reviewDepthSchemaVersion` is not 2 on the latest iteration. Otherwise pass when the current iteration's `reviewDepthApplicability.scopeClass` is `trivial` with `enforcement: \"skip\"` AND `reviewDepthApplicability.evidenceRefs` is non-empty, OR when the reducer registry's `searchDebt` is empty AND `candidateCoverage.covered` is a superset of `searchCoverage.requiredBugClasses` for the lineage. Otherwise pass = false; record `searchDebt` items as blocked-stop evidence; blocker name = \"candidateCoverageGate\"; recovery_strategy = \"Resolve deferred/blocked obligations in next iteration or downgrade scope explicitly to trivial with cited evidence.\"\n549:                i) graphlessFallbackGate: skip when `reviewDepthSchemaVersion` is not 2 OR the reducer registry's last-iteration `searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode` is `graph`. Applies when graphCoverageMode is `graphless_fallback` or `unavailable_blocked`. Pass when graphCoverageMode is `graphless_fallback` AND at least one `searchLedger` row exists for each entry in `searchCoverage.requiredBugClasses` with `searchActions[].method` in {\"direct_read\",\"exact_grep\",\"semantic_search\",\"code_graph_status_check\",\"producer_consumer_trace\",\"negative_test_inspection\"} AND non-empty `evidenceRefs`. Fail automatically when graphCoverageMode is `unavailable_blocked`; record the explicit unavailability reason. Otherwise pass = false; blocker name = \"graphlessFallbackGate\"; recovery_strategy = \"Add cited fallback ledger rows (direct read, exact search, producer/consumer trace, negative-test inspection) or set graphCoverageMode to 'graph' once graph data is available.\"\n550:              if STOP is a candidate and any gate fails:\n551:                decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n552:                stop_blocked = true\n553:                stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n554:                blocked_by_json = JSON array of failing gate names (always include \"claimAdjudicationGate\" when claim_adjudication_gate_pass == false, \"fixCompletenessReplayGate\" when fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass == false, \"candidateCoverageGate\" when candidate_coverage_gate_pass == false, and \"graphlessFallbackGate\" when graphless_fallback_gate_pass == false)\n555:                blocked_by_csv = comma-separated list of failing gate names\n556:                convergence_gate_pass = boolean\n557:                convergence_gate_score = numeric convergence score\n558:                dimension_coverage_gate_pass = boolean\n559:                dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json = JSON array of covered review dimensions\n560:                dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json = JSON array of missing review dimensions\n561:                p0_resolution_gate_pass = boolean\n562:                active_p0_count = number of active P0 findings\n563:                evidence_density_gate_pass = boolean\n564:                avg_evidence_per_finding = numeric evidence density\n565:                hotspot_saturation_gate_pass = boolean\n566:                claim_adjudication_gate_pass = boolean\n567:                claim_adjudication_active_count = numeric count of active P0/P1 at the gate\n568:                fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass = boolean\n569:                security_sensitive_fix_scope = boolean\n570:                fix_completeness_replay_required_rows = numeric count of closed-gate replay rows required for security-sensitive fix reruns\n571:                fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows = numeric count of required closed-gate replay rows marked PASS with evidence\n572:                candidate_coverage_gate_pass = boolean\n573:                candidate_coverage_search_debt_json = JSON array of reducer-owned searchDebt obligations blocking STOP, else []\n574:                candidate_coverage_missing_json = JSON array of required bug classes not present in candidateCoverage.covered, else []\n575:                graphless_fallback_gate_pass = boolean\n576:                graphless_fallback_mode = latest reducer-owned searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode value\n577:                graphless_fallback_missing_json = JSON array of required bug classes without cited fallback ledger rows, else []\n578:                graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason = explicit reason when graphCoverageMode == \"unavailable_blocked\", else empty string\n579:                recovery_strategy = one-line hint describing the next review action needed to satisfy the failed gates; combine candidateCoverageGate and graphlessFallbackGate recovery guidance when both fail (when claimAdjudicationGate is the failing gate, prefer the step-0 recovery_strategy already set)\n580:           6. COMBINED STOP RULE:\n581:                a) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\": decision = \"STOP\"\n582:                b) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\":\n583:                     decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n584:                     stop_blocked = true\n585:                     stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n586:                     # Blocked-stop closure: blockedBy must be string[] per the\n587:                     # published review blocked-stop contract. Extract the `.type`\n588:                     # field from each structured graph blocker; preserve the full\n589:                     # objects in graph_blocker_detail_json for operator inspection.\n590:                     blocked_by_json = JSON.stringify(graph_blockers_json.map(b => typeof b === \"string\" ? b : (b && b.type) || \"graph_blocker\"))\n591:                     blocked_by_csv = graph_blockers_csv\n592:                     graph_blocker_detail_json = graph_blockers_json\n593:                     recovery_strategy = \"Resolve review coverage-graph blockers before stopping.\"\n594:                c) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"CONTINUE\":\n595:                     decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n596:                     stop_blocked = false\n597:                     reason = \"graph_convergence_continue\"\n598:                d) else keep the existing STUCK_RECOVERY or CONTINUE outcome\n599:         outputs:\n600:           - decision: \"STOP | BLOCKED | STUCK_RECOVERY | CONTINUE\"\n601:           - reason: \"Human-readable stop reason\"\n602:           - stop_blocked: \"Boolean true when STOP is vetoed by inline legal-stop gates or graph_decision == STOP_BLOCKED\"\n603:           - blocked_by_json: \"JSON array of failed legal-stop gates when decision == BLOCKED\"\n604:           - blocked_by_csv: \"Comma-separated list of failed legal-stop gates when decision == BLOCKED\"\n605:           - convergence_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for convergenceGate\"\n606:           - convergence_gate_score: \"Numeric score recorded for convergenceGate\"\n607:           - dimension_coverage_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for dimensionCoverageGate\"\n608:           - dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json: \"JSON array of covered review dimensions\"\n609:           - dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json: \"JSON array of missing review dimensions\"\n610:           - p0_resolution_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for p0ResolutionGate\"\n611:           - active_p0_count: \"Active P0 finding count at stop-check time\"\n612:           - evidence_density_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for evidenceDensityGate\"\n613:           - avg_evidence_per_finding: \"Numeric evidence density for active findings\"\n614:           - hotspot_saturation_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for hotspotSaturationGate\"\n615:           - claim_adjudication_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for claimAdjudicationGate (false vetoes STOP)\"\n616:           - claim_adjudication_active_count: \"Count of active P0/P1 findings evaluated by claimAdjudicationGate\"\n617:           - fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for fixCompletenessReplayGate (false vetoes STOP on security-sensitive fix reruns)\"\n618:           - security_sensitive_fix_scope: \"Boolean true when the review is a security-sensitive fix rerun\"\n619:           - fix_completeness_replay_required_rows: \"Count of closed-gate replay rows required before STOP\"\n620:           - fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows: \"Count of required closed-gate replay rows that passed with evidence\"\n621:           - candidate_coverage_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for candidateCoverageGate (false vetoes STOP for unresolved reducer-owned search debt or uncovered required bug classes)\"\n622:           - candidate_coverage_search_debt_json: \"JSON array of reducer-owned searchDebt obligations used as blocked-stop evidence\"\n623:           - candidate_coverage_missing_json: \"JSON array of required bug classes missing from candidateCoverage.covered\"\n624:           - graphless_fallback_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for graphlessFallbackGate (false vetoes STOP when graphless fallback evidence is absent or unavailable_blocked)\"\n625:           - graphless_fallback_mode: \"Latest reducer-owned searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode value\"\n626:           - graphless_fallback_missing_json: \"JSON array of required bug classes missing cited fallback ledger rows\"\n627:           - graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason: \"Explicit unavailability reason when graphCoverageMode == unavailable_blocked\"\n628:           - graph_decision: \"CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED from step_graph_convergence\"\n629:           - graph_signals_json: \"JSON object returned by graph convergence\"\n630:           - graph_blockers_json: \"JSON array of graph blockers\"\n631:           - graph_blockers_csv: \"Comma-separated graph blocker summary\"\n632:           - recovery_strategy: \"One-line hint describing the next review action when decision == BLOCKED or STUCK_RECOVERY\"\n633: \n634:       step_emit_blocked_stop:\n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 1-634. Use offset=635 to continue.)\n</content>\n\n<system-reminder>\nInstructions from: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/CONTEXT.md\n---\ndescription: Codebase-context loop: heterogeneous parallel sweep with convergence detection. Modes :auto, :confirm.\nargument-hint: \"<scope> [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--executor=<type> [--model=X] [--prompt-framework=X] [--label=X] ...] [--executors=<json>] [--concurrency=N] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context\n---\n\n# Deep Start Context Loop\n\nThin router for the deep-context loop. This command verifies the orchestrating agent, resolves setup and execution mode, loads the presentation contract, then executes the owned workflow YAML.\n\n## 1. ROUTER CONTRACT\n\nDo not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Agent dispatch, workflow steps, and artifact-writing behavior are owned by the workflow YAML assets.\n\nLoad the presentation contract before showing startup questions, dashboards, checkpoints, success output, failure output, examples, or next-step prompts.\n\nThis command is **general-agent based** and must pass the @general verification gate before setup routing continues. Gate 1 (@general verification) and Gate 2 (the BLOCKED Unified Setup Phase) are HARD BLOCKS; neither may be skipped.\n\n### PHASE 0: @GENERAL AGENT VERIFICATION\n\n**STATUS: вҳҗ BLOCKED**\n\n```\nEXECUTE THIS AUTOMATIC SELF-CHECK (NOT A USER QUESTION):\n\nSELF-CHECK: Are you operating as the @general agent?\nв”Ӯ\nв”ңв”Җ INDICATORS that you ARE @general agent:\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җ You can orchestrate the deep-context loop (YAML workflow execution)\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җ You can orchestrate Read/Write/Edit/Bash workflow execution\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җ You can load skill references and execute defined logic\nв”Ӯ\nв”ңв”Җ IF YES (all indicators present):\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җ general_agent_verified = TRUE вҶ’ Continue to the Unified Setup Phase (also a HARD BLOCK)\nв”Ӯ\nв””в”Җ IF NO or UNCERTAIN:\n    в”Ӯ\n    в”ңв”Җ вӣ” HARD BLOCK - DO NOT PROCEED\n    в”Ӯ\n    в”ңв”Җ DISPLAY to user:\n    в”Ӯ   в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n    в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ вӣ” GENERAL AGENT REQUIRED                                  в”Ӯ\n    в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ                                                            в”Ӯ\n    в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ This command orchestrates the deep-context loop and runs   в”Ӯ\n    в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ general-agent based.                                       в”Ӯ\n    в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ                                                            в”Ӯ\n    в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ To proceed, restart with:                                  в”Ӯ\n    в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   /deep:context [arguments]                                в”Ӯ \n    в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n    в”Ӯ\n    в””в”Җ RETURN: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"General agent required\"\n```\n\n**Phase Output:**\n- `general_agent_verified = ________________`\n\n### MANDATORY INPUT GATE\n\n- **DO NOT** dispatch any agent from this document\n- **ALL** agent dispatching is handled by the YAML workflow steps\n- **MARKDOWN OWNS SETUP**: resolve setup inputs here first, then hand off to YAML\n- **YAML START CONDITION**: do not load YAML until ALL required inputs are bound:\n  - `scope`, `spec_folder`, `execution_mode`, `maxIterations`, `convergenceThreshold`\n- Resolve `executor_pool` before persisting config and entering the YAML workflow.\n\n---\n\n## 2. OWNED ASSETS\n\n| Purpose | Asset |\n|---------|-------|\n| Presentation source of truth | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_presentation.txt` |\n| Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_auto.yaml` |\n| Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_confirm.yaml` |\n\nNo workflow-asset gap exists for this command.\n\n---\n\n## 3. MODE ROUTING\n\n1. Parse `$ARGUMENTS` for attached command suffixes (`:auto` or `:confirm`). Canonical mode syntax is `/deep:context:auto` and `/deep:context:confirm`; keep AGENTS, skills, and quick references synchronized to this entrypoint.\n2. Treat scope text, `--max-iterations`, `--convergence`, relevance/agreement flags, executor pool flags, and pre-bound setup answers as workflow inputs, not execution modes.\n3. If `:auto` is present, set `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS` and resolve required setup inputs through the presentation contract's three-tier auto setup resolution before loading YAML.\n4. If `:confirm` is present, set `execution_mode = INTERACTIVE` and use the presentation contract's consolidated setup prompt before loading YAML.\n5. If no mode suffix is present, set `execution_mode = ASK` and use the presentation contract's consolidated setup prompt to ask for execution mode.\n6. Load the selected workflow asset only after `scope`, `spec_folder`, `execution_mode`, `maxIterations`, `convergenceThreshold`, and `executor_pool` are bound.\n\n---\n\n## 4. EXECUTION TARGETS\n\n| Mode | Workflow |\n|------|----------|\n| `:auto` | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_auto.yaml` |\n| `:confirm` or interactive choice | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_confirm.yaml` |\n\n---\n\n## 5. PRESENTATION BOUNDARY\n\nThe following content lives only in `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_presentation.txt`:\n\n- Startup-question wording, consolidated setup prompt text, question text, and reply-format examples.\n- `:auto` pre-bound setup answer schema, default resolution table, targeted-ask rules, and fail-fast display behavior.\n- Dashboard/checkpoint layouts, workflow overview displays, convergence threshold semantics, runtime robustness/session classification displays, and memory/skill reference displays.\n- Success and failure result templates, output formats, and error-handling displays.\n- Example invocations, executor-pool explanation display, and next-step suggestion wording.\n\n---\n\n## 6. WORKFLOW SUMMARY\n\nThe YAML workflow runs iterative codebase-context gathering by seeding a `SLICE` frontier from the scope, dispatching every executor over the same focus as a parallel sweep, merging findings by `file:symbol` with agreement counts, and synthesizing a reuse-first Context Report under `context/`. Convergence uses deep-context's relevance-gated coverage saturation with agreement and relevance as blocking guards; do not transfer sibling defaults from deep-research or deep-review. Code graph tool IDs remain stable as `code_graph_query` and `code_graph_context`; implementation and docs live under `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/`.\n\n**Context path:** `/deep:context` -> `/speckit:plan` -> `/speckit:implement`\n**Research:** `/deep:research` -> `/speckit:plan` -> `/speckit:implement`\n**Review:** `/deep:review` -> (if issues) `/speckit:plan` -> `/speckit:implement`\n\n</system-reminder>","metadata":{"preview":"# в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n# DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n# DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\nrole: Deep Review Loop Manager\npurpose: Iterative code/spec review with convergence detection across review dimensions\naction: Run deep-review loop from initialization through synthesis\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: iterative_loop\n  workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n  workflow_execution: autonomous\n  approvals: none\n  tracking: progressive_review_state\n  validation: convergence_detection\n\n# в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n# OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n# в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\noperating_principles:","truncated":true,"loaded":["/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/CONTEXT.md"],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","text":"# в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n# DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n# DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\nrole: Deep Review Loop Manager\npurpose: Iterative code/spec review with convergence detection across review dimensions\naction: Run deep-review loop from initialization through synthesis\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: iterative_loop\n  workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n  workflow_execution: autonomous\n  approvals: none\n  tracking: progressive_review_state\n  validation: convergence_detection\n\n# в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n# OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n# в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\noperating_principles:\n  core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n  approach: \"Dispatch focused review agent per dimension, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n  mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files. Review target is READ-ONLY.\"\n\n# в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n# USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n# в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\nuser_inputs:\n  review_target: \"[REVIEW_TARGET] - What to review. REQUIRED.\"\n  review_target_type: \"[spec-folder|skill|agent|track|files] - Target type for scope derivation. REQUIRED.\"\n  review_dimensions: \"[all|correctness,security,traceability,maintainability] - Dimensions to check. Default: all.\"\n  spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path for state files. REQUIRED.\"\n  lineage_mode: \"[auto|resume|restart] - Session lifecycle intent. Default: auto. The runtime only persists lineage events for `resume` (same sessionId, no archive) and `restart` (new sessionId, generation+1, prior review/ archived). `fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred and no longer accepted вҖ” see deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md В§Lifecycle Branches.\"\n  max_iterations: 7\n  convergence_threshold: 0.10\n\n# в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n# CONTEXT LOADING\n# в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\ncontext_loading:\n  trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n  purpose: \"Load prior review context for the target and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n  mcp_integration:\n    tool: memory_context\n    note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n    parameters: { input: \"{review_target}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n  when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n  behavior:\n    if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n    if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n\n# в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n# SKILL REFERENCE\n# в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\nskill_reference:\n  skill: deep-loop-workflows\n  skill_md: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md\n  references:\n    loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n    state_format: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md\n    convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md\n  templates:\n    config: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json\n    strategy: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md\n\n# в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n# AGENT CONFIGURATION\n# в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\nagent_config:\n  agent: deep-review\n  agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-review.md\"\n  # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n  mode: subagent\n  model: opus\n  leaf_only: true\n  tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob]\n  mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n  tool_call_budget: { target: 9, soft_max: 12, hard_max: 13 }\n\n# в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n# STATE FILE PATHS\n# в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\nstate_paths:\n  # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n  # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep\n  # root-local review/ and child phases keep local review/ packet dirs.\n  # Canonical root-spec write targets remain review/deep-review-config.json,\n  # review/deep-review-state.jsonl, and review/deep-review-findings-registry.json.\n  packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n  local_packet_dir: \"{spec_folder}/review\"\n  legacy_root_report: \"{spec_folder}/review-report.md\"\n  config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json\"\n  state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl\"\n  findings_registry: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json\"\n  strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n  dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n  pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\"\n  lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review.lock\"\n  prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n  iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n  iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n  # Per-iteration structured delta stream вҖ” complement to the canonical state_log\n  # append. MUST contain at least one record with `type === \"iteration\"`; variants\n  # like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer.\n  delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n  delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n  review_output: \"{artifact_dir}/review-report.md\"\n  resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n  archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n\n# в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n# WORKFLOW\n# в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\nworkflow:\n\n  step_resolve_artifact_root:\n    description: \"Resolve artifact directory вҖ” use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n    note: \"Root specs keep review artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/review/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/review/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/review_archive/{packet}/.\"\n    branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n    if_present:\n      bind:\n        artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_subfolder: null\n        artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n    if_absent:\n      command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'review')));\\\"\"\n      outputs:\n        - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local review owner directory\"\n        - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n        - artifact_dir: \"Resolved review packet directory for this target\"\n        - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local review archive directory for this target\"\n\n  step_fanout_spawn:\n    description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n    skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n    instructions: |\n      Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n      isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n      After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis вҖ” skip phase_init and\n      phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n      phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n    sub_steps:\n      step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n        description: \"Spawn all CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n        skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind != 'native'\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n            --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n            --loop-type review \\\n            --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n            --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true\n      step_fanout_spawn_native:\n        description: \"Dispatch each native lineage as a sequential deep-review sub-agent\"\n        skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind == 'native'\"\n        for_each: \"lineage in expanded native entries of config.fanout\"\n        dispatch:\n          agent: deep-review\n          model: opus\n          context: |\n            Execute the deep-review loop with these parameters:\n              spec_folder: {spec_folder}\n              config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: {artifact_dir}/lineages/{lineage.label}\n              session_id: fanout-{lineage.label}-{fanout_run_id}\n              executor: native\n            Run to convergence. Write all outputs to the override directory.\n        wait_for_completion: true\n\n  # в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ\n  # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n  # в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ\n  phase_init:\n    purpose: Create all state files for the review session and resolve review scope\n    steps:\n\n      step_preflight_contract:\n        action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n        verify:\n          - required_values_present: [review_target, review_target_type, review_dimensions, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold]\n          - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n          - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n          - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n        on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n\n      step_create_directories:\n        action: \"Create spec folder and canonical review packet directories if they don't exist\"\n        command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n\n      step_detect_resource_map:\n        action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist coverage-gate state\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n        classify:\n          present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n          absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n        outputs:\n          - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n          - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: concise resource-map snapshot for Known Context and charter framing. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_migrate_legacy_review_state:\n        action: \"Rehome legacy review artifacts into review/iterations before session classification\"\n        detect:\n          canonical_review_state:\n            - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n            - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n            - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n            - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n          legacy_review_state:\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/iteration-*.md\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause\"\n            - \"{state_paths.local_packet_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n            - \"{state_paths.legacy_root_report}\"\n          legacy_review_markers:\n            - \"scratch/deep-review-strategy.md exists\"\n            - \"scratch/deep-research-config.json declares mode == 'review' OR scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl contains mode == 'review'\"\n        migrate_only:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json -> {state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl -> {state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md -> {state_paths.strategy}\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md -> {state_paths.dashboard}\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/iteration-*.md -> {state_paths.iteration_dir}/\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause -> {state_paths.pause_sentinel}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.local_packet_dir}/iteration-*.md -> {state_paths.iteration_dir}/\"\n          - \"{state_paths.legacy_root_report} -> {state_paths.review_output}\"\n        on_canonical_present: \"Leave canonical review/ state untouched and do not overwrite it with legacy scratch artifacts.\"\n        on_legacy_detected: \"Move only the review-specific whitelist, append a migration event to the canonical JSONL, and leave unrelated scratch files untouched.\"\n        on_conflict: \"If canonical review/ state and legacy scratch review state both exist but disagree, halt for operator repair instead of merging contradictory state.\"\n        command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.iteration_dir} && if [ ! -e {state_paths.config} ] && [ ! -e {state_paths.state_log} ] && [ ! -e {state_paths.strategy} ] && [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md ] && ( [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json ] || [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl ] ); then [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json {state_paths.config}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl {state_paths.state_log}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md {state_paths.strategy}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md {state_paths.dashboard}; find {spec_folder}/scratch -maxdepth 1 -name 'iteration-*.md' -exec mv {} {state_paths.iteration_dir}/ \\\\; ; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause {state_paths.pause_sentinel}; [ -e {state_paths.legacy_root_report} ] && mv {state_paths.legacy_root_report} {state_paths.review_output}; if [ -e {state_paths.state_log} ]; then printf '%s\\n' '{\\\"type\\\":\\\"event\\\",\\\"event\\\":\\\"migration\\\",\\\"mode\\\":\\\"review\\\",\\\"legacyArtifacts\\\":[\\\"deep-research-config.json\\\",\\\"deep-research-state.jsonl\\\",\\\".deep-research-pause\\\"],\\\"canonicalArtifacts\\\":[\\\"deep-review-config.json\\\",\\\"deep-review-state.jsonl\\\",\\\".deep-review-pause\\\"],\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\\\"}' >> {state_paths.state_log}; fi; fi; find {state_paths.local_packet_dir} -maxdepth 1 -name 'iteration-*.md' -exec mv {} {state_paths.iteration_dir}/ \\\\; 2>/dev/null || true\"\n\n      step_acquire_lock:\n        action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n        on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed вҖ” another deep-review run already holds this packet.\"\n        note: \"Uses the promoted deep-loop-runtime loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory вҖ” best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n        # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n        # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n        on_halt:\n          action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n          applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\"]\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n        on_cancel:\n          action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n        on_workflow_exit:\n          action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent вҖ” safe to invoke when already released\"\n\n      step_classify_session:\n        action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        classify:\n          fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n          resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and config.mode == 'review' and agree on target/spec folder\"\n          completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n          invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n        outputs:\n          - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n        on_resume:\n          log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: phase_loop\n        on_restart:\n          action: \"Archive the current review packet under the root-level review_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n          command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n          set:\n            lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n            parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n            generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: step_create_config\n        note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md В§Lifecycle Branches for the one-session contract.\"\n        on_completed_session:\n          log: \"Prior session already completed. Either archive the completed review/ tree and start a fresh session, or jump straight to synthesis with the existing artifacts.\"\n          skip_to: phase_synthesis\n        on_invalid_state:\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Existing deep-review state in review/ is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid review packet before continuing.\"\n        on_fresh:\n          action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n\n      step_scope_discovery:\n        action: \"Resolve review target to a concrete file list based on target type\"\n        resolve:\n          spec-folder: |\n            1. Read spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md, checklist.md, implementation-summary.md\n            2. Discover implementation files referenced in spec artifacts\n            3. Discover test files associated with implementation\n            4. Set scope = all discovered files\n          skill: |\n            1. Read SKILL.md from .opencode/skills/{skill_name}/\n            2. Discover references/, assets/, scripts/ contents\n            3. Find agent definitions referencing this skill across runtimes\n            4. Find command entry points referencing this skill\n            5. Set scope = all discovered files\n          agent: |\n            1. Find agent definition across repo-managed runtimes (.claude/agents/, .opencode/agents/, .codex/agents/, .agents/)\n            2. Compare agent definitions for consistency\n            3. Set scope = all discovered agent files\n          track: |\n            1. List all child spec folders under specs/{track}/ or .opencode/specs/{track}/\n            2. For each: read spec.md + checklist.md\n            3. Set scope = all child spec artifacts\n          files: |\n            1. Expand glob patterns from review_target\n            2. Validate all files exist\n            3. Discover immediate cross-references (imports, links)\n            4. Set scope = expanded file list + cross-references\n        outputs:\n          - review_scope_files: \"List of all files in review scope\"\n          - cross_reference_targets: \"{ spec_paths: [...], code_paths: [...], test_paths: [...] }\"\n\n      step_order_dimensions:\n        action: \"Order review dimensions based on risk priority\"\n        algorithm: |\n          1. Iteration 0 (inventory pass): Build artifact map, identify file types, estimate complexity\n          2. Subsequent iterations follow risk-ordered deep passes:\n             correctness вҶ’ security вҶ’ traceability вҶ’ maintainability\n          3. If review_dimensions != \"all\", filter to only requested dimensions\n          4. Derive traceability protocol plan:\n             - core: spec_code, checklist_evidence\n             - overlay: skill_agent, agent_cross_runtime, feature_catalog_code, playbook_capability\n          5. If resource_map_present, reserve at least one traceability-oriented pass to cross-check target_files from applied/T-*.md against resource-map.md and classify touched / expected-by-scope / gap / absent-from-map outcomes\n          6. Store ordered list as dimension_queue\n        outputs:\n          - dimension_queue: \"Ordered list of dimensions to review\"\n          - inventory_pass: true\n\n      step_normalize_review_dimensions:\n        action: \"Normalize reviewDimensions once during init for config + JSONL reuse\"\n        outputs:\n          - review_dimensions_normalized: \"Canonical string[] for deep-review-config.json\"\n          - review_dimensions_json: \"JSON.stringify(review_dimensions_normalized) for JSONL config record\"\n        normalize: |\n          Accept {review_dimensions} in any of these shapes and convert once:\n            - \"all\" вҶ’ [\"correctness\",\"security\",\"traceability\",\"maintainability\"]\n            - \"correctness,security\" вҶ’ [\"correctness\",\"security\"]\n            - [\"correctness\"] вҶ’ [\"correctness\"]\n          Every element MUST be one of the four canonical dimension names.\n\n      step_create_config:\n        action: \"Create deep-review-config.json from template with review-specific fields\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json\n        populate:\n          topic: \"Review: {review_target}\"\n          mode: \"review\"\n          sessionId: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n          parentSessionId: null\n          lineageMode: \"new\"\n          generation: 1\n          continuedFromRun: null\n          reviewTarget: \"{review_target}\"\n          reviewTargetType: \"{review_target_type}\"\n          # Reuse the single normalized init-time value from step_normalize_review_dimensions.\n          reviewDimensions: \"{review_dimensions_normalized}\"\n          resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n          reviewScopeFiles: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n          severityThreshold: \"P2\"\n          crossReference:\n            core: [\"spec_code\", \"checklist_evidence\"]\n            overlay: [\"skill_agent\", \"agent_cross_runtime\", \"feature_catalog_code\", \"playbook_capability\"]\n          maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          # Semantic: weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio. See SKILL.md В§\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n          convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n          stuckThreshold: 2\n          maxDurationMinutes: 120\n          specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n          # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n          # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-review.md:71 (default true; false when flag is set).\n          # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n          resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n          createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n          status: \"initialized\"\n          releaseReadinessState: \"in-progress\"\n          executionMode: \"auto\"\n        output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n\n      step_create_state_log:\n        action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record including review fields and lineage metadata\"\n        note: \"Reuse review_dimensions_json from step_normalize_review_dimensions. Never re-normalize or wrap the raw template value.\"\n        # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n        # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n        content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"reviewTarget\":\"{review_target}\",\"reviewTargetType\":\"{review_target_type}\",\"reviewDimensions\":{review_dimensions_json},\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"sessionId\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"parentSessionId\":null,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"generation\":1,\"continuedFromRun\":null,\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\"}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n\n      step_create_findings_registry:\n        action: \"Initialize reducer-owned review findings registry\"\n        content: '{\"sessionId\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"generation\":1,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"openFindings\":[],\"resolvedFindings\":[],\"repeatedFindings\":[],\"dimensionCoverage\":{\"correctness\":false,\"security\":false,\"traceability\":false,\"maintainability\":false},\"findingsBySeverity\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"openFindingsCount\":0,\"resolvedFindingsCount\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0.0}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n\n      step_create_strategy:\n        action: \"Create review strategy file from deep_review_strategy.md template\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md\n        populate:\n          review_target: \"{review_target}\"\n          review_target_type: \"{review_target_type}\"\n          dimensions: \"{dimension_queue}\"\n          scope_files: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n          cross_reference_targets: \"{cross_reference_targets}\"\n          max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n        output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_context:\n        action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n        condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n        action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot and add Resource Map Coverage to the Review Charter. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_init_complete:\n        log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, and strategy files created. Review scope: {review_scope_files_count} files, {dimension_queue_count} dimensions.\"\n        set: { current_iteration: 1, stuck_count: 0, p0_count: 0, p1_count: 0, p2_count: 0 }\n\n  # в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ\n  # PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n  # в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ\n  phase_loop:\n    purpose: Dispatch review agent iterations until convergence\n    repeat: true\n    max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n    steps:\n\n      step_read_state:\n        action: \"Read current state from JSONL, strategy, and config\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n        extract:\n          - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n          - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n          - last_newFindingsRatio: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from last iteration record\"\n          - last_focus: \"Extract focus/dimension from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - ratio_prev: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - ratio_latest: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - next_dimension: \"Next uncovered dimension from dimension_queue in strategy.md\"\n          - dimensions_covered: \"List of dimensions already reviewed\"\n          - dimensions_remaining: \"List of dimensions not yet reviewed\"\n          - dimension_coverage: \"covered / total dimensions\"\n          - coverage_age: \"Iterations since dimension coverage last changed; require >= 1 before STOP\"\n          - p0_count: \"Count P0 findings across all iterations\"\n          - p1_count: \"Count P1 findings across all iterations\"\n          - p2_count: \"Count P2 findings across all iterations\"\n          - resource_map_present: \"Extract boolean from deep-review-config.json, default false\"\n          - resource_map_prompt_line: \"If resource_map_present is true, return 'Resource Map Coverage: cross-check target_files from {spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md against {spec_folder}/resource-map.md and classify only missed coverage as gaps.' Else return 'Resource Map Coverage: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.'\"\n          - session_id: \"Extract sessionId from deep-review-config.json\"\n          - generation: \"Extract generation from deep-review-config.json, else 1\"\n          - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: dimension (ratio, P0/P1/P2)'\"\n          - latest_status: \"Extract status from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - last_claim_adjudication_passed: \"Scan state.jsonl for the most recent `claim_adjudication` event; use its `passed` boolean. Default true when no event exists or when activeP0 + activeP1 == 0 (gate is vacuous without adjudicable findings).\"\n          - claim_adjudication_active_count: \"Count of active P0/P1 findings at the time of the last claim_adjudication event; 0 when none exist\"\n          - security_sensitive_fix_scope: \"Boolean true when the current review is a rerun after fixes involving security, path disclosure, auth/authz, sandboxing, env precedence, public schemas, persistence, or user-visible error payloads; derive from the latest review report, remediation notes, or planning packet when present, else false.\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_required_rows: \"Count prior active or remediated P0/P1 findings, plus any prior security/path P2 findings, that require closed-gate replay before STOP.\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows: \"Count required replay rows marked PASS with file:line or command evidence and producer/consumer/matrix coverage.\"\n\n      step_check_pause_sentinel:\n        action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n        check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n        if_exists:\n          set:\n            pending_stop_event: \"paused\"\n            pending_stop_reason: \"userPaused\"\n            pending_stop_detail: \"sentinel file detected\"\n          skip_to: step_normalize_pause_events\n        if_not_exists:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_graph_convergence:\n        action: \"Evaluate coverage-graph convergence before the inline review convergence vote\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n        transform: |\n          1. Call graph convergence on the current review lineage before the inline 3-signal vote.\n          2. Record the decision as one of CONTINUE, STOP_ALLOWED, STOP_BLOCKED.\n          3. Preserve raw graph signals and blockers for reducer rollup and blocked-stop evidence.\n          4. Normalize blockers to both JSON array and CSV forms for downstream stop handling.\n          5. Set graph_stop_blocked = true only when graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\".\n        bash: 'node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"review\" --session-id \"{session_id}\"'\n        note: \"Invoke the runtime script directly. Review-side graph convergence must run before the inline review stop vote.\"\n        append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"graph_convergence\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"decision\":\"{graph_decision}\",\"signals\":{graph_signals_json},\"blockers\":{graph_blockers_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n        outputs:\n          - graph_decision: \"CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED\"\n          - graph_signals_json: \"JSON object returned by convergence.cjs\"\n          - graph_blockers_json: \"JSON array of graph blockers when present, else []\"\n          - graph_blockers_csv: \"Comma-separated blocker summary when graph blocks STOP, else empty string\"\n          - graph_stop_blocked: \"Boolean true when graph_decision == STOP_BLOCKED\"\n\n      step_check_convergence:\n        action: \"Evaluate graph-assisted review stop conditions and the legal-stop decision tree\"\n        algorithm: |\n          0. CLAIM-ADJUDICATION PRE-CHECK (universal STOP veto; runs before hard stops and composite convergence):\n             claim_adjudication_gate_pass = (last_claim_adjudication_passed != false) OR (p0_count + p1_count == 0)\n             If claim_adjudication_gate_pass == false:\n               candidate_decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n               stop_blocked = true\n               stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n               blocked_gates = [\"claimAdjudicationGate\"]\n               recovery_strategy = \"Reviewer must add typed claim-adjudication packets (claim, evidenceRefs, counterevidenceSought, alternativeExplanation, finalSeverity, confidence, downgradeTrigger) for every active P0/P1 finding before STOP is allowed.\"\n               Skip hard stops (1) and composite convergence (4); proceed directly to step 5 legal-stop decision-tree assembly so blocked_by_json, gate outputs, and the blocked_stop event still populate consistently.\n          1. HARD STOPS:\n             a) if iteration_count >= max_iterations: set decision = \"STOP\", stopReason = \"maxIterationsReached\", hard_stop_reason = \"max_iterations_reached\", preserve any failed legal-stop gates as terminal evidence, and proceed to synthesis without legal-stop veto\n             b) if all dimensions clean AND required traceability protocols are covered AND p0_count == 0 AND p1_count == 0 AND coverage_age >= 1 AND all quality gates pass (evidence: every P0/P1 has file:line; scope: all findings within target; coverage: all dimensions reviewed): mark hard_stop_reason = \"all_dimensions_clean\" and promote to STOP candidate\n             Operator stop reasons (`maxIterationsReached`, `manualStop`, `userPaused`, unrecoverable `error`) are terminal ceilings. They do not hide failed gates; they record them in synthesis and stop dispatch.\n          2. STUCK DETECTION (threshold 2):\n             if stuck_count >= 2: STUCK_RECOVERY\n          3. GRAPH CONVERGENCE PREREQUISITE:\n               graph_decision, graph_signals_json, and graph_blockers_json are already populated by step_graph_convergence.\n               Final STOP is never legal unless the inline review vote says STOP AND graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\".\n               If graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\", set stop_blocked = true and route through blocked_stop emission instead of stopping.\n          4. COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE (3-signal weighted vote with split thresholds):\n               signals = []\n               a) Rolling average (w=0.30, window=2, needs 2+ iterations):\n                  avg = mean(last 2 newFindingsRatios)\n                  stop if avg <= 0.08\n               b) MAD noise floor (w=0.25, needs 3+ iterations):\n                  noiseFloor = MAD(all ratios) * 1.4826\n                  stop if latest ratio <= noiseFloor\n               c) Dimension coverage (w=0.45):\n                  coverage = dimensions_covered / total_dimensions\n                  stop if coverage >= 1.0 AND required traceability protocols are covered AND coverage_age >= 1\n               Redistribute weights for unavailable signals.\n               if latest ratio <= 0.05: mark no_progress_threshold_reached\n               if weighted_stop_score >= 0.60: inline STOP becomes a candidate and binary gates must run\n          5. LEGAL-STOP DECISION TREE (review-specific gates; runs whenever step 0, all-dimensions-clean, or the composite vote promotes STOP to a candidate; terminal max-iteration/manual/error stops bypass veto and record failed gates as evidence):\n               a) convergenceGate: pass when a hard-stop condition is met OR weighted_stop_score >= 0.60; record score\n               b) dimensionCoverageGate: pass when configured dimensions and required traceability coverage are complete and coverage_age >= 1; record covered and missing dimensions\n               c) p0ResolutionGate: pass when activeP0 == 0; record activeP0\n               d) evidenceDensityGate: pass when every active P0/P1 has concrete file:line evidence and no active P0/P1 relies only on inference; record avgEvidencePerFinding\n               e) hotspotSaturationGate: pass when review hotspots have been revisited enough times to satisfy the saturation heuristic\n               f) claimAdjudicationGate: pass when claim_adjudication_gate_pass == true (i.e. last_claim_adjudication_passed != false OR there are no active P0/P1 findings to adjudicate); record last_claim_adjudication_passed and claim_adjudication_active_count\n               g) fixCompletenessReplayGate: pass when security_sensitive_fix_scope == false OR every required closed-gate replay row passes with file:line or command evidence and producer/consumer/matrix coverage; record security_sensitive_fix_scope, fix_completeness_replay_required_rows, and fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows\n               h) candidateCoverageGate: skip entirely when `reviewDepthSchemaVersion` is not 2 on the latest iteration. Otherwise pass when the current iteration's `reviewDepthApplicability.scopeClass` is `trivial` with `enforcement: \"skip\"` AND `reviewDepthApplicability.evidenceRefs` is non-empty, OR when the reducer registry's `searchDebt` is empty AND `candidateCoverage.covered` is a superset of `searchCoverage.requiredBugClasses` for the lineage. Otherwise pass = false; record `searchDebt` items as blocked-stop evidence; blocker name = \"candidateCoverageGate\"; recovery_strategy = \"Resolve deferred/blocked obligations in next iteration or downgrade scope explicitly to trivial with cited evidence.\"\n               i) graphlessFallbackGate: skip when `reviewDepthSchemaVersion` is not 2 OR the reducer registry's last-iteration `searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode` is `graph`. Applies when graphCoverageMode is `graphless_fallback` or `unavailable_blocked`. Pass when graphCoverageMode is `graphless_fallback` AND at least one `searchLedger` row exists for each entry in `searchCoverage.requiredBugClasses` with `searchActions[].method` in {\"direct_read\",\"exact_grep\",\"semantic_search\",\"code_graph_status_check\",\"producer_consumer_trace\",\"negative_test_inspection\"} AND non-empty `evidenceRefs`. Fail automatically when graphCoverageMode is `unavailable_blocked`; record the explicit unavailability reason. Otherwise pass = false; blocker name = \"graphlessFallbackGate\"; recovery_strategy = \"Add cited fallback ledger rows (direct read, exact search, producer/consumer trace, negative-test inspection) or set graphCoverageMode to 'graph' once graph data is available.\"\n             if STOP is a candidate and any gate fails:\n               decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n               stop_blocked = true\n               stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n               blocked_by_json = JSON array of failing gate names (always include \"claimAdjudicationGate\" when claim_adjudication_gate_pass == false, \"fixCompletenessReplayGate\" when fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass == false, \"candidateCoverageGate\" when candidate_coverage_gate_pass == false, and \"graphlessFallbackGate\" when graphless_fallback_gate_pass == false)\n               blocked_by_csv = comma-separated list of failing gate names\n               convergence_gate_pass = boolean\n               convergence_gate_score = numeric convergence score\n               dimension_coverage_gate_pass = boolean\n               dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json = JSON array of covered review dimensions\n               dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json = JSON array of missing review dimensions\n               p0_resolution_gate_pass = boolean\n               active_p0_count = number of active P0 findings\n               evidence_density_gate_pass = boolean\n               avg_evidence_per_finding = numeric evidence density\n               hotspot_saturation_gate_pass = boolean\n               claim_adjudication_gate_pass = boolean\n               claim_adjudication_active_count = numeric count of active P0/P1 at the gate\n               fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass = boolean\n               security_sensitive_fix_scope = boolean\n               fix_completeness_replay_required_rows = numeric count of closed-gate replay rows required for security-sensitive fix reruns\n               fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows = numeric count of required closed-gate replay rows marked PASS with evidence\n               candidate_coverage_gate_pass = boolean\n               candidate_coverage_search_debt_json = JSON array of reducer-owned searchDebt obligations blocking STOP, else []\n               candidate_coverage_missing_json = JSON array of required bug classes not present in candidateCoverage.covered, else []\n               graphless_fallback_gate_pass = boolean\n               graphless_fallback_mode = latest reducer-owned searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode value\n               graphless_fallback_missing_json = JSON array of required bug classes without cited fallback ledger rows, else []\n               graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason = explicit reason when graphCoverageMode == \"unavailable_blocked\", else empty string\n               recovery_strategy = one-line hint describing the next review action needed to satisfy the failed gates; combine candidateCoverageGate and graphlessFallbackGate recovery guidance when both fail (when claimAdjudicationGate is the failing gate, prefer the step-0 recovery_strategy already set)\n          6. COMBINED STOP RULE:\n               a) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\": decision = \"STOP\"\n               b) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\":\n                    decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n                    stop_blocked = true\n                    stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n                    # Blocked-stop closure: blockedBy must be string[] per the\n                    # published review blocked-stop contract. Extract the `.type`\n                    # field from each structured graph blocker; preserve the full\n                    # objects in graph_blocker_detail_json for operator inspection.\n                    blocked_by_json = JSON.stringify(graph_blockers_json.map(b => typeof b === \"string\" ? b : (b && b.type) || \"graph_blocker\"))\n                    blocked_by_csv = graph_blockers_csv\n                    graph_blocker_detail_json = graph_blockers_json\n                    recovery_strategy = \"Resolve review coverage-graph blockers before stopping.\"\n               c) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"CONTINUE\":\n                    decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n                    stop_blocked = false\n                    reason = \"graph_convergence_continue\"\n               d) else keep the existing STUCK_RECOVERY or CONTINUE outcome\n        outputs:\n          - decision: \"STOP | BLOCKED | STUCK_RECOVERY | CONTINUE\"\n          - reason: \"Human-readable stop reason\"\n          - stop_blocked: \"Boolean true when STOP is vetoed by inline legal-stop gates or graph_decision == STOP_BLOCKED\"\n          - blocked_by_json: \"JSON array of failed legal-stop gates when decision == BLOCKED\"\n          - blocked_by_csv: \"Comma-separated list of failed legal-stop gates when decision == BLOCKED\"\n          - convergence_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for convergenceGate\"\n          - convergence_gate_score: \"Numeric score recorded for convergenceGate\"\n          - dimension_coverage_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for dimensionCoverageGate\"\n          - dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json: \"JSON array of covered review dimensions\"\n          - dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json: \"JSON array of missing review dimensions\"\n          - p0_resolution_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for p0ResolutionGate\"\n          - active_p0_count: \"Active P0 finding count at stop-check time\"\n          - evidence_density_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for evidenceDensityGate\"\n          - avg_evidence_per_finding: \"Numeric evidence density for active findings\"\n          - hotspot_saturation_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for hotspotSaturationGate\"\n          - claim_adjudication_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for claimAdjudicationGate (false vetoes STOP)\"\n          - claim_adjudication_active_count: \"Count of active P0/P1 findings evaluated by claimAdjudicationGate\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for fixCompletenessReplayGate (false vetoes STOP on security-sensitive fix reruns)\"\n          - security_sensitive_fix_scope: \"Boolean true when the review is a security-sensitive fix rerun\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_required_rows: \"Count of closed-gate replay rows required before STOP\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows: \"Count of required closed-gate replay rows that passed with evidence\"\n          - candidate_coverage_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for candidateCoverageGate (false vetoes STOP for unresolved reducer-owned search debt or uncovered required bug classes)\"\n          - candidate_coverage_search_debt_json: \"JSON array of reducer-owned searchDebt obligations used as blocked-stop evidence\"\n          - candidate_coverage_missing_json: \"JSON array of required bug classes missing from candidateCoverage.covered\"\n          - graphless_fallback_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for graphlessFallbackGate (false vetoes STOP when graphless fallback evidence is absent or unavailable_blocked)\"\n          - graphless_fallback_mode: \"Latest reducer-owned searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode value\"\n          - graphless_fallback_missing_json: \"JSON array of required bug classes missing cited fallback ledger rows\"\n          - graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason: \"Explicit unavailability reason when graphCoverageMode == unavailable_blocked\"\n          - graph_decision: \"CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED from step_graph_convergence\"\n          - graph_signals_json: \"JSON object returned by graph convergence\"\n          - graph_blockers_json: \"JSON array of graph blockers\"\n          - graph_blockers_csv: \"Comma-separated graph blocker summary\"\n          - recovery_strategy: \"One-line hint describing the next review action when decision == BLOCKED or STUCK_RECOVERY\"\n\n      step_emit_blocked_stop:","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":634,"totalLines":635,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1781764129604,"end":1781764129611}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b44746d26baa3f3016a33902184648191a69573232056f10e"}},"id":"prt_ed96b031e001bG9XbB60GdK227","sessionID":"ses_126960be2ffewGSaH1Z0io46OH","messageID":"msg_ed96ad021001BRShGoUZQuXYyJ"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781764129625,"sessionID":"ses_126960be2ffewGSaH1Z0io46OH","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_QAM9Rn7gJFMGBS2Jafm72bBT","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json","offset":1,"limit":1200},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"topic\": \"\",\n3:   \"sessionId\": \"\",\n4:   \"parentSessionId\": null,\n5:   \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n6:   \"generation\": 1,\n7:   \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n8:   \"migrationWindowEndsAt\": \"\",\n9:   \"maxIterations\": 7,\n10:   \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.10,\n11:   \"stuckThreshold\": 2,\n12:   \"maxDurationMinutes\": 120,\n13:   \"maxToolCallsPerIteration\": 12,\n14:   \"maxMinutesPerIteration\": 10,\n15:   \"progressiveSynthesis\": false,\n16:   \"specFolder\": \"\",\n17:   \"createdAt\": \"\",\n18:   \"status\": \"initialized\",\n19:   \"releaseReadinessState\": \"in-progress\",\n20:   \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n21:   \"executor\": {\n22:     \"kind\": \"native\",\n23:     \"model\": null,\n24:     \"reasoningEffort\": null,\n25:     \"serviceTier\": null,\n26:     \"sandboxMode\": null,\n27:     \"timeoutSeconds\": 900\n28:   },\n29:   \"mode\": \"review\",\n30:   \"reviewTarget\": \"\",\n31:   \"reviewTargetType\": \"spec-folder\",\n32:   \"reviewDimensions\": [\n33:     \"correctness\",\n34:     \"security\",\n35:     \"traceability\",\n36:     \"maintainability\"\n37:   ],\n38:   \"severityThreshold\": \"P2\",\n39:   \"crossReference\": {\n40:     \"core\": [\n41:       \"spec_code\",\n42:       \"checklist_evidence\"\n43:     ],\n44:     \"overlay\": [\n45:       \"skill_agent\",\n46:       \"agent_cross_runtime\",\n47:       \"feature_catalog_code\",\n48:       \"playbook_capability\"\n49:     ]\n50:   },\n51:   \"qualityGateThreshold\": true,\n52:   \"runtimeCapabilityResolver\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs\",\n53:   \"reducerScriptPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs\",\n54:   \"fileProtection\": {\n55:     \"deep-review-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n56:     \"deep-review-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n57:     \"deep-review-findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n58:     \"deep-review-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n59:     \"deep-review-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n60:     \".deep-review-pause\": \"operator-controlled\",\n61:     \"review-report.md\": \"mutable\",\n62:     \"review-report-v*.md\": \"write-once\",\n63:     \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\"\n64:   },\n65:   \"reducer\": {\n66:     \"enabled\": true,\n67:     \"inputs\": [\n68:       \"latestJSONLDelta\",\n69:       \"newIterationFile\",\n70:       \"priorReducedState\"\n71:     ],\n72:     \"outputs\": [\n73:       \"findingsRegistry\",\n74:       \"dashboardMetrics\",\n75:       \"strategyUpdates\"\n76:     ],\n77:     \"metrics\": [\n78:       \"dimensionsCovered\",\n79:       \"findingsBySeverity\",\n80:       \"openFindings\",\n81:       \"resolvedFindings\",\n82:       \"convergenceScore\"\n83:     ]\n84:   },\n85:   \"_optimizerManaged\": {\n86:     \"description\": \"Fields managed by the offline loop optimizer (042.004). See optimizer-manifest.json for the canonical tunable/locked field registry.\",\n87:     \"manifestPath\": \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json\",\n88:     \"tunableFields\": [\"convergenceThreshold\", \"stuckThreshold\", \"maxIterations\"],\n89:     \"lockedFields\": [\"lineageMode\", \"reducer\", \"fileProtection\", \"sessionId\", \"mode\", \"reviewDimensions\"],\n90:     \"promotionMode\": \"advisory-only\"\n91:   }\n92: }\n\n(End of file - total 92 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"topic\": \"\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"\",\n  \"parentSessionId\": null,\n  \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n  \"migrationWindowEndsAt\": \"\",\n  \"maxIterations\": 7,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.10,\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 2,\n  \"maxDurationMinutes\": 120,\n  \"maxToolCallsPerIteration\": 12,\n  \"maxMinutesPerIteration\": 10,\n  \"progressiveSynthesis\": false,\n  \"specFolder\": \"\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"\",\n  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n  \"releaseReadinessState\": \"in-progress\",\n  \"executionMode\": \"auto\",","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json","text":"{\n  \"topic\": \"\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"\",\n  \"parentSessionId\": null,\n  \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n  \"migrationWindowEndsAt\": \"\",\n  \"maxIterations\": 7,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.10,\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 2,\n  \"maxDurationMinutes\": 120,\n  \"maxToolCallsPerIteration\": 12,\n  \"maxMinutesPerIteration\": 10,\n  \"progressiveSynthesis\": false,\n  \"specFolder\": \"\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"\",\n  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n  \"releaseReadinessState\": \"in-progress\",\n  \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n  \"executor\": {\n    \"kind\": \"native\",\n    \"model\": null,\n    \"reasoningEffort\": null,\n    \"serviceTier\": null,\n    \"sandboxMode\": null,\n    \"timeoutSeconds\": 900\n  },\n  \"mode\": \"review\",\n  \"reviewTarget\": \"\",\n  \"reviewTargetType\": \"spec-folder\",\n  \"reviewDimensions\": [\n    \"correctness\",\n    \"security\",\n    \"traceability\",\n    \"maintainability\"\n  ],\n  \"severityThreshold\": \"P2\",\n  \"crossReference\": {\n    \"core\": [\n      \"spec_code\",\n      \"checklist_evidence\"\n    ],\n    \"overlay\": [\n      \"skill_agent\",\n      \"agent_cross_runtime\",\n      \"feature_catalog_code\",\n      \"playbook_capability\"\n    ]\n  },\n  \"qualityGateThreshold\": true,\n  \"runtimeCapabilityResolver\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs\",\n  \"reducerScriptPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs\",\n  \"fileProtection\": {\n    \"deep-review-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n    \"deep-review-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n    \"deep-review-findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"deep-review-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n    \"deep-review-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \".deep-review-pause\": \"operator-controlled\",\n    \"review-report.md\": \"mutable\",\n    \"review-report-v*.md\": \"write-once\",\n    \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\"\n  },\n  \"reducer\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"inputs\": [\n      \"latestJSONLDelta\",\n      \"newIterationFile\",\n      \"priorReducedState\"\n    ],\n    \"outputs\": [\n      \"findingsRegistry\",\n      \"dashboardMetrics\",\n      \"strategyUpdates\"\n    ],\n    \"metrics\": [\n      \"dimensionsCovered\",\n      \"findingsBySeverity\",\n      \"openFindings\",\n      \"resolvedFindings\",\n      \"convergenceScore\"\n    ]\n  },\n  \"_optimizerManaged\": {\n    \"description\": \"Fields managed by the offline loop optimizer (042.004). See optimizer-manifest.json for the canonical tunable/locked field registry.\",\n    \"manifestPath\": \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json\",\n    \"tunableFields\": [\"convergenceThreshold\", \"stuckThreshold\", \"maxIterations\"],\n    \"lockedFields\": [\"lineageMode\", \"reducer\", \"fileProtection\", \"sessionId\", \"mode\", \"reviewDimensions\"],\n    \"promotionMode\": \"advisory-only\"\n  }\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":92,"totalLines":92,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json","time":{"start":1781764129620,"end":1781764129624}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b44746d26baa3f3016a339021848081918397a1483ce78bc5"}},"id":"prt_ed96b0346001CdxQrEGyEytYui","sessionID":"ses_126960be2ffewGSaH1Z0io46OH","messageID":"msg_ed96ad021001BRShGoUZQuXYyJ"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781764129645,"sessionID":"ses_126960be2ffewGSaH1Z0io46OH","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_PFzKlcCA0IeHWJLyx9AafsPq","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md","offset":1,"limit":1200},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review Strategy Template\n3: description: Runtime template copied to review/ during initialization to track review progress, dimension coverage, findings, and outcomes across iterations.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review strategy template\"\n6:   - \"review dimension tracking\"\n7:   - \"exhausted review approaches\"\n8:   - \"review session tracking\"\n9: importance_tier: normal\n10: contextType: planning\n11: ---\n12: \n13: # Deep Review Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n14: \n15: Runtime template copied into the resolved `{artifact_dir}/` during initialization. Tracks review progress across iterations.\n16: \n17: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n18: \n19: ### Purpose\n20: \n21: Serves as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep review session. Records which dimensions remain, what was found (P0/P1/P2), what review approaches worked or failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n22: \n23: ### Usage\n24: \n25: - **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Review Dimensions, Known Context, and Review Boundaries from config and memory context.\n26: - **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, reviews the assigned dimension/files, updates findings, marks dimensions complete, and sets new Next Focus.\n27: - **Mutability:** Mutable, updated by both orchestrator and agents throughout the session.\n28: - **Protection:** None (shared mutable state). Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n29: - **Ownership:** Machine-managed metrics and coverage blocks are wrapped in explicit ownership markers. Human commentary and operator overrides live outside those markers.\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: ## 2. TOPIC\n34: [Review target description from config -- set during initialization]\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ## 3. REVIEW DIMENSIONS (remaining)\n39: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n40: - [ ] D1 Correctness, Logic errors, off-by-one, wrong return types, broken invariants\n41: - [ ] D2 Security, Injection, auth bypass, secrets exposure, unsafe deserialization\n42: - [ ] D3 Traceability, Spec/code alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity\n43: - [ ] D4 Maintainability, Patterns, clarity, documentation quality, safe follow-on change cost\n44: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n45: \n46: ---\n47: \n48: ## 4. NON-GOALS\n49: [What this review session is NOT trying to assess -- populated during initialization]\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: ## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n54: [Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: ## 6. COMPLETED DIMENSIONS\n59: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n60: [None yet -- populated as iterations complete dimension reviews]\n61: \n62: | Dimension | Verdict | Iteration | Summary |\n63: |-----------|---------|-----------|---------|\n64: | [D1 Correctness] | [PASS/CONDITIONAL/FAIL] | [N] | [1-sentence result] |\n65: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n66: \n67: ---\n68: \n69: ## 7. RUNNING FINDINGS\n70: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n71: - **P0 (Critical):** 0 active\n72: - **P1 (Major):** 0 active\n73: - **P2 (Minor):** 0 active\n74: - **Delta this iteration:** +0 P0, +0 P1, +0 P2\n75: \n76: [Findings are tracked in `deep-review-findings-registry.json`. This section provides a running count summary updated after each iteration.]\n77: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ## 8. WHAT WORKED\n82: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n83: - [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n84: \n85: ---\n86: \n87: ## 9. WHAT FAILED\n88: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n89: - [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ## 10. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n94: [Populated when a review approach has been tried from multiple angles without yielding new findings]\n95: \n96: ### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n97: - What was tried: [specific review approaches attempted]\n98: - Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n99: - Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n100: \n101: ### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n102: - What worked: [successful review approaches in this category]\n103: - Prefer for: [related dimensions where this category may help]\n104: \n105: ---\n106: \n107: ## 11. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n108: [Review angles that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n109: - [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n110: \n111: ---\n112: \n113: ## 12. NEXT FOCUS\n114: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n115: [Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration. Includes target dimension and/or specific files to review.]\n116: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n117: \n118: ---\n119: \n120: ## 13. KNOWN CONTEXT\n121: [Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n122: \n123: ---\n124: \n125: ## 14. CROSS-REFERENCE STATUS\n126: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n127: [Alignment checks completed across core and overlay protocols]\n128: \n129: | Protocol | Level | Status | Iteration | Notes |\n130: |----------|-------|--------|-----------|-------|\n131: | `spec_code` | core | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked] | [N] | [details] |\n132: | `checklist_evidence` | core | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked] | [N] | [details] |\n133: | `skill_agent` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n134: | `agent_cross_runtime` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n135: | `feature_catalog_code` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n136: | `playbook_capability` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n137: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n138: \n139: ---\n140: \n141: ## 15. FILES UNDER REVIEW\n142: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n143: [Per-file coverage state table -- populated during initialization from scope discovery]\n144: \n145: | File | Dimensions Reviewed | Last Iteration | Findings | Status |\n146: |------|-------------------|----------------|----------|--------|\n147: | [path/to/file] | [D1, D3] | [N] | [0 P0, 1 P1, 2 P2] | [partial/complete] |\n148: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ## 16. REVIEW BOUNDARIES\n153: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n154: - Max iterations: [from config]\n155: - Convergence threshold: [from config]\n156: - Rolling STOP threshold: 0.08\n157: - No-progress threshold: 0.05\n158: - Coverage stabilization passes required: 1\n159: - Session lineage: sessionId=[from config.sessionId], parentSessionId=[from config.parentSessionId], generation=[from config.generation], lineageMode=[from config.lineageMode]\n160: - Findings registry: `deep-review-findings-registry.json`\n161: - Release-readiness states: in-progress | converged | release-blocking\n162: - Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n163: - Severity threshold: [from config.severityThreshold]\n164: - Review target type: [from config.reviewTargetType]\n165: - Cross-reference checks: core=[from config.crossReference.core], overlay=[from config.crossReference.overlay]\n166: - Started: [timestamp]\n167: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n168: \n169: ---\n170: \n171: ## 17. EXAMPLE (POPULATED)\n172: \n173: Reference snippet showing a partially populated strategy file mid-review. Use this as a visual anchor when opening a live strategy doc.\n174: \n175: ```markdown\n176: ## 1. REVIEW CHARTER\n177: - Target: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research (skill, v1.4.0)\n178: - Dimensions: correctness, test-coverage, cross-runtime-parity, observability\n179: - Stop conditions: rolling newInfoRatio < 0.08 for 2 iterations OR all dimensions converged OR max=7 reached\n180: - Success criteria: zero P0 in correctness; test-coverage P0 resolved or deferred with rationale\n181: \n182: ## 4. NEXT FOCUS\n183: - Dimension: test-coverage\n184: - Files: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs, .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/deep-research-contract-parity.vitest.ts\n185: - Why: Iteration 2 surfaced a P0 (convergence-path coverage gap); needs a focused follow-up before correctness can terminate PASS.\n186: \n187: ## 9. COVERAGE MATRIX\n188: | Dimension            | Status     | Iterations touched |\n189: |----------------------|------------|--------------------|\n190: | correctness          | converged  | 1                  |\n191: | test-coverage        | converging | 2, 4               |\n192: | cross-runtime-parity | converging | 3                  |\n193: | observability        | converging | 4                  |\n194: ```\n\n(End of file - total 194 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to review/ during initialization to track review progress, dimension coverage, findings, and outcomes across iterations.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review strategy template\"\n  - \"review dimension tracking\"\n  - \"exhausted review approaches\"\n  - \"review session tracking\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\n---\n\n# Deep Review Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied into the resolved `{artifact_dir}/` during initialization. Tracks review progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to review/ during initialization to track review progress, dimension coverage, findings, and outcomes across iterations.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review strategy template\"\n  - \"review dimension tracking\"\n  - \"exhausted review approaches\"\n  - \"review session tracking\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\n---\n\n# Deep Review Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied into the resolved `{artifact_dir}/` during initialization. Tracks review progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nServes as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep review session. Records which dimensions remain, what was found (P0/P1/P2), what review approaches worked or failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n\n### Usage\n\n- **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Review Dimensions, Known Context, and Review Boundaries from config and memory context.\n- **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, reviews the assigned dimension/files, updates findings, marks dimensions complete, and sets new Next Focus.\n- **Mutability:** Mutable, updated by both orchestrator and agents throughout the session.\n- **Protection:** None (shared mutable state). Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n- **Ownership:** Machine-managed metrics and coverage blocks are wrapped in explicit ownership markers. Human commentary and operator overrides live outside those markers.\n\n---\n\n## 2. TOPIC\n[Review target description from config -- set during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 3. REVIEW DIMENSIONS (remaining)\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- [ ] D1 Correctness, Logic errors, off-by-one, wrong return types, broken invariants\n- [ ] D2 Security, Injection, auth bypass, secrets exposure, unsafe deserialization\n- [ ] D3 Traceability, Spec/code alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity\n- [ ] D4 Maintainability, Patterns, clarity, documentation quality, safe follow-on change cost\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n[What this review session is NOT trying to assess -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n[Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 6. COMPLETED DIMENSIONS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n[None yet -- populated as iterations complete dimension reviews]\n\n| Dimension | Verdict | Iteration | Summary |\n|-----------|---------|-----------|---------|\n| [D1 Correctness] | [PASS/CONDITIONAL/FAIL] | [N] | [1-sentence result] |\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 7. RUNNING FINDINGS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- **P0 (Critical):** 0 active\n- **P1 (Major):** 0 active\n- **P2 (Minor):** 0 active\n- **Delta this iteration:** +0 P0, +0 P1, +0 P2\n\n[Findings are tracked in `deep-review-findings-registry.json`. This section provides a running count summary updated after each iteration.]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 8. WHAT WORKED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n\n---\n\n## 9. WHAT FAILED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n\n---\n\n## 10. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n[Populated when a review approach has been tried from multiple angles without yielding new findings]\n\n### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n- What was tried: [specific review approaches attempted]\n- Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n- Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n\n### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n- What worked: [successful review approaches in this category]\n- Prefer for: [related dimensions where this category may help]\n\n---\n\n## 11. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n[Review angles that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n- [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n\n---\n\n## 12. NEXT FOCUS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n[Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration. Includes target dimension and/or specific files to review.]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 13. KNOWN CONTEXT\n[Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n\n---\n\n## 14. CROSS-REFERENCE STATUS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n[Alignment checks completed across core and overlay protocols]\n\n| Protocol | Level | Status | Iteration | Notes |\n|----------|-------|--------|-----------|-------|\n| `spec_code` | core | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked] | [N] | [details] |\n| `checklist_evidence` | core | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked] | [N] | [details] |\n| `skill_agent` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n| `agent_cross_runtime` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n| `feature_catalog_code` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n| `playbook_capability` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 15. FILES UNDER REVIEW\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n[Per-file coverage state table -- populated during initialization from scope discovery]\n\n| File | Dimensions Reviewed | Last Iteration | Findings | Status |\n|------|-------------------|----------------|----------|--------|\n| [path/to/file] | [D1, D3] | [N] | [0 P0, 1 P1, 2 P2] | [partial/complete] |\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 16. REVIEW BOUNDARIES\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- Max iterations: [from config]\n- Convergence threshold: [from config]\n- Rolling STOP threshold: 0.08\n- No-progress threshold: 0.05\n- Coverage stabilization passes required: 1\n- Session lineage: sessionId=[from config.sessionId], parentSessionId=[from config.parentSessionId], generation=[from config.generation], lineageMode=[from config.lineageMode]\n- Findings registry: `deep-review-findings-registry.json`\n- Release-readiness states: in-progress | converged | release-blocking\n- Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n- Severity threshold: [from config.severityThreshold]\n- Review target type: [from config.reviewTargetType]\n- Cross-reference checks: core=[from config.crossReference.core], overlay=[from config.crossReference.overlay]\n- Started: [timestamp]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 17. EXAMPLE (POPULATED)\n\nReference snippet showing a partially populated strategy file mid-review. Use this as a visual anchor when opening a live strategy doc.\n\n```markdown\n## 1. REVIEW CHARTER\n- Target: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research (skill, v1.4.0)\n- Dimensions: correctness, test-coverage, cross-runtime-parity, observability\n- Stop conditions: rolling newInfoRatio < 0.08 for 2 iterations OR all dimensions converged OR max=7 reached\n- Success criteria: zero P0 in correctness; test-coverage P0 resolved or deferred with rationale\n\n## 4. NEXT FOCUS\n- Dimension: test-coverage\n- Files: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs, .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/deep-research-contract-parity.vitest.ts\n- Why: Iteration 2 surfaced a P0 (convergence-path coverage gap); needs a focused follow-up before correctness can terminate PASS.\n\n## 9. COVERAGE MATRIX\n| Dimension            | Status     | Iterations touched |\n|----------------------|------------|--------------------|\n| correctness          | converged  | 1                  |\n| test-coverage        | converging | 2, 4               |\n| cross-runtime-parity | converging | 3                  |\n| observability        | converging | 4                  |\n```","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":194,"totalLines":194,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md","time":{"start":1781764129626,"end":1781764129643}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b44746d26baa3f3016a33902184908191b338737f4c540fbf"}},"id":"prt_ed96b0355001oT4YYZ1Vs73ncs","sessionID":"ses_126960be2ffewGSaH1Z0io46OH","messageID":"msg_ed96ad021001BRShGoUZQuXYyJ"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781764129645,"sessionID":"ses_126960be2ffewGSaH1Z0io46OH","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_FkApmAMNWsoEIE53dqCwnSFa","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_dashboard.md","offset":1,"limit":1200},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_dashboard.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review Dashboard\n3: description: Auto-generated review session overview, refreshed after each iteration from JSONL state and strategy.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review dashboard\"\n6:   - \"review session overview\"\n7:   - \"review findings summary\"\n8:   - \"review coverage trend\"\n9: importance_tier: normal\n10: contextType: general\n11: ---\n12: \n13: # Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview\n14: \n15: Auto-generated summary of the current review session, regenerated after every iteration evaluation from JSONL state and strategy. Never edited manually.\n16: \n17: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n18: \n19: ### Purpose\n20: \n21: Provides a compact, human-readable summary of the current review session. Serves three roles:\n22: 1. **Observability**, quick status check during long autonomous review runs\n23: 2. **Recovery surface**, second recovery channel alongside JSONL after context compaction\n24: 3. **Resume decision**, in confirm mode, shown to user before resume/restart choice\n25: \n26: ### Usage\n27: \n28: - **Location:** `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md`\n29: - **Generated by:** Orchestrator (step_generate_dashboard in YAML workflow)\n30: - **Data sources:** `deep-review-state.jsonl` + `deep-review-strategy.md` + `deep-review-findings-registry.json`\n31: - **Protection:** `auto-generated`, overwritten each iteration, never manually edited\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ## 2. STATUS\n36: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n37: - Target: [from config.reviewTarget]\n38: - Target Type: [from config.reviewTargetType]\n39: - Started: [from config.createdAt]\n40: - Session: [from config.sessionId] (generation [from config.generation], lineage [from config.lineageMode])\n41: - Status: [ITERATING | CONVERGING | STUCK_RECOVERY | COMPLETE]\n42: - Release Readiness: [in-progress | converged | release-blocking]\n43: - Iteration: [N] of [maxIterations]\n44: - Provisional Verdict: [PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL | PENDING]\n45: - hasAdvisories: [true | false]\n46: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ## 3. FINDINGS SUMMARY\n51: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n52: - **P0 (Critical):** [N] active, [N] new this iteration, [N] upgrades, [N] resolved\n53: - **P1 (Major):** [N] active, [N] new this iteration, [N] upgrades, [N] resolved\n54: - **P2 (Minor):** [N] active, [N] new this iteration, [N] upgrades, [N] resolved\n55: - **Repeated findings:** [N]\n56: - **Dimensions covered:** [correctness, security, traceability, maintainability]\n57: - **Convergence score:** [0.00-1.00]\n58: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ## 4. PROGRESS\n63: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n64: \n65: | # | Focus | Files | Dimensions | New P0/P1/P2 | Ratio | Status |\n66: |---|-------|-------|------------|---------------|-------|--------|\n67: | [per iteration from JSONL] |\n68: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n69: \n70: ---\n71: \n72: ## 5. COVERAGE\n73: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n74: - Files reviewed: [X] / [Y] total\n75: - Dimensions complete: [X] / 4 total\n76: - Core protocols complete: [X] / [Y] required\n77: - Overlay protocols complete: [X] / [Y] applicable\n78: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: ## 6. TREND\n83: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n84: - Severity trend (last 3): [P0:N P1:N P2:N -> P0:N P1:N P2:N -> P0:N P1:N P2:N]\n85: - New findings trend (last 3): [N -> N -> N] [increasing | stable | decreasing]\n86: - Traceability trend (last 3): [pass/partial/fail counts -> ...]\n87: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n88: \n89: ---\n90: \n91: ## 7. RESOLVED / RULED OUT\n92: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n93: - **Disproved findings:** [findings investigated and determined to be false positives]\n94: - **Dead-end review paths:** [review approaches that yielded no actionable results]\n95: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n96: \n97: ---\n98: \n99: ## 8. NEXT FOCUS\n100: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n101: [from strategy.md \"Next Focus\" section, next dimension, file set, or review lens]\n102: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n103: \n104: ---\n105: \n106: ## 9. ACTIVE RISKS\n107: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n108: - [blockers, missing coverage, unresolved contradictions, gate violations, high stuck count, declining trend, etc.]\n109: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n110: \n111: ---\n112: \n113: ## 10. EXAMPLE (POPULATED)\n114: \n115: Reference snippet showing what a rendered review dashboard looks like after iteration 4 of a 7-iteration run. Use this as a visual anchor when inspecting a live dashboard.\n116: \n117: ```markdown\n118: # Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview\n119: \n120: ## 2. STATUS\n121: - Target: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research (skill)\n122: - Started: 2026-04-21T10:02:11+02:00\n123: - Status: ITERATING\n124: - Iteration: 4 of 7\n125: - Verdict: PENDING\n126: - Coverage: core=pass, overlay=partial\n127: \n128: ## 3. PROGRESS\n129: \n130: | # | Dimension            | Files touched | P0 | P1 | P2 | Ratio | Status     |\n131: |---|----------------------|---------------|----|----|----|-------|------------|\n132: | 1 | correctness          | 8             | 0  | 3  | 4  | 0.78  | converged  |\n133: | 2 | test-coverage        | 6             | 1  | 2  | 1  | 0.52  | converging |\n134: | 3 | cross-runtime-parity | 5             | 0  | 2  | 0  | 0.41  | converging |\n135: | 4 | observability        | 4             | 0  | 1  | 2  | 0.29  | converging |\n136: \n137: ## 6. TRACEABILITY TREND\n138: - Core protocols: spec_code=pass, checklist_evidence=pass\n139: - Overlay protocols: skill_agent=pass, agent_cross_runtime=partial\n140: - Traceability trend (last 3): 3/0/1 -> 4/0/0 -> 4/1/0\n141: \n142: ## 9. ACTIVE RISKS\n143: - 1 P0 in test-coverage dimension -- review cannot terminate PASS until resolved\n144: - agent_cross_runtime protocol partial: Codex runtime path still unverified\n145: ```\n\n(End of file - total 145 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Dashboard\ndescription: Auto-generated review session overview, refreshed after each iteration from JSONL state and strategy.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review dashboard\"\n  - \"review session overview\"\n  - \"review findings summary\"\n  - \"review coverage trend\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: general\n---\n\n# Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview\n\nAuto-generated summary of the current review session, regenerated after every iteration evaluation from JSONL state and strategy. Never edited manually.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_dashboard.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Dashboard\ndescription: Auto-generated review session overview, refreshed after each iteration from JSONL state and strategy.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review dashboard\"\n  - \"review session overview\"\n  - \"review findings summary\"\n  - \"review coverage trend\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: general\n---\n\n# Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview\n\nAuto-generated summary of the current review session, regenerated after every iteration evaluation from JSONL state and strategy. Never edited manually.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nProvides a compact, human-readable summary of the current review session. Serves three roles:\n1. **Observability**, quick status check during long autonomous review runs\n2. **Recovery surface**, second recovery channel alongside JSONL after context compaction\n3. **Resume decision**, in confirm mode, shown to user before resume/restart choice\n\n### Usage\n\n- **Location:** `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md`\n- **Generated by:** Orchestrator (step_generate_dashboard in YAML workflow)\n- **Data sources:** `deep-review-state.jsonl` + `deep-review-strategy.md` + `deep-review-findings-registry.json`\n- **Protection:** `auto-generated`, overwritten each iteration, never manually edited\n\n---\n\n## 2. STATUS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- Target: [from config.reviewTarget]\n- Target Type: [from config.reviewTargetType]\n- Started: [from config.createdAt]\n- Session: [from config.sessionId] (generation [from config.generation], lineage [from config.lineageMode])\n- Status: [ITERATING | CONVERGING | STUCK_RECOVERY | COMPLETE]\n- Release Readiness: [in-progress | converged | release-blocking]\n- Iteration: [N] of [maxIterations]\n- Provisional Verdict: [PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL | PENDING]\n- hasAdvisories: [true | false]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 3. FINDINGS SUMMARY\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- **P0 (Critical):** [N] active, [N] new this iteration, [N] upgrades, [N] resolved\n- **P1 (Major):** [N] active, [N] new this iteration, [N] upgrades, [N] resolved\n- **P2 (Minor):** [N] active, [N] new this iteration, [N] upgrades, [N] resolved\n- **Repeated findings:** [N]\n- **Dimensions covered:** [correctness, security, traceability, maintainability]\n- **Convergence score:** [0.00-1.00]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 4. PROGRESS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n\n| # | Focus | Files | Dimensions | New P0/P1/P2 | Ratio | Status |\n|---|-------|-------|------------|---------------|-------|--------|\n| [per iteration from JSONL] |\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 5. COVERAGE\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- Files reviewed: [X] / [Y] total\n- Dimensions complete: [X] / 4 total\n- Core protocols complete: [X] / [Y] required\n- Overlay protocols complete: [X] / [Y] applicable\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 6. TREND\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- Severity trend (last 3): [P0:N P1:N P2:N -> P0:N P1:N P2:N -> P0:N P1:N P2:N]\n- New findings trend (last 3): [N -> N -> N] [increasing | stable | decreasing]\n- Traceability trend (last 3): [pass/partial/fail counts -> ...]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 7. RESOLVED / RULED OUT\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- **Disproved findings:** [findings investigated and determined to be false positives]\n- **Dead-end review paths:** [review approaches that yielded no actionable results]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 8. NEXT FOCUS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n[from strategy.md \"Next Focus\" section, next dimension, file set, or review lens]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 9. ACTIVE RISKS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- [blockers, missing coverage, unresolved contradictions, gate violations, high stuck count, declining trend, etc.]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 10. EXAMPLE (POPULATED)\n\nReference snippet showing what a rendered review dashboard looks like after iteration 4 of a 7-iteration run. Use this as a visual anchor when inspecting a live dashboard.\n\n```markdown\n# Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview\n\n## 2. STATUS\n- Target: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research (skill)\n- Started: 2026-04-21T10:02:11+02:00\n- Status: ITERATING\n- Iteration: 4 of 7\n- Verdict: PENDING\n- Coverage: core=pass, overlay=partial\n\n## 3. PROGRESS\n\n| # | Dimension            | Files touched | P0 | P1 | P2 | Ratio | Status     |\n|---|----------------------|---------------|----|----|----|-------|------------|\n| 1 | correctness          | 8             | 0  | 3  | 4  | 0.78  | converged  |\n| 2 | test-coverage        | 6             | 1  | 2  | 1  | 0.52  | converging |\n| 3 | cross-runtime-parity | 5             | 0  | 2  | 0  | 0.41  | converging |\n| 4 | observability        | 4             | 0  | 1  | 2  | 0.29  | converging |\n\n## 6. TRACEABILITY TREND\n- Core protocols: spec_code=pass, checklist_evidence=pass\n- Overlay protocols: skill_agent=pass, agent_cross_runtime=partial\n- Traceability trend (last 3): 3/0/1 -> 4/0/0 -> 4/1/0\n\n## 9. ACTIVE RISKS\n- 1 P0 in test-coverage dimension -- review cannot terminate PASS until resolved\n- agent_cross_runtime protocol partial: Codex runtime path still unverified\n```","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":145,"totalLines":145,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_dashboard.md","time":{"start":1781764129629,"end":1781764129644}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b44746d26baa3f3016a339021849881919afffd4b6e8a59ab"}},"id":"prt_ed96b035b001mu6IXx0KeW4kDl","sessionID":"ses_126960be2ffewGSaH1Z0io46OH","messageID":"msg_ed96ad021001BRShGoUZQuXYyJ"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781764129651,"sessionID":"ses_126960be2ffewGSaH1Z0io46OH","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_dh3gxkCWizsP9FEuXkLQIWdE","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/README.md","offset":1,"limit":1200},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"deep review scripts: Code README\"\n3: description: \"Code-facing README for .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep-review scripts\"\n6:   - \"code README\"\n7: ---\n8: \n9: # deep review scripts\n10: \n11: Operator and maintenance scripts for this skill.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n16: \n17: ### Purpose\n18: \n19: This README documents the code-bearing folder `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts` so operators can understand its role without opening every source file first. It follows the sk-doc skill README structure while staying focused on code navigation.\n20: \n21: ### Usage\n22: \n23: Use this file to identify the folder boundary, the likely verification path, and the local source files that need sk-code conventions. Keep behavior details in source comments and higher-level workflow details in the owning `SKILL.md`.\n24: \n25: ### Key Statistics\n26: \n27: | Metric | Value |\n28: |---|---:|\n29: | Code files | 2 |\n30: | README scope | Direct files in this folder |\n31: | Audit context | Internal validation notes |\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ## 2. QUICK START\n36: \n37: **Step 1: Confirm the owner.**\n38: \n39: Start with `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md` for runtime routing and workflow boundaries.\n40: \n41: **Step 2: Inspect the local code.**\n42: \n43: ```bash\n44: rg --files .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts\n45: ```\n46: \n47: Expected result: the command lists the source files summarized below.\n48: \n49: **Step 3: Verify changes.**\n50: \n51: Run individual scripts from the repository root with the documented arguments.\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: ## 3. FEATURES\n56: \n57: | Feature | What It Does |\n58: |---|---|\n59: | Folder boundary | Documents direct code files under `scripts`. |\n60: | sk-code alignment | Points reviewers at OpenCode naming, header, error-handling, and type-discipline checks. |\n61: | Verification handoff | Records the expected owner and audit packet for follow-up work. |\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: ## 4. STRUCTURE\n66: \n67: | Path | Purpose |\n68: |---|---|\n69: | `reduce-state.cjs` | CJS source file in this folder. |\n70: | `runtime-capabilities.cjs` | CJS source file in this folder. |\n71: \n72: ---\n73: \n74: ## 5. CONFIGURATION\n75: \n76: | Setting | Default | Purpose |\n77: |---|---|---|\n78: | sk-code surface | OPENCODE | Applies OpenCode TypeScript, JavaScript, Python, Shell, and config conventions. |\n79: | README scope | Direct folder | This file documents this folder, not sibling folders. |\n80: \n81: ---\n82: \n83: ## 6. USAGE EXAMPLES\n84: \n85: **Audit this folder**\n86: \n87: ```text\n88: User request: Check .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts for sk-code and README coverage.\n89: Skill routing: sk-code plus sk-doc.\n90: Expected output: Findings recorded in the 026 audit report.\n91: ```\n92: \n93: ---\n94: \n95: ## 7. TROUBLESHOOTING\n96: \n97: | What You See | Cause | Fix |\n98: |---|---|---|\n99: | README appears stale | Source files changed after this audit | Refresh the structure table and rerun the 026 audit check. |\n100: | Verification command is unclear | Folder is a helper boundary | Use the nearest package or skill-level verification command. |\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ## 8. RELATED DOCUMENTS\n105: \n106: | Document | Purpose |\n107: |---|---|\n108: | [`deep-review/SKILL.md`](../SKILL.md) | Runtime instructions for the owning skill. |\n109: | [`sk-code/SKILL.md`](../../sk-code/SKILL.md) | OpenCode coding standards and verification routing. |\n110: | [`sk-doc skill_readme_template.md`](../../sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_readme_template.md) | README structure used for this code README. |\n\n(End of file - total 110 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"deep review scripts: Code README\"\ndescription: \"Code-facing README for .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep-review scripts\"\n  - \"code README\"\n---\n\n# deep review scripts\n\nOperator and maintenance scripts for this skill.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nThis README documents the code-bearing folder `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts` so operators can understand its role without opening every source file first. It follows the sk-doc skill README structure while staying focused on code navigation.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/README.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"deep review scripts: Code README\"\ndescription: \"Code-facing README for .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep-review scripts\"\n  - \"code README\"\n---\n\n# deep review scripts\n\nOperator and maintenance scripts for this skill.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nThis README documents the code-bearing folder `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts` so operators can understand its role without opening every source file first. It follows the sk-doc skill README structure while staying focused on code navigation.\n\n### Usage\n\nUse this file to identify the folder boundary, the likely verification path, and the local source files that need sk-code conventions. Keep behavior details in source comments and higher-level workflow details in the owning `SKILL.md`.\n\n### Key Statistics\n\n| Metric | Value |\n|---|---:|\n| Code files | 2 |\n| README scope | Direct files in this folder |\n| Audit context | Internal validation notes |\n\n---\n\n## 2. QUICK START\n\n**Step 1: Confirm the owner.**\n\nStart with `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md` for runtime routing and workflow boundaries.\n\n**Step 2: Inspect the local code.**\n\n```bash\nrg --files .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts\n```\n\nExpected result: the command lists the source files summarized below.\n\n**Step 3: Verify changes.**\n\nRun individual scripts from the repository root with the documented arguments.\n\n---\n\n## 3. FEATURES\n\n| Feature | What It Does |\n|---|---|\n| Folder boundary | Documents direct code files under `scripts`. |\n| sk-code alignment | Points reviewers at OpenCode naming, header, error-handling, and type-discipline checks. |\n| Verification handoff | Records the expected owner and audit packet for follow-up work. |\n\n---\n\n## 4. STRUCTURE\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `reduce-state.cjs` | CJS source file in this folder. |\n| `runtime-capabilities.cjs` | CJS source file in this folder. |\n\n---\n\n## 5. CONFIGURATION\n\n| Setting | Default | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| sk-code surface | OPENCODE | Applies OpenCode TypeScript, JavaScript, Python, Shell, and config conventions. |\n| README scope | Direct folder | This file documents this folder, not sibling folders. |\n\n---\n\n## 6. USAGE EXAMPLES\n\n**Audit this folder**\n\n```text\nUser request: Check .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts for sk-code and README coverage.\nSkill routing: sk-code plus sk-doc.\nExpected output: Findings recorded in the 026 audit report.\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. TROUBLESHOOTING\n\n| What You See | Cause | Fix |\n|---|---|---|\n| README appears stale | Source files changed after this audit | Refresh the structure table and rerun the 026 audit check. |\n| Verification command is unclear | Folder is a helper boundary | Use the nearest package or skill-level verification command. |\n\n---\n\n## 8. RELATED DOCUMENTS\n\n| Document | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| [`deep-review/SKILL.md`](../SKILL.md) | Runtime instructions for the owning skill. |\n| [`sk-code/SKILL.md`](../../sk-code/SKILL.md) | OpenCode coding standards and verification routing. |\n| [`sk-doc skill_readme_template.md`](../../sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_readme_template.md) | README structure used for this code README. |","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":110,"totalLines":110,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/README.md","time":{"start":1781764129640,"end":1781764129649}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b44746d26baa3f3016a33902184b08191bc2e939b02216c05"}},"id":"prt_ed96b0366001D0vwVKTL9qGM49","sessionID":"ses_126960be2ffewGSaH1Z0io46OH","messageID":"msg_ed96ad021001BRShGoUZQuXYyJ"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781764129651,"sessionID":"ses_126960be2ffewGSaH1Z0io46OH","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_xa4zyGJRuFb5jKKbXxKBWr8C","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl","offset":1,"limit":1200},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: DEEP-REVIEW\n2: \n3: # Deep-Review Iteration Prompt Pack\n4: \n5: This prompt pack renders the per-iteration context for the `@deep-review` LEAF agent (native executor) or a CLI executor (e.g. `codex exec`). Tokens use curly-brace syntax and are substituted by `renderPromptPack` before dispatch.\n6: \n7: ## STATE\n8: \n9: {state_summary}\n10: \n11: Review Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n12: Mode: review\n13: Dimension: {next_dimension}\n14: Review Target: {review_target}\n15: Review Scope Files: {review_scope_files}\n16: Prior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n17: \n18: ## SHARED DOCTRINE\n19: \n20: Load `.opencode/skills/sk-code-review/references/review_core.md` before final severity calls.\n21: \n22: ## REVIEW DIMENSIONS\n23: \n24: correctness, security, traceability, maintainability\n25: \n26: ## TRACEABILITY PROTOCOLS\n27: \n28: - **Core**: spec_code, checklist_evidence\n29: - **Overlay**: skill_agent, agent_cross_runtime, feature_catalog_code, playbook_capability\n30: \n31: ## QUALITY GATES\n32: \n33: evidence, scope, coverage\n34: \n35: ## VERDICTS\n36: \n37: `FAIL | CONDITIONAL | PASS`, PASS may set `hasAdvisories=true` when only P2 remain.\n38: \n39: ## CLAIM ADJUDICATION\n40: \n41: Every new P0/P1 must include: claim, evidenceRefs, counterevidenceSought, alternativeExplanation, finalSeverity, confidence, and downgradeTrigger.\n42: \n43: ## STATE FILES\n44: \n45: All paths are relative to the repo root.\n46: \n47: - Config: {state_paths_config}\n48: - State Log: {state_paths_state_log}\n49: - Findings Registry: {state_paths_findings_registry}\n50: - Strategy: {state_paths_strategy}\n51: - Write iteration narrative to: {state_paths_iteration_pattern}\n52: - Write per-iteration delta file to: {state_paths_delta_pattern}\n53: \n54: ## CONSTRAINTS\n55: \n56: - You are a LEAF agent. Do NOT dispatch sub-agents.\n57: - Target 9 tool calls. Soft max 12, hard max 13.\n58: - Write ALL findings to files. Do not hold in context.\n59: - Review target is READ-ONLY. Do not modify reviewed files.\n60: - Do not implement fixes during review. Report findings only; implementation is a separate follow-up step.\n61: - **ALLOWED WRITE PATHS (the ONLY paths you may create, modify, or append to)**:\n62:   - `{state_paths_iteration_pattern}`, this iteration's narrative markdown\n63:   - `{state_paths_state_log}`, append-only JSONL state log\n64:   - `{state_paths_delta_pattern}`, this iteration's delta JSONL\n65:   - `{state_paths_strategy}`, strategy.md (in-place updates only)\n66:   - `{state_paths_findings_registry}`, findings registry (in-place updates only)\n67: - **BANNED OPERATIONS (NEVER execute against any path)**: `rm`, `rm -rf`, `git rm`, `mv`, `sed -i` (including `sed -i ''`), `rmdir`, `find ... -delete`, shell output-redirect truncate `>` against any file not in the allowed-write list, and any tool call whose effect is to delete, rename, or replace a file outside the allowed-write list. Reading is unrestricted; **writing, renaming, and deleting are scoped**.\n68: - **SCOPE VIOLATION PROTOCOL**: if your plan would require modifying any path NOT in the allowed-write list, you MUST STOP that action and emit a finding instead. Record the would-be mutation as a `scope_violation` entry in the iteration narrative (under a `## SCOPE VIOLATIONS` heading) and continue the review. NEVER execute the out-of-scope mutation. The review packet (`{state_paths_iteration_pattern}` directory and parents) is the only zone for your writes; the reviewed target spec/code is off-limits.\n69: - Append JSONL record with dimensions, filesReviewed, findingsSummary, findingsNew, traceabilityChecks, newFindingsRatio, and optional graphEvents.\n70: - When emitting the iteration JSONL record, include an optional `graphEvents` array of `{type, id, label, relation?, source?, target?}` objects representing coverage graph nodes and edges discovered this iteration. Omit the field when no graph events are produced.\n71: \n72: ## OUTPUT CONTRACT\n73: \n74: You MUST produce THREE artifacts per iteration. The YAML-owned post_dispatch_validate step emits a `schema_mismatch` conflict event if any is missing or malformed.\n75: \n76: 1. **Iteration narrative markdown** at `{state_paths_iteration_pattern}` (path pre-substituted for the current iteration number). Structure: headings for Dimension, Files Reviewed, Findings by Severity (P0/P1/P2), Traceability Checks, Verdict, Next Dimension.\n77: \n78: 2. **Canonical JSONL iteration record** APPENDED to `{state_paths_state_log}`. The record MUST use `\"type\":\"iteration\"` EXACTLY, NOT `\"iteration_delta\"` or any other variant. The reducer counts records where `type === \"iteration\"` only; other types are silently ignored. Required schema:\n79: \n80: ```json\n81: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":<n>,\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":\"<run-id>\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"<dimension-or-focus>\",\"dimensions\":[\"...\"],\"filesReviewed\":[\"path:line\"],\"findingsCount\":<n>,\"findingsSummary\":{\"P0\":<n>,\"P1\":<n>,\"P2\":<n>},\"findingsNew\":[],\"traceabilityChecks\":{},\"newFindingsRatio\":<0..1>,\"sessionId\":\"<session-id>\",\"generation\":<n>,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"timestamp\":\"<ISO-8601>\",\"durationMs\":<n>,\"graphEvents\":[/* optional */]}\n82: ```\n83: \n84: ### v2 Search Depth Output (when scopeClass is standard or complex)\n85: \n86: For standard or complex review scope, set `\"reviewDepthSchemaVersion\":2` on the same iteration JSONL record and include these v2 fields in addition to the v1 fields above:\n87: \n88: - `reviewDepthApplicability`: `{scopeClass,enforcement,reason,evidenceRefs}` where `scopeClass` is `trivial`, `standard`, or `complex`; `enforcement` is `strict`, `warn`, or `skip`.\n89: - `targetSelection`: `{selectedTargets,selectionReason,discoveryMethods,omittedHighRiskTargets,graphStatus,semanticSearchStatus,evidenceRefs}`. Name how targets were chosen, what high-risk targets were omitted, and whether graph/semantic search was available, unavailable, or partial.\n90: - `searchCoverage`: `{requiredBugClasses,covered,ruledOut,deferred,blocked,graphCoverageMode}` where `graphCoverageMode` is `graph`, `graphless_fallback`, or `unavailable_blocked`.\n91: - `searchLedger[]`: ledger rows with required `id`, `dimension`, `targetRefs`, `bugClass`, `disposition`, and `rationale`; include `hypothesis` or `invariant` (at least one); include `searchActions[]` with `{method,queryOrPath,result,evidenceRefs}`.\n92: - Each ledger row needs exactly one disposition link: `linkedFindingId` for `finding` (must match an id in `findingDetails[]`), `ruledOutReason` for `ruled_out`, `deferredReason` for `deferred`, `blockedReason` for `blocked`, or `notApplicableReason` for `not_applicable`.\n93: \n94: Trivial-scope exemption: when `scopeClass` is `trivial` and `enforcement` is `skip`, `searchLedger` may be `[]`, but `reviewDepthApplicability.evidenceRefs` MUST cite proof that the target is trivial.\n95: \n96: Compact v2 example:\n97: \n98: ```json\n99: {\"reviewDepthSchemaVersion\":2,\"reviewDepthApplicability\":{\"scopeClass\":\"standard\",\"enforcement\":\"strict\",\"reason\":\"non-trivial target\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\"path/to/file.ts:42\"]},\"targetSelection\":{\"selectedTargets\":[\"path/to/file.ts\"],\"selectionReason\":\"state transition producer\",\"discoveryMethods\":[\"direct_read\",\"exact_search\"],\"omittedHighRiskTargets\":[],\"graphStatus\":\"unavailable\",\"semanticSearchStatus\":\"partial\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\"path/to/file.ts:42\"]},\"searchCoverage\":{\"requiredBugClasses\":[\"state_transition\"],\"covered\":[],\"ruledOut\":[\"state_transition\"],\"deferred\":[],\"blocked\":[],\"graphCoverageMode\":\"graphless_fallback\"},\"searchLedger\":[{\"id\":\"SL-001\",\"dimension\":\"correctness\",\"targetRefs\":[\"path/to/file.ts\"],\"bugClass\":\"state_transition\",\"hypothesis\":\"state transition can skip validation\",\"searchActions\":[{\"method\":\"direct_read\",\"queryOrPath\":\"path/to/file.ts\",\"result\":\"guard present on all branches\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\"path/to/file.ts:42\"]}],\"disposition\":\"ruled_out\",\"rationale\":\"all branches call the guard\",\"ruledOutReason\":\"verified by direct read\"}]}\n100: ```\n101: \n102: Legacy unversioned records remain valid during rollout. Phase D validator behavior should warn on legacy shallow records and strictly enforce this shape only for explicit v2 records.\n103: \n104: Append via single-line JSON with newline terminator, e.g. `echo '<single-line-json>' >> {state_paths_state_log}`. Do NOT pretty-print. Do NOT print to stdout only; it MUST land in the state log file.\n105: \n106: 3. **Per-iteration delta file** at `{state_paths_delta_pattern}` (path pre-substituted, e.g. `deltas/iter-001.jsonl`). This file holds the structured delta stream for this iteration: one `{\"type\":\"iteration\",...}` record (same as the state-log append) plus per-event structured records (one per graphEvent, finding, classification, traceability-check, ruled_out direction). Each record on its own JSON line.\n107: \n108: Example delta file contents (one review iteration):\n109: ```json\n110: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":3,\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":\"run-001\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"correctness\",\"dimensions\":[\"correctness\"],\"filesReviewed\":[\"path/to/file.ts:42\"],\"findingsCount\":7,\"findingsSummary\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":2,\"P2\":5},\"findingsNew\":[],\"newFindingsRatio\":0.41,\"sessionId\":\"session-001\",\"generation\":1,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-30T00:00:00Z\",\"durationMs\":120000,\"graphEvents\":[]}\n111: {\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"R3-P1-001\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"cluster\":\"...\",\"file\":\"path:line\",\"title\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n112: {\"type\":\"classification\",\"detail\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n113: {\"type\":\"ruled_out\",\"direction\":\"...\",\"reason\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n114: ```\n115: \n116: All three artifacts are REQUIRED. The post_dispatch_validate step fails the iteration if any artifact is missing, malformed, or if the state-log append uses the wrong record type (`iteration_delta` etc.).\n\n(End of file - total 116 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"DEEP-REVIEW\n\n# Deep-Review Iteration Prompt Pack\n\nThis prompt pack renders the per-iteration context for the `@deep-review` LEAF agent (native executor) or a CLI executor (e.g. `codex exec`). Tokens use curly-brace syntax and are substituted by `renderPromptPack` before dispatch.\n\n## STATE\n\n{state_summary}\n\nReview Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\nMode: review\nDimension: {next_dimension}\nReview Target: {review_target}\nReview Scope Files: {review_scope_files}\nPrior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n\n## SHARED DOCTRINE\n\nLoad `.opencode/skills/sk-code-review/references/review_core.md` before final severity calls.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl","text":"DEEP-REVIEW\n\n# Deep-Review Iteration Prompt Pack\n\nThis prompt pack renders the per-iteration context for the `@deep-review` LEAF agent (native executor) or a CLI executor (e.g. `codex exec`). Tokens use curly-brace syntax and are substituted by `renderPromptPack` before dispatch.\n\n## STATE\n\n{state_summary}\n\nReview Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\nMode: review\nDimension: {next_dimension}\nReview Target: {review_target}\nReview Scope Files: {review_scope_files}\nPrior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n\n## SHARED DOCTRINE\n\nLoad `.opencode/skills/sk-code-review/references/review_core.md` before final severity calls.\n\n## REVIEW DIMENSIONS\n\ncorrectness, security, traceability, maintainability\n\n## TRACEABILITY PROTOCOLS\n\n- **Core**: spec_code, checklist_evidence\n- **Overlay**: skill_agent, agent_cross_runtime, feature_catalog_code, playbook_capability\n\n## QUALITY GATES\n\nevidence, scope, coverage\n\n## VERDICTS\n\n`FAIL | CONDITIONAL | PASS`, PASS may set `hasAdvisories=true` when only P2 remain.\n\n## CLAIM ADJUDICATION\n\nEvery new P0/P1 must include: claim, evidenceRefs, counterevidenceSought, alternativeExplanation, finalSeverity, confidence, and downgradeTrigger.\n\n## STATE FILES\n\nAll paths are relative to the repo root.\n\n- Config: {state_paths_config}\n- State Log: {state_paths_state_log}\n- Findings Registry: {state_paths_findings_registry}\n- Strategy: {state_paths_strategy}\n- Write iteration narrative to: {state_paths_iteration_pattern}\n- Write per-iteration delta file to: {state_paths_delta_pattern}\n\n## CONSTRAINTS\n\n- You are a LEAF agent. Do NOT dispatch sub-agents.\n- Target 9 tool calls. Soft max 12, hard max 13.\n- Write ALL findings to files. Do not hold in context.\n- Review target is READ-ONLY. Do not modify reviewed files.\n- Do not implement fixes during review. Report findings only; implementation is a separate follow-up step.\n- **ALLOWED WRITE PATHS (the ONLY paths you may create, modify, or append to)**:\n  - `{state_paths_iteration_pattern}`, this iteration's narrative markdown\n  - `{state_paths_state_log}`, append-only JSONL state log\n  - `{state_paths_delta_pattern}`, this iteration's delta JSONL\n  - `{state_paths_strategy}`, strategy.md (in-place updates only)\n  - `{state_paths_findings_registry}`, findings registry (in-place updates only)\n- **BANNED OPERATIONS (NEVER execute against any path)**: `rm`, `rm -rf`, `git rm`, `mv`, `sed -i` (including `sed -i ''`), `rmdir`, `find ... -delete`, shell output-redirect truncate `>` against any file not in the allowed-write list, and any tool call whose effect is to delete, rename, or replace a file outside the allowed-write list. Reading is unrestricted; **writing, renaming, and deleting are scoped**.\n- **SCOPE VIOLATION PROTOCOL**: if your plan would require modifying any path NOT in the allowed-write list, you MUST STOP that action and emit a finding instead. Record the would-be mutation as a `scope_violation` entry in the iteration narrative (under a `## SCOPE VIOLATIONS` heading) and continue the review. NEVER execute the out-of-scope mutation. The review packet (`{state_paths_iteration_pattern}` directory and parents) is the only zone for your writes; the reviewed target spec/code is off-limits.\n- Append JSONL record with dimensions, filesReviewed, findingsSummary, findingsNew, traceabilityChecks, newFindingsRatio, and optional graphEvents.\n- When emitting the iteration JSONL record, include an optional `graphEvents` array of `{type, id, label, relation?, source?, target?}` objects representing coverage graph nodes and edges discovered this iteration. Omit the field when no graph events are produced.\n\n## OUTPUT CONTRACT\n\nYou MUST produce THREE artifacts per iteration. The YAML-owned post_dispatch_validate step emits a `schema_mismatch` conflict event if any is missing or malformed.\n\n1. **Iteration narrative markdown** at `{state_paths_iteration_pattern}` (path pre-substituted for the current iteration number). Structure: headings for Dimension, Files Reviewed, Findings by Severity (P0/P1/P2), Traceability Checks, Verdict, Next Dimension.\n\n2. **Canonical JSONL iteration record** APPENDED to `{state_paths_state_log}`. The record MUST use `\"type\":\"iteration\"` EXACTLY, NOT `\"iteration_delta\"` or any other variant. The reducer counts records where `type === \"iteration\"` only; other types are silently ignored. Required schema:\n\n```json\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":<n>,\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":\"<run-id>\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"<dimension-or-focus>\",\"dimensions\":[\"...\"],\"filesReviewed\":[\"path:line\"],\"findingsCount\":<n>,\"findingsSummary\":{\"P0\":<n>,\"P1\":<n>,\"P2\":<n>},\"findingsNew\":[],\"traceabilityChecks\":{},\"newFindingsRatio\":<0..1>,\"sessionId\":\"<session-id>\",\"generation\":<n>,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"timestamp\":\"<ISO-8601>\",\"durationMs\":<n>,\"graphEvents\":[/* optional */]}\n```\n\n### v2 Search Depth Output (when scopeClass is standard or complex)\n\nFor standard or complex review scope, set `\"reviewDepthSchemaVersion\":2` on the same iteration JSONL record and include these v2 fields in addition to the v1 fields above:\n\n- `reviewDepthApplicability`: `{scopeClass,enforcement,reason,evidenceRefs}` where `scopeClass` is `trivial`, `standard`, or `complex`; `enforcement` is `strict`, `warn`, or `skip`.\n- `targetSelection`: `{selectedTargets,selectionReason,discoveryMethods,omittedHighRiskTargets,graphStatus,semanticSearchStatus,evidenceRefs}`. Name how targets were chosen, what high-risk targets were omitted, and whether graph/semantic search was available, unavailable, or partial.\n- `searchCoverage`: `{requiredBugClasses,covered,ruledOut,deferred,blocked,graphCoverageMode}` where `graphCoverageMode` is `graph`, `graphless_fallback`, or `unavailable_blocked`.\n- `searchLedger[]`: ledger rows with required `id`, `dimension`, `targetRefs`, `bugClass`, `disposition`, and `rationale`; include `hypothesis` or `invariant` (at least one); include `searchActions[]` with `{method,queryOrPath,result,evidenceRefs}`.\n- Each ledger row needs exactly one disposition link: `linkedFindingId` for `finding` (must match an id in `findingDetails[]`), `ruledOutReason` for `ruled_out`, `deferredReason` for `deferred`, `blockedReason` for `blocked`, or `notApplicableReason` for `not_applicable`.\n\nTrivial-scope exemption: when `scopeClass` is `trivial` and `enforcement` is `skip`, `searchLedger` may be `[]`, but `reviewDepthApplicability.evidenceRefs` MUST cite proof that the target is trivial.\n\nCompact v2 example:\n\n```json\n{\"reviewDepthSchemaVersion\":2,\"reviewDepthApplicability\":{\"scopeClass\":\"standard\",\"enforcement\":\"strict\",\"reason\":\"non-trivial target\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\"path/to/file.ts:42\"]},\"targetSelection\":{\"selectedTargets\":[\"path/to/file.ts\"],\"selectionReason\":\"state transition producer\",\"discoveryMethods\":[\"direct_read\",\"exact_search\"],\"omittedHighRiskTargets\":[],\"graphStatus\":\"unavailable\",\"semanticSearchStatus\":\"partial\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\"path/to/file.ts:42\"]},\"searchCoverage\":{\"requiredBugClasses\":[\"state_transition\"],\"covered\":[],\"ruledOut\":[\"state_transition\"],\"deferred\":[],\"blocked\":[],\"graphCoverageMode\":\"graphless_fallback\"},\"searchLedger\":[{\"id\":\"SL-001\",\"dimension\":\"correctness\",\"targetRefs\":[\"path/to/file.ts\"],\"bugClass\":\"state_transition\",\"hypothesis\":\"state transition can skip validation\",\"searchActions\":[{\"method\":\"direct_read\",\"queryOrPath\":\"path/to/file.ts\",\"result\":\"guard present on all branches\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\"path/to/file.ts:42\"]}],\"disposition\":\"ruled_out\",\"rationale\":\"all branches call the guard\",\"ruledOutReason\":\"verified by direct read\"}]}\n```\n\nLegacy unversioned records remain valid during rollout. Phase D validator behavior should warn on legacy shallow records and strictly enforce this shape only for explicit v2 records.\n\nAppend via single-line JSON with newline terminator, e.g. `echo '<single-line-json>' >> {state_paths_state_log}`. Do NOT pretty-print. Do NOT print to stdout only; it MUST land in the state log file.\n\n3. **Per-iteration delta file** at `{state_paths_delta_pattern}` (path pre-substituted, e.g. `deltas/iter-001.jsonl`). This file holds the structured delta stream for this iteration: one `{\"type\":\"iteration\",...}` record (same as the state-log append) plus per-event structured records (one per graphEvent, finding, classification, traceability-check, ruled_out direction). Each record on its own JSON line.\n\nExample delta file contents (one review iteration):\n```json\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":3,\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":\"run-001\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"correctness\",\"dimensions\":[\"correctness\"],\"filesReviewed\":[\"path/to/file.ts:42\"],\"findingsCount\":7,\"findingsSummary\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":2,\"P2\":5},\"findingsNew\":[],\"newFindingsRatio\":0.41,\"sessionId\":\"session-001\",\"generation\":1,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-30T00:00:00Z\",\"durationMs\":120000,\"graphEvents\":[]}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"R3-P1-001\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"cluster\":\"...\",\"file\":\"path:line\",\"title\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n{\"type\":\"classification\",\"detail\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n{\"type\":\"ruled_out\",\"direction\":\"...\",\"reason\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n```\n\nAll three artifacts are REQUIRED. The post_dispatch_validate step fails the iteration if any artifact is missing, malformed, or if the state-log append uses the wrong record type (`iteration_delta` etc.).","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":116,"totalLines":116,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl","time":{"start":1781764129636,"end":1781764129650}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b44746d26baa3f3016a33902184a88191b3b1b096fb2b4518"}},"id":"prt_ed96b035e0015HvyKb4bOryABg","sessionID":"ses_126960be2ffewGSaH1Z0io46OH","messageID":"msg_ed96ad021001BRShGoUZQuXYyJ"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1781764129963,"sessionID":"ses_126960be2ffewGSaH1Z0io46OH","part":{"id":"prt_ed96b04a9001aylwx3cTR7VzhI","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"0cbb3f453def76ed51880b6d15995f8b048af6c1","messageID":"msg_ed96ad021001BRShGoUZQuXYyJ","sessionID":"ses_126960be2ffewGSaH1Z0io46OH","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":92640,"input":39856,"output":364,"reasoning":196,"cache":{"write":0,"read":52224}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1781764132878,"sessionID":"ses_126960be2ffewGSaH1Z0io46OH","part":{"id":"prt_ed96b100d00128YfhsfpaNILGE","messageID":"msg_ed96b05b00010tZKTUOsOIOWCU","sessionID":"ses_126960be2ffewGSaH1Z0io46OH","snapshot":"0cbb3f453def76ed51880b6d15995f8b048af6c1","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1781764135957,"sessionID":"ses_126960be2ffewGSaH1Z0io46OH","part":{"id":"prt_ed96b1881001J7mvXZsv7WHy5L","messageID":"msg_ed96b05b00010tZKTUOsOIOWCU","sessionID":"ses_126960be2ffewGSaH1Z0io46OH","type":"text","text":"The YAML confirms the fan-out lineage override is the intended binding and that all canonical writes are under `{artifact_dir}`. IвҖҷm reading the remaining loop and synthesis steps to mirror the contract with the override already applied.","time":{"start":1781764135041,"end":1781764135955},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_08d89cdc047971e6016a339026d5e08191956fa0c60ed7b144","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781764136325,"sessionID":"ses_126960be2ffewGSaH1Z0io46OH","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_oBw9t27EnlKZqYBxun1gAvtP","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","offset":635,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n635:         action: \"Persist blocked-stop evidence whenever the review legal-stop decision tree vetoes STOP\"\n636:         if_blocked:\n637:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergenceGate\":{\"pass\":{convergence_gate_pass},\"score\":{convergence_gate_score}},\"dimensionCoverageGate\":{\"pass\":{dimension_coverage_gate_pass},\"covered\":{dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json},\"missing\":{dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json}},\"p0ResolutionGate\":{\"pass\":{p0_resolution_gate_pass},\"activeP0\":{active_p0_count}},\"evidenceDensityGate\":{\"pass\":{evidence_density_gate_pass},\"avgEvidencePerFinding\":{avg_evidence_per_finding}},\"hotspotSaturationGate\":{\"pass\":{hotspot_saturation_gate_pass}},\"claimAdjudicationGate\":{\"pass\":{claim_adjudication_gate_pass},\"activeP0P1\":{claim_adjudication_active_count}},\"fixCompletenessReplayGate\":{\"pass\":{fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass},\"securitySensitive\":{security_sensitive_fix_scope},\"requiredRows\":{fix_completeness_replay_required_rows},\"passingRows\":{fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows}},\"candidateCoverageGate\":{\"pass\":{candidate_coverage_gate_pass},\"searchDebt\":{candidate_coverage_search_debt_json},\"missing\":{candidate_coverage_missing_json}},\"graphlessFallbackGate\":{\"pass\":{graphless_fallback_gate_pass},\"mode\":\"{graphless_fallback_mode}\",\"missing\":{graphless_fallback_missing_json},\"unavailabilityReason\":\"{graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason}\"}},\"graphBlockerDetail\":{graph_blockers_json},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n638:           log: \"Blocked STOP persisted for review loop. Failed gates: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n639:         if_not_blocked:\n640:           proceed: true\n641: \n642:       step_handle_convergence:\n643:         action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n644:         if_stop:\n645:           log: \"Loop stopping. Reason: {reason}\"\n646:           skip_to: phase_synthesis\n647:         if_blocked:\n648:           log: \"Legal-stop gates blocked STOP. Failed gates: {blocked_by_csv}. Continuing review.\"\n649:         if_stuck_recovery:\n650:           log: \"Stuck detected ({stuck_count} consecutive no-progress). Entering recovery.\"\n651:           recovery_strategies:\n652:             - \"Change granularity: file-level вҶ’ function-level вҶ’ line-level review\"\n653:             - \"Traceability protocol replay: re-run unresolved core or overlay checks\"\n654:             - \"Escalate severity review: re-examine P2 findings for potential P1 upgrades\"\n655:           pivot_target: \"Pivot to the least-covered dimension (the review dimension with the fewest iteration passes and lowest coverage ratio).\"\n656:           set:\n657:             next_dimension: \"RECOVERY: {recovery_strategy}. Least-covered dimension: {least_explored}\"\n658:             pending_stop_event: \"stuck_recovery\"\n659:             pending_stop_reason: \"stuckRecovery\"\n660:             pending_stop_detail: \"Recovery path activated after repeated no-progress iterations\"\n661:           reset: { stuck_count: 0 }\n662:         if_continue:\n663:           log: \"Iteration {current_iteration}: Continuing. Dimension: {next_dimension}\"\n664: \n665:       step_normalize_pause_events:\n666:         action: \"Rewrite raw pause and recovery events to the frozen STOP_REASONS enum at emission time: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused\"\n667:         if_pending_pause_event:\n668:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"reason\":\"{pending_stop_detail}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n669:           message: \"Review paused. Delete review/.deep-review-pause to resume.\"\n670:           reset:\n671:             pending_stop_event: null\n672:             pending_stop_reason: null\n673:             pending_stop_detail: null\n674:           halt: true\n675:         if_pending_stuck_recovery:\n676:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"strategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"targetDimension\":\"{least_explored}\",\"outcome\":\"pending\",\"reason\":\"{pending_stop_detail}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n677:           reset:\n678:             pending_stop_event: null\n679:             pending_stop_reason: null\n680:             pending_stop_detail: null\n681:         if_no_pending_event:\n682:           proceed: true\n683: \n684:       step_generate_state_summary:\n685:         action: \"Generate compact state summary for dispatch context (~200 tokens)\"\n686:         generate: |\n687:           STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n688:           Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n689:           Dimension: {next_dimension}\n690:           Prior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n691:           Dimension Coverage: {dimensions_covered_list} ({dimension_coverage})\n692:           Traceability: core={core_protocol_status} overlay={overlay_protocol_status}\n693:           {resource_map_prompt_line}\n694:           Coverage Age: {coverage_age}\n695:           Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest}\n696:           Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n697:           Provisional Verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n698: \n699:       step_marker_scan:\n700:         action: \"H-2 loop-prevention guard: scan previous iteration's rendered prompt for nested review marker\"\n701:         algorithm: |\n702:           if current_iteration > 1:\n703:             PREV_PROMPT_PATH = \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{previous_iteration}.md\"\n704:             if file_exists(PREV_PROMPT_PATH):\n705:               PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE = head -1 of PREV_PROMPT_PATH\n706:               if PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE matches ^(DEEP-REVIEW|DEEP-RESEARCH|CODE-REVIEW)$:\n707:                 log \"ERROR: nested review-of-review loop detected (marker found in previous iteration prompt). Aborting.\"\n708:                 halt with exit code 2\n709:         note: |\n710:           False-positive prevention: only matches when the first line is exactly one of the\n711:           three canonical markers. Markers appearing in comments or body text are ignored.\n712:           True-positive triggers only when a previous iteration's rendered prompt literally\n713:           starts with a deep-loop marker, indicating a nested review-of-review dispatch.\n714: \n715:       step_dispatch_iteration:\n716:         action: \"Dispatch @deep-review agent for one review iteration\"\n717:         resolve_executor:\n718:           source: \"config.executor\"\n719:           loader: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n720:         pre_dispatch:\n721:           generate_summary: |\n722:             STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n723:             Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n724:             Dimension: {next_dimension}\n725:             Prior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n726:             Dimension Coverage: {dimensions_covered_list} ({dimension_coverage})\n727:             Traceability: core={core_protocol_status} overlay={overlay_protocol_status}\n728:             {resource_map_prompt_line}\n729:             Coverage Age: {coverage_age}\n730:             Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest}\n731:             Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n732:             Provisional Verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n733:           render_prompt_pack:\n734:             template_path: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl\"\n735:             renderer: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n736:             output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n737:             variables:\n738:               state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"\n739:               current_iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n740:               max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n741:               next_dimension: \"{next_dimension}\"\n742:               review_target: \"{review_target}\"\n743:               review_scope_files: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n744:               p0_count: \"{p0_count}\"\n745:               p1_count: \"{p1_count}\"\n746:               p2_count: \"{p2_count}\"\n747:               state_paths_config: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n748:               state_paths_state_log: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n749:               state_paths_findings_registry: \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n750:               state_paths_strategy: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n751:               state_paths_iteration_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n752:               state_paths_delta_pattern: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n753:         pre_dispatch_audit:\n754:           skip_when: \"config.executor.kind == 'native'\"\n755:           call: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts#writeFirstRecordExecutor\"\n756:           args:\n757:             stateLogPath: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n758:             executor: \"{config.executor}\"\n759:             iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n760:         branch_on: \"config.executor.kind\"\n761:         if_native:\n762:           dispatch:\n763:             agent: deep-review\n764:             model: opus\n765:             context_source: \"rendered_prompt_pack\"\n766:           wait_for_completion: true\n767:         if_cli_codex:\n768:           command: |\n769:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n770:             import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n771: \n772:             import { runAuditedExecutorCommandAsync } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n773:             import { resolveCodexSandboxMode } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n774: \n775:             const executor = {\n776:               kind: 'cli-codex',\n777:               model: '{config.executor.model}',\n778:               configDir: '{config.executor.configDir}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.configDir}',\n779:               reasoningEffort: '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}',\n780:               serviceTier: '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}',\n781:               sandboxMode: '{config.executor.sandboxMode}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.sandboxMode}',\n782:               timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n783:             };\n784: \n785:             process.exit(await runAuditedExecutorCommandAsync({\n786:               command: 'codex',\n787:               args: [\n788:                 'exec',\n789:                 '--model',\n790:                 executor.model,\n791:                 '-c',\n792:                 `model_reasoning_effort=${executor.reasoningEffort}`,\n793:                 '-c',\n794:                 `service_tier=${executor.serviceTier}`,\n795:                 '-c',\n796:                 'approval_policy=never',\n797:                 '--sandbox',\n798:                 resolveCodexSandboxMode(executor.sandboxMode),\n799:                 '-',\n800:               ],\n801:               cwd: '{repo_root}',\n802:               timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n803:               stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n804:               executor,\n805:               iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n806:               input: readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n807:             }));\n808:             EOF\n809:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n810:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n811:           wait_for_completion: true\n812:         if_cli_copilot:\n813:           command: |\n814:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n815:             import { readFileSync, writeFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n816:             import { spawnSync } from 'node:child_process';\n817: \n818:             import { buildCopilotPromptArg } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n819: \n820:             const promptPath = '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md';\n821:             const prompt = readFileSync(promptPath, 'utf8');\n822: \n823:             // Workflow-resolved spec folder is the only legal write authority.\n824:             // The helper (`validateSpecFolder` inside `buildCopilotPromptArg`)\n825:             // is the single source of truth for rejecting empty / unresolved\n826:             // template / whitespace-only / string-coerced empty values. The\n827:             // YAML hands the raw `{spec_folder}` directly; on rejection the\n828:             // helper safe-fails to `type:\"missing\", writeIntent:true` (Gate-3\n829:             // enforcement, --allow-all-tools stripped).\n830:             const specFolderRaw = '{spec_folder}';\n831:             const targetAuthority = { type: 'approved', specFolder: specFolderRaw };\n832: \n833:             const baseArgs = [\n834:               '-p',\n835:               prompt,\n836:               '--model',\n837:               '{config.executor.model}',\n838:               '--allow-all-tools',\n839:               '--no-ask-user',\n840:             ];\n841: \n842:             const built = buildCopilotPromptArg({\n843:               promptPath,\n844:               prompt,\n845:               targetAuthority,\n846:               baseArgv: baseArgs,\n847:             });\n848: \n849:             // Large-prompt @PROMPT_PATH wrapper: helper emits a `promptFileBody`\n850:             // containing `<TARGET AUTHORITY preamble>\\n\\n---\\n\\n<original>`.\n851:             // Write it to disk so the file Copilot reads via @path opens with\n852:             // the authority block. Without this, recovered/bootstrap folder\n853:             // mentions inside the file could still anchor the model.\n854:             if (built.promptFileBody !== undefined) {\n855:               writeFileSync(promptPath, built.promptFileBody, 'utf8');\n856:             }\n857: \n858:             const result = spawnSync('copilot', built.argv, {\n859:               cwd: '{repo_root}',\n860:               stdio: 'inherit',\n861:               timeout: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}') * 1000,\n862:             });\n863:             process.exit(result.status ?? 1);\n864:             EOF\n865:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n866:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n867:           wait_for_completion: true\n868:           notes:\n869:             - \"copilot has no stdin support; prompt is positional\"\n870:             - \"Size check uses 16KB threshold; above that uses @PROMPT_PATH wrapper prompt\"\n871:             - \"Large-prompt path relies on copilot honoring @path references within its prompt string\"\n872:             - \"buildCopilotPromptArg attaches a TARGET AUTHORITY preamble bound to the workflow-approved spec folder; recovered context cannot override it (authority guard source: .opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_deep-review_auto.yaml)\"\n873:             - \"If spec_folder is missing/malformed/unresolved on a write-intent dispatch, the helper enforces plan-only by replacing the prompt with a Gate-3 question and stripping --allow-all-tools\"\n874:             - \"Large-prompt wrapper mode rewrites the prompt file at promptPath to include the TARGET AUTHORITY preamble (prefix + divider + original body); the argv becomes a bare @promptPath reference\"\n875:         if_cli_claude_code:\n876:           command: |\n877:             if [ -n \"{optional_claude_config_dir}\" ]; then export CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR=\"{optional_claude_config_dir}\"; fi\n878:             claude \\\n879:               -p \"$(cat '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md')\" \\\n880:               --model \"{config.executor.model}\" \\\n881:               --permission-mode acceptEdits \\\n882:               --output-format text \\\n883:               {optional_effort_flag}\n884:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n885:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n886:           wait_for_completion: true\n887:           render_hint:\n888:             optional_claude_config_dir: |\n889:               If config.executor.configDir is set and non-null, expand a leading ~ to HOME and bind that path.\n890:               Otherwise expand to empty string.\n891:             optional_effort_flag: |\n892:               If config.executor.reasoningEffort is set and non-null, expand to: --effort {config.executor.reasoningEffort}\n893:               Otherwise expand to empty string.\n894:           notes:\n895:             - \"claude-code default permission-mode is 'plan' (read-only); we override to 'acceptEdits' for iteration writes\"\n896:             - \"config.executor.configDir maps to CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR for account-specific Claude Code routing\"\n897:             - \"claude-code has no serviceTier flag\"\n898:             - \"claude-code supports --effort for reasoning depth\"\n899:         if_cli_opencode:\n900:           command: |\n901:             opencode run \\\n902:               --model \"{config.executor.model}\" \\\n903:               --format json \\\n904:               --dangerously-skip-permissions \\\n905:               --pure \\\n906:               --dir \"{repo_root}\" \\\n907:               {optional_variant_flag} \\\n908:               \"$(cat '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md')\" \\\n909:               </dev/null\n910:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n911:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n912:           wait_for_completion: true\n913:           render_hint:\n914:             optional_variant_flag: |\n915:               If config.executor.reasoningEffort is set and non-null, expand to: --variant {config.executor.reasoningEffort}\n916:               Otherwise expand to empty string.\n917:           notes:\n918:             - \"opencode run takes a positional message; prompt is fed via command substitution\"\n919:             - \"--variant maps reasoningEffort to opencode's provider-specific reasoning lever (e.g., high, medium, minimal)\"\n920:             - \"--dangerously-skip-permissions enables hands-off automation; sandboxMode='read-only' is not currently honored (no opencode equivalent)\"\n921:             - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude/Codex/raw shell). The cli-opencode skill SKILL.md В§SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"\n922:             - \"</dev/null required: opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation. Without explicit closed stdin, automation that redirects stdout/stderr hangs at 0% CPU after `+60s snapshot prune cleanup`. See cli-opencode SKILL.md В§4 ALWAYS rule + memory feedback_opencode_run_requires_dev_null_stdin.md.\"\n923:         post_dispatch_validate:\n924:           validator: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts#validateIterationOutputs\"\n925:           assert_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n926:           assert_appended: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n927:           assert_jsonl_fields: [type, iteration, mode, run, status, focus, dimensions, filesReviewed, findingsCount, findingsSummary, findingsNew, findingDetails, newFindingsRatio, sessionId, generation, lineageMode, timestamp, durationMs]\n928:           assert_canonical_type: \"iteration\"\n929:           assert_delta_file_exists: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n930:           assert_delta_file_has_iteration_record: true\n931:           failure_reasons:\n932:             - iteration_file_missing\n933:             - iteration_file_empty\n934:             - jsonl_not_appended\n935:             - jsonl_missing_fields\n936:             - jsonl_parse_error\n937:             - jsonl_wrong_type\n938:             - delta_file_missing\n939:             - delta_file_empty\n940:             - delta_file_missing_iteration_record\n941:             - executor_missing\n942:             - dispatch_failure_logged\n943:             - v2_missing_ledger\n944:             - v2_uncited_ledger_row\n945:             - v2_broken_linked_finding\n946:             - v2_shallow_finding_details\n947:             - delta_iteration_id_mismatch\n948:             - state_delta_iteration_mismatch\n949:           warning_surface:\n950:             source: \"result.warnings\"\n951:             action: \"emit schema_advisory canonical conflict event\"\n952:             severity: \"advisory\"\n953:             event_shape: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"schema_advisory\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"iteration\":{current_iteration},\"warnings\":{result.warnings},\"severity\":\"advisory\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n954:             note: \"Warnings do not fail dispatch. Hard failures still emit schema_mismatch through on_failure.\"\n955:           on_failure:\n956:             action: \"emit schema_mismatch canonical conflict event\"\n957:             escalation: \"After 3 consecutive failures, trigger stuck_recovery event with diagnostic context\"\n958:         record_executor_audit:\n959:           skip_when: \"config.executor.kind == 'native'\"\n960:           target: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n961:           field: \"executor\"\n962:           value:\n963:             kind: \"{config.executor.kind}\"\n964:             model: \"{config.executor.model}\"\n965:             reasoningEffort: \"{config.executor.reasoningEffort}\"\n966:             serviceTier: \"{config.executor.serviceTier}\"\n967: \n968:       step_evaluate_results:\n969:         action: \"Verify iteration outputs and extract metrics\"\n970:         verify:\n971:           - file_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n972:           - jsonl_appended: \"New iteration record in state.jsonl\"\n973:           - strategy_updated: \"Strategy.md has been modified\"\n974:         extract:\n975:           - newFindingsRatio: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n976:           - findings_count: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n977:           - severity_counts: \"From latest JSONL iteration record (P0, P1, P2)\"\n978:           - dimensions: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n979:           - files_reviewed: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n980:           - status: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n981:           - reviewed_artifacts: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n982:           - traceability_checks: \"From latest JSONL iteration record when present\"\n983:         on_missing_outputs:\n984:           action: \"Mark iteration as 'error', continue to next\"\n985:           # <!-- F-010-B5-03 -->\n986:           # Canonical iteration record: include sessionId, generation, durationMs so the reducer can persist\n987:           # the failure without dropping the iteration. Schema source: state_format.md В§Iteration Records.\n988:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":{current_iteration},\"run\":{current_iteration},\"mode\":\"review\",\"status\":\"error\",\"focus\":\"{next_dimension}\",\"dimensions\":[\"{next_dimension}\"],\"filesReviewed\":[],\"findingsCount\":0,\"findingsSummary\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"findingsNew\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"findingDetails\":[],\"traceabilityChecks\":{\"summary\":{\"required\":0,\"executed\":0,\"pass\":0,\"partial\":0,\"fail\":0,\"blocked\":0,\"notApplicable\":0,\"gatingFailures\":0},\"results\":[]},\"newFindingsRatio\":0.0,\"durationMs\":0,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation},\"lineageMode\":\"{config.lineage.lineageMode}\"}'\n989: \n990:       step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication:\n991:         action: \"Validate typed claim-adjudication packets for any new P0/P1 findings and persist the result to state.jsonl so the next iteration's claimAdjudicationGate can read it\"\n992:         verify:\n993:           - typed_packets_present: \"Every new P0/P1 finding in review/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md contains a claim-adjudication JSON block\"\n994:           - packet_fields: \"Each packet includes claim, evidenceRefs, counterevidenceSought, alternativeExplanation, finalSeverity, confidence, downgradeTrigger\"\n995:           - missing_packet_ids: \"List of new P0/P1 finding IDs that are missing a typed packet or field; empty array when all packets validate\"\n996:         on_pass:\n997:           set:\n998:             claim_adjudication_passed: true\n999:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"passed\":true,\"activeP0P1\":{active_p0_p1_count},\"missingPackets\":[],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n1000:           log: \"Claim adjudication passed for iteration {current_iteration}. All new P0/P1 findings have typed packets.\"\n1001:         on_fail:\n1002:           action: \"Mark the iteration as invalid for convergence. The next iteration's claimAdjudicationGate (step_check_convergence step 0) reads the persisted `passed: false` event and vetoes STOP until a follow-up iteration rewrites the packets.\"\n1003:           set:\n1004:             claim_adjudication_passed: false\n1005:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"passed\":false,\"activeP0P1\":{active_p0_p1_count},\"missingPackets\":{missing_packet_ids},\"reason\":\"Missing typed packet fields for new P0/P1 findings\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n1006:           log: \"Claim adjudication incomplete for new P0/P1 findings. Event persisted. The next iteration's step_check_convergence claim-adjudication pre-check will veto STOP while `passed: false` remains the latest event and active P0/P1 > 0.\"\n1007: \n1008:       step_reduce_review_state:\n1009:         action: \"Run reducer to refresh the canonical findings registry before dashboard generation\"\n1010:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n1011:         read:\n1012:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1013:           - \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1014:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1015:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1016:         write:\n1017:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1018:           - \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n1019:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1020:         failure_modes:\n1021:           malformed_delta: \"skip + warn\"\n1022:           missing_iteration_file: \"no-op + error\"\n1023:           schema_mismatch: \"reject + conflict event\"\n1024:         guarantee: \"Idempotent for identical inputs\"\n1025:         note: \"Reducer outputs findingsRegistry, dashboardMetrics, and strategyUpdates. Re-running the same inputs must be idempotent.\"\n1026: \n1027:       step_graph_upsert:\n1028:         action: \"Transform the latest iteration graphEvents delta into review graph nodes and edges, then upsert it\"\n1029:         read:\n1030:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1031:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1032:         transform: |\n1033:           1. Read the latest iteration JSONL record after reducer completion.\n1034:           2. If graphEvents is absent or empty, set graph_nodes_json = [] and graph_edges_json = [] and skip the upsert.\n1035:           3. For each graph event without relation/source/target, normalize type = uppercase(event.type || event.nodeKind || event.type) and keep only DIMENSION, FILE, FINDING, EVIDENCE, REMEDIATION, BUG_CLASS, INVARIANT, PRODUCER, CONSUMER, TEST.\n1036:           4. Emit nodes as { id, type, name, iteration, metadata } using the event label (or id fallback) and review metadata for run/current focus.\n1037:           5. For each graph event with relation + source + target, normalize relation = uppercase(event.relation) and keep only COVERS, EVIDENCE_FOR, CONTRADICTS, RESOLVES, CONFIRMS, ESCALATES, IN_DIMENSION, IN_FILE.\n1038:           6. Emit edges as { id, relation, sourceId, targetId, metadata } and deduplicate the batch by id.\n1039:           7. Discard malformed or unknown graph events instead of failing the review iteration.\n1040:         bash: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"review\\\" --session-id \\\"{session_id}\\\" --nodes '{graph_nodes_json}' --edges '{graph_edges_json}'\"\n1041:         note: \"Invoke the runtime script directly. Upsert only the latest iteration graph delta.\"\n1042:         outputs:\n1043:           - graph_nodes_json: \"JSON array of normalized review graph nodes for the latest iteration\"\n1044:           - graph_edges_json: \"JSON array of normalized review graph edges for the latest iteration\"\n1045:         skip_conditions:\n1046:           - \"Latest iteration record has no graphEvents array\"\n1047: \n1048:       step_generate_dashboard:\n1049:         action: \"Generate or refresh the review dashboard\"\n1050:         read:\n1051:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1052:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1053:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1054:         content: |\n1055:           # Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview\n1056: \n1057:           Auto-generated from JSONL state log and strategy file. Regenerated after every iteration evaluation.\n1058: \n1059:           ## Status\n1060:           - Review Target: {review_target} ({review_target_type})\n1061:           - Status: [ITERATING | CONVERGING | STUCK_RECOVERY | COMPLETE]\n1062:           - Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n1063:           - Provisional Verdict: [PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL | PENDING]\n1064:           - hasAdvisories: {has_advisories}\n1065: \n1066:           ## Findings Summary\n1067:           | Severity | Count | Trend |\n1068:           |----------|------:|-------|\n1069:           | P0 (Blockers) | {p0_count} | {p0_trend} |\n1070:           | P1 (Required) | {p1_count} | {p1_trend} |\n1071:           | P2 (Suggestions) | {p2_count} | {p2_trend} |\n1072: \n1073:           ## Dimension Coverage\n1074:           | Dimension | Status | Iteration | Findings |\n1075:           |-----------|--------|-----------|----------|\n1076:           | [per dimension from strategy + JSONL] |\n1077: \n1078:           ## Traceability Coverage\n1079:           | Protocol | Level | Status | Findings |\n1080:           |----------|-------|--------|----------|\n1081:           | [per protocol from traceabilityChecks] |\n1082: \n1083:           ## Progress\n1084:           | # | Dimension | Ratio | P0/P1/P2 | Status |\n1085:           |---|-----------|-------|----------|--------|\n1086:           | [per iteration from JSONL] |\n1087: \n1088:           ## Trend\n1089:           - Last 3 ratios: [{ratios}] [{trend}]\n1090:           - Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n1091:           - Gate violations: {guard_violations}\n1092: \n1093:           ## Next Focus\n1094:           {next_dimension}\n1095:         output: \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n1096:         note: \"Auto-generated from JSONL + strategy. Never manually edited.\"\n1097: \n1098:       step_update_tracking:\n1099:         action: \"Update loop tracking variables\"\n1100:         set:\n1101:           current_iteration: \"{current_iteration + 1}\"\n1102:           p0_count: \"Accumulate from severity_counts\"\n1103:           p1_count: \"Accumulate from severity_counts\"\n1104:           p2_count: \"Accumulate from severity_counts\"\n1105:           stuck_count: |\n1106:             if status == 'thought': unchanged (skip)\n1107:             if status == 'insight': 0 (reset)\n1108:             if newFindingsRatio <= 0.05: stuck_count + 1\n1109:             else: 0\n1110:         log: \"Iteration {N} complete. Dimensions: {dimensions}. newFindingsRatio: {newFindingsRatio}. Findings: P0={severity_counts.P0} P1={severity_counts.P1} P2={severity_counts.P2}. Stuck count: {stuck_count}.\"\n1111: \n1112:       step_loop_decision:\n1113:         action: \"Return to step_read_state for next iteration\"\n1114:         goto: step_read_state\n1115: \n1116:   # в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ\n1117:   # PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS\n1118:   # в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ\n1119:   phase_synthesis:\n1120:     purpose: Compile all iteration findings into review/review-report.md\n1121:     steps:\n1122: \n1123:       step_fanout_merge:\n1124:         description: \"Merge N lineage registries with strongest-restriction; bind p0/p1/p2 counts for step_derive_verdict; skip when single-executor\"\n1125:         skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n1126:         command: |\n1127:           node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs \\\n1128:             --loop-type review \\\n1129:             --artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n1130:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1131:         wait_for_completion: true\n1132:         bind_from_output:\n1133:           p0_count: \"active_p0\"\n1134:           p1_count: \"active_p1\"\n1135:           p2_count: \"active_p2\"\n1136: \n1137:       step_hydrate_summary_metrics:\n1138:         action: \"Hydrate summary metrics before synthesis\"\n1139:         read:\n1140:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1141:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1142:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1143:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1144:         extract:\n1145:           - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n1146:           - p0_count: \"Total P0 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n1147:           - p1_count: \"Total P1 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n1148:           - p2_count: \"Total P2 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n1149:           - dimensions_covered: \"List of reviewed dimensions\"\n1150:           - dimension_coverage: \"covered / total\"\n1151:           - ac_coverage_signal: \"For spec-folder targets only: if level is 2+ and checklist.md exists and implementation-summary.md is in-progress or later, surface the AC_COVERAGE advisory status; otherwise mark exempt.\"\n1152:           - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records\"\n1153:           - reason: \"Use the latest stop reason if present, else the frozen default 'converged'. (Must be a member of the STOP_REASONS enum: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused.)\"\n1154: \n1155:       # H-1 verdict derivation: parse findings JSONL, map highest severity to verdict\n1156:       # - PASS: no P0 or P1 findings (P2-only or clean)\n1157:       # - CONDITIONAL: any P1 findings (no P0)\n1158:       # - FAIL: any P0 findings\n1159:       # Final line of iteration-NNN.md MUST be exactly: \"Review verdict: PASS\" / \"Review verdict: CONDITIONAL\" / \"Review verdict: FAIL\"\n1160:       step_derive_verdict:\n1161:         action: \"Derive review verdict from accumulated findings\"\n1162:         algorithm: |\n1163:           if p0_count > 0:\n1164:             verdict = \"FAIL\"\n1165:           elif p1_count > 0:\n1166:             verdict = \"CONDITIONAL\"\n1167:           else:\n1168:             verdict = \"PASS\"\n1169:           has_advisories = (verdict == \"PASS\" and p2_count > 0)\n1170:           ac_coverage_signal is advisory while the validation rule is INFO/default-off; include it in synthesis traceability, but do not change the exact verdict enum from this signal alone.\n1171:         outputs:\n1172:           - verdict: \"PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL\"\n1173:           - has_advisories: \"Boolean true when verdict is PASS and any active P2 findings exist\"\n1174:           - ac_coverage_signal: \"exempt | disabled | pass | advisory-shortfall\"\n1175:         contract: |\n1176:           Every iteration-NNN.md must end with exactly: \"Review verdict: PASS\" (or CONDITIONAL or FAIL).\n1177:           Downstream automation parses this final line via exact string match вҖ” do not vary the format.\n1178: \n1179:       step_read_all_iterations:\n1180:         action: \"Read all iteration files and strategy\"\n1181:         read_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n1182:         read_also: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1183: \n1184:       step_build_finding_registry:\n1185:         action: \"Build deduplicated finding registry from all iterations\"\n1186:         algorithm: |\n1187:           1. Extract all findings from iteration JSONL delta files\n1188:           2. Compute content_hash for each finding (emission requirement):\n1189:              content_hash = sha256(file_path + \"\\u001f\" + line_range + \"\\u001f\" + finding_type + \"\\u001f\" + normalized_description_80chars)\n1190:              Normalized description = whitespace-collapsed, lowercased, first 80 chars of the finding description.\n1191:           3. Two-tier dedup:\n1192:              PRIMARY: group by content_hash field\n1193:                - Same content_hash, multiple dimensions вҶ’ single finding, merged `dimensions: [<all>]` array\n1194:                - Keep highest severity on duplicates\n1195:              FALLBACK (legacy records lacking content_hash): file:line + normalized_title\n1196:                - Same file:line, multiple dimensions вҶ’ single finding, multiple dimension tags\n1197:                - Keep highest severity on duplicates\n1198:           4. Track finding lifecycle:\n1199:              - status: active | duplicate | upgraded | downgraded | contested | resolved_false_positive\n1200:              - Record first_seen, upgraded_in, previous_severity for severity changes\n1201:              - Record dimensions array reflecting all dimensions that emitted this finding\n1202:           5. Resolve contradictions:\n1203:              - Findings marked contested across iterations вҶ’ referee pass\n1204:              - Determine final severity and status\n1205:           6. Count only 'active' findings for totals\n1206:         outputs:\n1207:           - finding_registry: \"Deduplicated list of all findings with metadata\"\n1208:           - active_p0: \"Count of active P0 findings\"\n1209:           - active_p1: \"Count of active P1 findings\"\n1210:           - active_p2: \"Count of active P2 findings\"\n1211: \n1212:       step_adversarial_selfcheck:\n1213:         action: \"Final adversarial self-check on all P0 and P1 findings\"\n1214:         algorithm: |\n1215:           For each active P0/P1 finding:\n1216:             1. Hunter: Re-verify finding against source code (re-read file:line)\n1217:             2. Skeptic: Challenge severity вҖ” is this really P0/P1? Could it be P2?\n1218:             3. Referee: Final call вҖ” confirm, downgrade, or mark false_positive\n1219:           Update finding_registry with adjudicated results.\n1220: \n1221:       step_emit_resource_map:\n1222:         action: \"Emit {state_paths.resource_map_output} from converged review deltas unless config.resource_map.emit is false\"\n1223:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} --emit-resource-map\"\n1224:         read:\n1225:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1226:           - \"{state_paths.delta_dir}/iter-*.jsonl\"\n1227:         write:\n1228:           - \"{state_paths.resource_map_output}\"\n1229:         guarantee: \"Reducer skips cleanly when config.resource_map.emit == false and writes a deterministic resource-map when enabled.\"\n1230: \n1231:       step_resource_map_coverage_gate:\n1232:         action: \"If resource_map_present, compute the Resource Map Coverage Gate synthesis inputs; otherwise preserve the skip note\"\n1233:         note: \"Cross-check target_files from {spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md against {spec_folder}/resource-map.md. Report touched entries, untouched entries split into expected-by-scope vs gap, and implementation paths absent from the map. Findings raised here use category resource-map-coverage with severity calibrated to the gate outcome.\"\n1234: \n1235:       step_compile_review_report:\n1236:         action: \"Compile review/review-report.md with 9 core sections, a conditional Resource Map Coverage Gate section, and an embedded Planning Packet\"\n1237:         instructions: |\n1238:           Create review/review-report.md with the following sections:\n1239: \n1240:           1. **Executive Summary**\n1241:              - Overall verdict: PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL\n1242:              - hasAdvisories: true when PASS carries active P2 items\n1243:              - P0/P1/P2 counts (active only)\n1244:              - Review scope summary\n1245: \n1246:           2. **Planning Trigger**\n1247:              - State whether `/speckit:plan` is required\n1248:              - Include a fenced `json` block labeled `Planning Packet`\n1249:              - The packet MUST include: `triggered`, `verdict`, `hasAdvisories`, `activeFindings`, `remediationWorkstreams`, `specSeed`, `planSeed`, `findingClasses`, `affectedSurfacesSeed`, `fixCompletenessRequired`\n1250:              - Build `activeFindings`, `findingClasses`, and `affectedSurfacesSeed` from reducer-owned state plus iteration JSONL `findingDetails`; if a field is missing, mark it `UNKNOWN` instead of inferring it from prose\n1251: \n1252:           3. **Active Finding Registry**\n1253:              - Unified registry for active P0/P1/P2 findings\n1254:              - For each: ID, severity, title, dimension, file:line, evidence, impact, fix recommendation, disposition, findingClass, scopeProof, affectedSurfaceHints\n1255: \n1256:           4. **Remediation Workstreams**\n1257:              - Ordered action groups: P0 first, then P1, with P2 advisories separated\n1258: \n1259:           5. **Spec Seed**\n1260:              - Concrete seed bullets for follow-on spec updates\n1261: \n1262:           6. **Plan Seed**\n1263:              - Concrete starter tasks for `/speckit:plan`\n1264: \n1265:            7. **Traceability Status**\n1266:               - Summarize required core protocols first, then applicable overlay protocols\n1267:               - Include status, evidence, and any unresolved drift per protocol\n1268:               - Include `AC_COVERAGE` status for lifecycle-active spec-folder targets: exempt, disabled, pass, or advisory-shortfall, with covered/total and floor when available\n1269: \n1270:           If `resource_map_present` is true, insert **## Resource Map Coverage Gate** after `Traceability Status` with exactly three bullets:\n1271:              - `Entries touched`: count of resource-map paths that appear in applied reports\n1272:              - `Entries not touched`: paths in resource-map not in implementation, labeled `expected-by-scope` or `gap`\n1273:              - `Implementation paths absent from resource-map`: `target_files` in applied reports not on the map\n1274: \n1275:           8. **Deferred Items**\n1276:              - Advisory-only or backlog-worthy follow-ups that do not block the current verdict\n1277: \n1278:           9. **Search Ledger**\n1279:              - Always include this section before the appendix.\n1280:              - Render reducer-owned `searchCoverage`, `candidateCoverage`, `searchDebt`, `ruledOutCandidates`, and `cleanSearchProof`.\n1281:              - If all arrays are empty or absent, include: `*No search-depth state captured (legacy v1 record)*`.\n1282:              - When `searchDebt` is non-empty, state `hasSearchDebt: true` and carry the dashboard verdict as CONDITIONAL unless active P0 findings make it FAIL.\n1283: \n1284:           10. **Audit Appendix**\n1285:              - Convergence summary, coverage summary, ruled-out claims, sources reviewed\n1286:              - Cross-reference appendix MUST be split into `Core Protocols` and `Overlay Protocols`\n1287: \n1288:           Preserve machine-owned markers so the reducer-owned registry, dashboard, and strategy anchors can be refreshed on re-run without mutating prior synthesis. (Note: `completed-continue` lineage branch is deferred вҖ” see `deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md В§Lifecycle Branches`.)\n1289:         output: \"{state_paths.review_output}\"\n1290: \n1291:       step_convergence_report:\n1292:         action: \"Append convergence report to JSONL\"\n1293:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"synthesis_complete\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"totalIterations\":{iteration_count},\"activeP0\":{active_p0},\"activeP1\":{active_p1},\"activeP2\":{active_p2},\"dimensionCoverage\":{dimension_coverage},\"verdict\":\"{verdict}\",\"releaseReadinessState\":\"{release_readiness_state}\",\"stopReason\":\"{reason}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n1294:         note: \"Emit as numeric ratio (e.g., 0.75), not quoted string. Compute: dimensions_covered / total_dimensions.\"\n1295: \n1296:       step_update_config_status:\n1297:         action: \"Mark config as complete\"\n1298:         edit: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1299:         set_field: { status: \"complete\" }\n1300: \n1301:       step_stage_artifact_dir:\n1302:         action: \"Stage all skill-owned artifacts under artifact_dir for the operator's next git commit\"\n1303:         command: \"git add {state_paths.packet_dir}\"\n1304:         note: \"Skill-owned contract fix (028): without this stage step, operators who do `git add review-report.md` lose the iteration trail (iterations/, deltas/, state.jsonl, strategy, findings-registry, etc.). Staging the whole artifact_dir keeps the audit trail intact. Operators retain commit authority and can `git restore --staged {path}` to unstage anything before commit. Failure is non-fatal вҖ” log warning and continue.\"\n1305:         on_fail: \"Log warning. Do not block synthesis. The artifact_dir may be outside a git repo (e.g., temp test fixture) which is a valid case.\"\n1306: \n1307:   # в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ\n1308:   # PHASE 4: SAVE\n1309:   # в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ\n1310:   phase_save:\n1311:     purpose: Preserve review context to memory system\n1312:     steps:\n1313: \n1314:       step_compose_save_payload:\n1315:         action: \"Compose the structured JSON payload consumed by generate-context.js\"\n1316:         output: \"/tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json\"\n1317:         requirements:\n1318:           - \"Write this file before invoking generate-context.js; the loader fails closed if the explicit JSON file is absent.\"\n1319:           - \"Include `specFolder`, a concise `sessionSummary`, curated `observations`, `recent_context`, `toolCalls`, and `exchanges` from the completed review loop.\"\n1320:           - \"Use a session-scoped temp filename; do not use the retired shared `/tmp/save-context-data.json` path.\"\n1321:         example_payload: |\n1322:           {\n1323:             \"specFolder\": \"{spec_folder}\",\n1324:             \"sessionSummary\": \"Deep review completed; see review/review-report.md for verdict, findings, and workstreams.\",\n1325:             \"observations\": [\"Summarize the active findings, verdict, and remediation guidance.\"],\n1326:             \"recent_context\": [\"Point to the generated review artifacts and next action.\"],\n1327:             \"exchanges\": [],\n1328:             \"toolCalls\": []\n1329:           }\n1330: \n1331:       step_generate_context:\n1332:         action: \"Route continuity content into the correct canonical spec document via generate-context.js\"\n1333:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json {spec_folder}\"\n1334:         critical_rule: \"NEVER manually author files under retired memory/ paths (the runtime rejects them); use generate-context.js so the save routes into decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md\"\n1335: \n1336:       step_index_memory:\n1337:         action: \"Index the routed canonical spec document with memory_save when immediate MCP visibility is required\"\n1338:         mcp_tool: memory_save\n1339:         invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"[routed-canonical-spec-doc-path]\" })'\n1340:         note: \"Use the actual canonical spec-doc path returned by generate-context.js (decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md); memory_index_scan remains the bulk fallback\"\n1341: \n1342:       step_verify_save:\n1343:         action: \"Verify canonical save routed content into the correct spec document\"\n1344:         check: \"Does {spec_folder}/implementation-summary.md, {spec_folder}/decision-record.md, or {spec_folder}/handover.md carry the new continuity update?\"\n1345:         on_fail: \"Log warning but do not block completion\"\n1346: \n1347:       step_release_lock:\n1348:         action: \"Release the single-writer lock after save, skip-save, or cancellation cleanup has resolved\"\n1349:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}\"\n1350:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"lock_released\",\"path\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"releasePhase\":\"save\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n1351: \n1352:   # в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ\n1353:   # COMPLETION\n1354:   # в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ\n1355:   completion:\n1356:     message: |\n1357:       Deep review complete.\n1358:       Iterations: {iteration_count} | Stop reason: {reason}\n1359:       Findings: P0={active_p0} P1={active_p1} P2={active_p2}\n1360:       Verdict: {verdict} | hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n1361: \n1362:       Artifacts:\n1363:         - review/review-report.md (compiled from {iteration_count} iterations)\n1364:         - {iteration_count} iteration files in review/iterations/\n1365:         - State files in review/: deep-review-config.json, deep-review-state.jsonl, deep-review-findings-registry.json, deep-review-strategy.md, deep-review-dashboard.md\n1366:         - Memory context saved\n1367: \n1368:       STATUS=OK PATH={spec_folder}\n1369:     next_steps:\n1370:       - \"/speckit:plan [remediation] (if FAIL or CONDITIONAL verdict)\"\n1371:       - \"/create:changelog (if PASS, including PASS with hasAdvisories=true)\"\n1372:       - \"/deep:review [target] (for another review)\"\n1373:       - \"/memory:save {spec_folder} (refresh canonical continuity before the next session)\"\n1374: \n1375: # в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n1376: # ERROR RECOVERY\n1377: # в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n1378: error_recovery:\n1379:   agent_dispatch_timeout: \"Retry once with reduced scope (fewer files per iteration). If second timeout, mark as 'timeout' and continue.\"\n1380:   state_file_missing: \"If JSONL missing during loop, reconstruct from iteration files. If strategy missing, create minimal version.\"\n1381:   consecutive_failures: \"After 3 consecutive errors, halt loop and enter synthesis with partial findings.\"\n1382:   memory_save_failure: \"Preserve the review packet in review/ as backup. Log warning.\"\n1383: \n1384: # в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n1385: # RULES\n1386: # в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n1387: rules:\n1388:   ALWAYS:\n1389:     - follow_workflow_phases_in_order\n1390:     - dispatch_deep_review_agent_per_iteration\n1391:     - check_convergence_before_each_iteration\n1392:     - write_all_state_to_files\n1393:     - save_memory_context_after_synthesis\n1394:     - respect_max_iterations_cap\n1395:     - treat_review_target_as_read_only\n1396:     - deduplicate_findings_before_synthesis\n1397:     - run_adversarial_selfcheck_on_p0_p1\n1398:   NEVER:\n1399:     - skip_convergence_check\n1400:     - dispatch_non_leaf_agents\n1401:     - hold_iteration_findings_in_memory_only\n1402:     - modify_config_after_initialization\n1403:     - overwrite_jsonl_state_log\n1404:     - proceed_without_state_file_verification\n1405:     - modify_files_under_review\n1406:     - report_p0_without_file_line_evidence\n1407: \n1408: # в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n1409: # REFERENCE-ONLY APPENDIX\n1410: # в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n1411: reference_only_appendix:\n1412:   checkpoint_commit:\n1413:     note: \"Checkpoint commits are intentionally excluded from workflow.steps.\"\n1414:     commands:\n1415:       - \"git add {state_paths.iteration_pattern} {state_paths.state_log} {state_paths.findings_registry} {state_paths.strategy} {state_paths.review_output}\"\n1416:       - 'git commit -m \"chore(deep-review): iteration {NNN} complete\"'\n1417:   severity_weights:\n1418:     note: \"Severity weights for newFindingsRatio calculation\"\n1419:     weights:\n1420:       P0: 10.0\n1421:       P1: 5.0\n1422:       P2: 1.0\n1423:     p0_override: \"If ANY new P0 discovered вҶ’ newFindingsRatio = max(calculated, 0.50). A single new P0 blocks convergence.\"\n1424:     clean_pass: \"If total_findings == 0 (clean pass) вҶ’ newFindingsRatio = 0.0\"\n1425:   review_dimensions:\n1426:     note: \"All 4 default review dimensions with priority ordering\"\n1427:     dimensions:\n1428:       - { priority: 1, name: \"correctness\", checks: \"Logic, state flow, edge cases, error handling\" }\n1429:       - { priority: 2, name: \"security\", checks: \"Auth, input/output safety, data exposure, permissions\" }\n1430:       - { priority: 3, name: \"traceability\", checks: \"Spec/checklist alignment, cross-reference integrity, evidence coverage\" }\n1431:       - { priority: 4, name: \"maintainability\", checks: \"Patterns, documentation quality, safe follow-on change clarity\" }\n1432:   cross_reference_protocols:\n1433:     note: \"Cross-reference verification protocols split into core and overlay classes\"\n1434:     core_protocols:\n1435:       - { check: \"Spec vs Code\", source: \"spec.md claims\", target: \"implementation\" }\n1436:       - { check: \"Checklist vs Evidence\", source: \"[x] items\", target: \"cited evidence\" }\n1437:     overlay_protocols:\n1438:       - { check: \"SKILL.md vs Agent\", source: \"Skill contracts\", target: \"agent files\" }\n1439:       - { check: \"Agent Cross-Runtime\", source: \".claude\", target: \".codex/.opencode/.agents\" }\n1440:       - { check: \"Feature Catalog vs Code\", source: \"Catalog claims\", target: \"implementation\" }\n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 635-1440. Use offset=1441 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"        action: \"Persist blocked-stop evidence whenever the review legal-stop decision tree vetoes STOP\"\n        if_blocked:\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergenceGate\":{\"pass\":{convergence_gate_pass},\"score\":{convergence_gate_score}},\"dimensionCoverageGate\":{\"pass\":{dimension_coverage_gate_pass},\"covered\":{dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json},\"missing\":{dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json}},\"p0ResolutionGate\":{\"pass\":{p0_resolution_gate_pass},\"activeP0\":{active_p0_count}},\"evidenceDensityGate\":{\"pass\":{evidence_density_gate_pass},\"avgEvidencePerFinding\":{avg_evidence_per_finding}},\"hotspotSaturationGate\":{\"pass\":{hotspot_saturation_gate_pass}},\"claimAdjudicationGate\":{\"pass\":{claim_adjudication_gate_pass},\"activeP0P1\":{claim_adjudication_active_count}},\"fixCompletenessReplayGate\":{\"pass\":{fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass},\"securitySensitive\":{security_sensitive_fix_scope},\"requiredRows\":{fix_completeness_replay_required_rows},\"passingRows\":{fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows}},\"candidateCoverageGate\":{\"pass\":{candidate_coverage_gate_pass},\"searchDebt\":{candidate_coverage_search_debt_json},\"missing\":{candidate_coverage_missing_json}},\"graphlessFallbackGate\":{\"pass\":{graphless_fallback_gate_pass},\"mode\":\"{graphless_fallback_mode}\",\"missing\":{graphless_fallback_missing_json},\"unavailabilityReason\":\"{graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason}\"}},\"graphBlockerDetail\":{graph_blockers_json},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n          log: \"Blocked STOP persisted for review loop. Failed gates: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n        if_not_blocked:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_handle_convergence:\n        action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n        if_stop:\n          log: \"Loop stopping. Reason: {reason}\"\n          skip_to: phase_synthesis\n        if_blocked:\n          log: \"Legal-stop gates blocked STOP. Failed gates: {blocked_by_csv}. Continuing review.\"\n        if_stuck_recovery:\n          log: \"Stuck detected ({stuck_count} consecutive no-progress). Entering recovery.\"\n          recovery_strategies:\n            - \"Change granularity: file-level вҶ’ function-level вҶ’ line-level review\"\n            - \"Traceability protocol replay: re-run unresolved core or overlay checks\"\n            - \"Escalate severity review: re-examine P2 findings for potential P1 upgrades\"","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","text":"        action: \"Persist blocked-stop evidence whenever the review legal-stop decision tree vetoes STOP\"\n        if_blocked:\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergenceGate\":{\"pass\":{convergence_gate_pass},\"score\":{convergence_gate_score}},\"dimensionCoverageGate\":{\"pass\":{dimension_coverage_gate_pass},\"covered\":{dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json},\"missing\":{dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json}},\"p0ResolutionGate\":{\"pass\":{p0_resolution_gate_pass},\"activeP0\":{active_p0_count}},\"evidenceDensityGate\":{\"pass\":{evidence_density_gate_pass},\"avgEvidencePerFinding\":{avg_evidence_per_finding}},\"hotspotSaturationGate\":{\"pass\":{hotspot_saturation_gate_pass}},\"claimAdjudicationGate\":{\"pass\":{claim_adjudication_gate_pass},\"activeP0P1\":{claim_adjudication_active_count}},\"fixCompletenessReplayGate\":{\"pass\":{fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass},\"securitySensitive\":{security_sensitive_fix_scope},\"requiredRows\":{fix_completeness_replay_required_rows},\"passingRows\":{fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows}},\"candidateCoverageGate\":{\"pass\":{candidate_coverage_gate_pass},\"searchDebt\":{candidate_coverage_search_debt_json},\"missing\":{candidate_coverage_missing_json}},\"graphlessFallbackGate\":{\"pass\":{graphless_fallback_gate_pass},\"mode\":\"{graphless_fallback_mode}\",\"missing\":{graphless_fallback_missing_json},\"unavailabilityReason\":\"{graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason}\"}},\"graphBlockerDetail\":{graph_blockers_json},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n          log: \"Blocked STOP persisted for review loop. Failed gates: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n        if_not_blocked:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_handle_convergence:\n        action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n        if_stop:\n          log: \"Loop stopping. Reason: {reason}\"\n          skip_to: phase_synthesis\n        if_blocked:\n          log: \"Legal-stop gates blocked STOP. Failed gates: {blocked_by_csv}. Continuing review.\"\n        if_stuck_recovery:\n          log: \"Stuck detected ({stuck_count} consecutive no-progress). Entering recovery.\"\n          recovery_strategies:\n            - \"Change granularity: file-level вҶ’ function-level вҶ’ line-level review\"\n            - \"Traceability protocol replay: re-run unresolved core or overlay checks\"\n            - \"Escalate severity review: re-examine P2 findings for potential P1 upgrades\"\n          pivot_target: \"Pivot to the least-covered dimension (the review dimension with the fewest iteration passes and lowest coverage ratio).\"\n          set:\n            next_dimension: \"RECOVERY: {recovery_strategy}. Least-covered dimension: {least_explored}\"\n            pending_stop_event: \"stuck_recovery\"\n            pending_stop_reason: \"stuckRecovery\"\n            pending_stop_detail: \"Recovery path activated after repeated no-progress iterations\"\n          reset: { stuck_count: 0 }\n        if_continue:\n          log: \"Iteration {current_iteration}: Continuing. Dimension: {next_dimension}\"\n\n      step_normalize_pause_events:\n        action: \"Rewrite raw pause and recovery events to the frozen STOP_REASONS enum at emission time: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused\"\n        if_pending_pause_event:\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"reason\":\"{pending_stop_detail}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n          message: \"Review paused. Delete review/.deep-review-pause to resume.\"\n          reset:\n            pending_stop_event: null\n            pending_stop_reason: null\n            pending_stop_detail: null\n          halt: true\n        if_pending_stuck_recovery:\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"strategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"targetDimension\":\"{least_explored}\",\"outcome\":\"pending\",\"reason\":\"{pending_stop_detail}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n          reset:\n            pending_stop_event: null\n            pending_stop_reason: null\n            pending_stop_detail: null\n        if_no_pending_event:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_generate_state_summary:\n        action: \"Generate compact state summary for dispatch context (~200 tokens)\"\n        generate: |\n          STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n          Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n          Dimension: {next_dimension}\n          Prior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n          Dimension Coverage: {dimensions_covered_list} ({dimension_coverage})\n          Traceability: core={core_protocol_status} overlay={overlay_protocol_status}\n          {resource_map_prompt_line}\n          Coverage Age: {coverage_age}\n          Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest}\n          Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n          Provisional Verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n\n      step_marker_scan:\n        action: \"H-2 loop-prevention guard: scan previous iteration's rendered prompt for nested review marker\"\n        algorithm: |\n          if current_iteration > 1:\n            PREV_PROMPT_PATH = \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{previous_iteration}.md\"\n            if file_exists(PREV_PROMPT_PATH):\n              PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE = head -1 of PREV_PROMPT_PATH\n              if PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE matches ^(DEEP-REVIEW|DEEP-RESEARCH|CODE-REVIEW)$:\n                log \"ERROR: nested review-of-review loop detected (marker found in previous iteration prompt). Aborting.\"\n                halt with exit code 2\n        note: |\n          False-positive prevention: only matches when the first line is exactly one of the\n          three canonical markers. Markers appearing in comments or body text are ignored.\n          True-positive triggers only when a previous iteration's rendered prompt literally\n          starts with a deep-loop marker, indicating a nested review-of-review dispatch.\n\n      step_dispatch_iteration:\n        action: \"Dispatch @deep-review agent for one review iteration\"\n        resolve_executor:\n          source: \"config.executor\"\n          loader: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n        pre_dispatch:\n          generate_summary: |\n            STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n            Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n            Dimension: {next_dimension}\n            Prior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n            Dimension Coverage: {dimensions_covered_list} ({dimension_coverage})\n            Traceability: core={core_protocol_status} overlay={overlay_protocol_status}\n            {resource_map_prompt_line}\n            Coverage Age: {coverage_age}\n            Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest}\n            Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n            Provisional Verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n          render_prompt_pack:\n            template_path: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl\"\n            renderer: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n            output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n            variables:\n              state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"\n              current_iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n              max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n              next_dimension: \"{next_dimension}\"\n              review_target: \"{review_target}\"\n              review_scope_files: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n              p0_count: \"{p0_count}\"\n              p1_count: \"{p1_count}\"\n              p2_count: \"{p2_count}\"\n              state_paths_config: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n              state_paths_state_log: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n              state_paths_findings_registry: \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n              state_paths_strategy: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n              state_paths_iteration_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n              state_paths_delta_pattern: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n        pre_dispatch_audit:\n          skip_when: \"config.executor.kind == 'native'\"\n          call: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts#writeFirstRecordExecutor\"\n          args:\n            stateLogPath: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n            executor: \"{config.executor}\"\n            iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n        branch_on: \"config.executor.kind\"\n        if_native:\n          dispatch:\n            agent: deep-review\n            model: opus\n            context_source: \"rendered_prompt_pack\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n        if_cli_codex:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n\n            import { runAuditedExecutorCommandAsync } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n            import { resolveCodexSandboxMode } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n\n            const executor = {\n              kind: 'cli-codex',\n              model: '{config.executor.model}',\n              configDir: '{config.executor.configDir}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.configDir}',\n              reasoningEffort: '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}',\n              serviceTier: '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}',\n              sandboxMode: '{config.executor.sandboxMode}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.sandboxMode}',\n              timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n            };\n\n            process.exit(await runAuditedExecutorCommandAsync({\n              command: 'codex',\n              args: [\n                'exec',\n                '--model',\n                executor.model,\n                '-c',\n                `model_reasoning_effort=${executor.reasoningEffort}`,\n                '-c',\n                `service_tier=${executor.serviceTier}`,\n                '-c',\n                'approval_policy=never',\n                '--sandbox',\n                resolveCodexSandboxMode(executor.sandboxMode),\n                '-',\n              ],\n              cwd: '{repo_root}',\n              timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n              stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n              executor,\n              iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n              input: readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n            }));\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n        if_cli_copilot:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync, writeFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n            import { spawnSync } from 'node:child_process';\n\n            import { buildCopilotPromptArg } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n\n            const promptPath = '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md';\n            const prompt = readFileSync(promptPath, 'utf8');\n\n            // Workflow-resolved spec folder is the only legal write authority.\n            // The helper (`validateSpecFolder` inside `buildCopilotPromptArg`)\n            // is the single source of truth for rejecting empty / unresolved\n            // template / whitespace-only / string-coerced empty values. The\n            // YAML hands the raw `{spec_folder}` directly; on rejection the\n            // helper safe-fails to `type:\"missing\", writeIntent:true` (Gate-3\n            // enforcement, --allow-all-tools stripped).\n            const specFolderRaw = '{spec_folder}';\n            const targetAuthority = { type: 'approved', specFolder: specFolderRaw };\n\n            const baseArgs = [\n              '-p',\n              prompt,\n              '--model',\n              '{config.executor.model}',\n              '--allow-all-tools',\n              '--no-ask-user',\n            ];\n\n            const built = buildCopilotPromptArg({\n              promptPath,\n              prompt,\n              targetAuthority,\n              baseArgv: baseArgs,\n            });\n\n            // Large-prompt @PROMPT_PATH wrapper: helper emits a `promptFileBody`\n            // containing `<TARGET AUTHORITY preamble>\\n\\n---\\n\\n<original>`.\n            // Write it to disk so the file Copilot reads via @path opens with\n            // the authority block. Without this, recovered/bootstrap folder\n            // mentions inside the file could still anchor the model.\n            if (built.promptFileBody !== undefined) {\n              writeFileSync(promptPath, built.promptFileBody, 'utf8');\n            }\n\n            const result = spawnSync('copilot', built.argv, {\n              cwd: '{repo_root}',\n              stdio: 'inherit',\n              timeout: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}') * 1000,\n            });\n            process.exit(result.status ?? 1);\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          notes:\n            - \"copilot has no stdin support; prompt is positional\"\n            - \"Size check uses 16KB threshold; above that uses @PROMPT_PATH wrapper prompt\"\n            - \"Large-prompt path relies on copilot honoring @path references within its prompt string\"\n            - \"buildCopilotPromptArg attaches a TARGET AUTHORITY preamble bound to the workflow-approved spec folder; recovered context cannot override it (authority guard source: .opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_deep-review_auto.yaml)\"\n            - \"If spec_folder is missing/malformed/unresolved on a write-intent dispatch, the helper enforces plan-only by replacing the prompt with a Gate-3 question and stripping --allow-all-tools\"\n            - \"Large-prompt wrapper mode rewrites the prompt file at promptPath to include the TARGET AUTHORITY preamble (prefix + divider + original body); the argv becomes a bare @promptPath reference\"\n        if_cli_claude_code:\n          command: |\n            if [ -n \"{optional_claude_config_dir}\" ]; then export CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR=\"{optional_claude_config_dir}\"; fi\n            claude \\\n              -p \"$(cat '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md')\" \\\n              --model \"{config.executor.model}\" \\\n              --permission-mode acceptEdits \\\n              --output-format text \\\n              {optional_effort_flag}\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          render_hint:\n            optional_claude_config_dir: |\n              If config.executor.configDir is set and non-null, expand a leading ~ to HOME and bind that path.\n              Otherwise expand to empty string.\n            optional_effort_flag: |\n              If config.executor.reasoningEffort is set and non-null, expand to: --effort {config.executor.reasoningEffort}\n              Otherwise expand to empty string.\n          notes:\n            - \"claude-code default permission-mode is 'plan' (read-only); we override to 'acceptEdits' for iteration writes\"\n            - \"config.executor.configDir maps to CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR for account-specific Claude Code routing\"\n            - \"claude-code has no serviceTier flag\"\n            - \"claude-code supports --effort for reasoning depth\"\n        if_cli_opencode:\n          command: |\n            opencode run \\\n              --model \"{config.executor.model}\" \\\n              --format json \\\n              --dangerously-skip-permissions \\\n              --pure \\\n              --dir \"{repo_root}\" \\\n              {optional_variant_flag} \\\n              \"$(cat '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md')\" \\\n              </dev/null\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          render_hint:\n            optional_variant_flag: |\n              If config.executor.reasoningEffort is set and non-null, expand to: --variant {config.executor.reasoningEffort}\n              Otherwise expand to empty string.\n          notes:\n            - \"opencode run takes a positional message; prompt is fed via command substitution\"\n            - \"--variant maps reasoningEffort to opencode's provider-specific reasoning lever (e.g., high, medium, minimal)\"\n            - \"--dangerously-skip-permissions enables hands-off automation; sandboxMode='read-only' is not currently honored (no opencode equivalent)\"\n            - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude/Codex/raw shell). The cli-opencode skill SKILL.md В§SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"\n            - \"</dev/null required: opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation. Without explicit closed stdin, automation that redirects stdout/stderr hangs at 0% CPU after `+60s snapshot prune cleanup`. See cli-opencode SKILL.md В§4 ALWAYS rule + memory feedback_opencode_run_requires_dev_null_stdin.md.\"\n        post_dispatch_validate:\n          validator: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts#validateIterationOutputs\"\n          assert_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          assert_appended: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          assert_jsonl_fields: [type, iteration, mode, run, status, focus, dimensions, filesReviewed, findingsCount, findingsSummary, findingsNew, findingDetails, newFindingsRatio, sessionId, generation, lineageMode, timestamp, durationMs]\n          assert_canonical_type: \"iteration\"\n          assert_delta_file_exists: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n          assert_delta_file_has_iteration_record: true\n          failure_reasons:\n            - iteration_file_missing\n            - iteration_file_empty\n            - jsonl_not_appended\n            - jsonl_missing_fields\n            - jsonl_parse_error\n            - jsonl_wrong_type\n            - delta_file_missing\n            - delta_file_empty\n            - delta_file_missing_iteration_record\n            - executor_missing\n            - dispatch_failure_logged\n            - v2_missing_ledger\n            - v2_uncited_ledger_row\n            - v2_broken_linked_finding\n            - v2_shallow_finding_details\n            - delta_iteration_id_mismatch\n            - state_delta_iteration_mismatch\n          warning_surface:\n            source: \"result.warnings\"\n            action: \"emit schema_advisory canonical conflict event\"\n            severity: \"advisory\"\n            event_shape: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"schema_advisory\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"iteration\":{current_iteration},\"warnings\":{result.warnings},\"severity\":\"advisory\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n            note: \"Warnings do not fail dispatch. Hard failures still emit schema_mismatch through on_failure.\"\n          on_failure:\n            action: \"emit schema_mismatch canonical conflict event\"\n            escalation: \"After 3 consecutive failures, trigger stuck_recovery event with diagnostic context\"\n        record_executor_audit:\n          skip_when: \"config.executor.kind == 'native'\"\n          target: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          field: \"executor\"\n          value:\n            kind: \"{config.executor.kind}\"\n            model: \"{config.executor.model}\"\n            reasoningEffort: \"{config.executor.reasoningEffort}\"\n            serviceTier: \"{config.executor.serviceTier}\"\n\n      step_evaluate_results:\n        action: \"Verify iteration outputs and extract metrics\"\n        verify:\n          - file_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          - jsonl_appended: \"New iteration record in state.jsonl\"\n          - strategy_updated: \"Strategy.md has been modified\"\n        extract:\n          - newFindingsRatio: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - findings_count: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - severity_counts: \"From latest JSONL iteration record (P0, P1, P2)\"\n          - dimensions: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - files_reviewed: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - status: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - reviewed_artifacts: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - traceability_checks: \"From latest JSONL iteration record when present\"\n        on_missing_outputs:\n          action: \"Mark iteration as 'error', continue to next\"\n          # <!-- F-010-B5-03 -->\n          # Canonical iteration record: include sessionId, generation, durationMs so the reducer can persist\n          # the failure without dropping the iteration. Schema source: state_format.md В§Iteration Records.\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":{current_iteration},\"run\":{current_iteration},\"mode\":\"review\",\"status\":\"error\",\"focus\":\"{next_dimension}\",\"dimensions\":[\"{next_dimension}\"],\"filesReviewed\":[],\"findingsCount\":0,\"findingsSummary\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"findingsNew\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"findingDetails\":[],\"traceabilityChecks\":{\"summary\":{\"required\":0,\"executed\":0,\"pass\":0,\"partial\":0,\"fail\":0,\"blocked\":0,\"notApplicable\":0,\"gatingFailures\":0},\"results\":[]},\"newFindingsRatio\":0.0,\"durationMs\":0,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation},\"lineageMode\":\"{config.lineage.lineageMode}\"}'\n\n      step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication:\n        action: \"Validate typed claim-adjudication packets for any new P0/P1 findings and persist the result to state.jsonl so the next iteration's claimAdjudicationGate can read it\"\n        verify:\n          - typed_packets_present: \"Every new P0/P1 finding in review/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md contains a claim-adjudication JSON block\"\n          - packet_fields: \"Each packet includes claim, evidenceRefs, counterevidenceSought, alternativeExplanation, finalSeverity, confidence, downgradeTrigger\"\n          - missing_packet_ids: \"List of new P0/P1 finding IDs that are missing a typed packet or field; empty array when all packets validate\"\n        on_pass:\n          set:\n            claim_adjudication_passed: true\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"passed\":true,\"activeP0P1\":{active_p0_p1_count},\"missingPackets\":[],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n          log: \"Claim adjudication passed for iteration {current_iteration}. All new P0/P1 findings have typed packets.\"\n        on_fail:\n          action: \"Mark the iteration as invalid for convergence. The next iteration's claimAdjudicationGate (step_check_convergence step 0) reads the persisted `passed: false` event and vetoes STOP until a follow-up iteration rewrites the packets.\"\n          set:\n            claim_adjudication_passed: false\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"passed\":false,\"activeP0P1\":{active_p0_p1_count},\"missingPackets\":{missing_packet_ids},\"reason\":\"Missing typed packet fields for new P0/P1 findings\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n          log: \"Claim adjudication incomplete for new P0/P1 findings. Event persisted. The next iteration's step_check_convergence claim-adjudication pre-check will veto STOP while `passed: false` remains the latest event and active P0/P1 > 0.\"\n\n      step_reduce_review_state:\n        action: \"Run reducer to refresh the canonical findings registry before dashboard generation\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        write:\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        failure_modes:\n          malformed_delta: \"skip + warn\"\n          missing_iteration_file: \"no-op + error\"\n          schema_mismatch: \"reject + conflict event\"\n        guarantee: \"Idempotent for identical inputs\"\n        note: \"Reducer outputs findingsRegistry, dashboardMetrics, and strategyUpdates. Re-running the same inputs must be idempotent.\"\n\n      step_graph_upsert:\n        action: \"Transform the latest iteration graphEvents delta into review graph nodes and edges, then upsert it\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n        transform: |\n          1. Read the latest iteration JSONL record after reducer completion.\n          2. If graphEvents is absent or empty, set graph_nodes_json = [] and graph_edges_json = [] and skip the upsert.\n          3. For each graph event without relation/source/target, normalize type = uppercase(event.type || event.nodeKind || event.type) and keep only DIMENSION, FILE, FINDING, EVIDENCE, REMEDIATION, BUG_CLASS, INVARIANT, PRODUCER, CONSUMER, TEST.\n          4. Emit nodes as { id, type, name, iteration, metadata } using the event label (or id fallback) and review metadata for run/current focus.\n          5. For each graph event with relation + source + target, normalize relation = uppercase(event.relation) and keep only COVERS, EVIDENCE_FOR, CONTRADICTS, RESOLVES, CONFIRMS, ESCALATES, IN_DIMENSION, IN_FILE.\n          6. Emit edges as { id, relation, sourceId, targetId, metadata } and deduplicate the batch by id.\n          7. Discard malformed or unknown graph events instead of failing the review iteration.\n        bash: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"review\\\" --session-id \\\"{session_id}\\\" --nodes '{graph_nodes_json}' --edges '{graph_edges_json}'\"\n        note: \"Invoke the runtime script directly. Upsert only the latest iteration graph delta.\"\n        outputs:\n          - graph_nodes_json: \"JSON array of normalized review graph nodes for the latest iteration\"\n          - graph_edges_json: \"JSON array of normalized review graph edges for the latest iteration\"\n        skip_conditions:\n          - \"Latest iteration record has no graphEvents array\"\n\n      step_generate_dashboard:\n        action: \"Generate or refresh the review dashboard\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        content: |\n          # Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview\n\n          Auto-generated from JSONL state log and strategy file. Regenerated after every iteration evaluation.\n\n          ## Status\n          - Review Target: {review_target} ({review_target_type})\n          - Status: [ITERATING | CONVERGING | STUCK_RECOVERY | COMPLETE]\n          - Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n          - Provisional Verdict: [PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL | PENDING]\n          - hasAdvisories: {has_advisories}\n\n          ## Findings Summary\n          | Severity | Count | Trend |\n          |----------|------:|-------|\n          | P0 (Blockers) | {p0_count} | {p0_trend} |\n          | P1 (Required) | {p1_count} | {p1_trend} |\n          | P2 (Suggestions) | {p2_count} | {p2_trend} |\n\n          ## Dimension Coverage\n          | Dimension | Status | Iteration | Findings |\n          |-----------|--------|-----------|----------|\n          | [per dimension from strategy + JSONL] |\n\n          ## Traceability Coverage\n          | Protocol | Level | Status | Findings |\n          |----------|-------|--------|----------|\n          | [per protocol from traceabilityChecks] |\n\n          ## Progress\n          | # | Dimension | Ratio | P0/P1/P2 | Status |\n          |---|-----------|-------|----------|--------|\n          | [per iteration from JSONL] |\n\n          ## Trend\n          - Last 3 ratios: [{ratios}] [{trend}]\n          - Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n          - Gate violations: {guard_violations}\n\n          ## Next Focus\n          {next_dimension}\n        output: \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n        note: \"Auto-generated from JSONL + strategy. Never manually edited.\"\n\n      step_update_tracking:\n        action: \"Update loop tracking variables\"\n        set:\n          current_iteration: \"{current_iteration + 1}\"\n          p0_count: \"Accumulate from severity_counts\"\n          p1_count: \"Accumulate from severity_counts\"\n          p2_count: \"Accumulate from severity_counts\"\n          stuck_count: |\n            if status == 'thought': unchanged (skip)\n            if status == 'insight': 0 (reset)\n            if newFindingsRatio <= 0.05: stuck_count + 1\n            else: 0\n        log: \"Iteration {N} complete. Dimensions: {dimensions}. newFindingsRatio: {newFindingsRatio}. Findings: P0={severity_counts.P0} P1={severity_counts.P1} P2={severity_counts.P2}. Stuck count: {stuck_count}.\"\n\n      step_loop_decision:\n        action: \"Return to step_read_state for next iteration\"\n        goto: step_read_state\n\n  # в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ\n  # PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS\n  # в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ\n  phase_synthesis:\n    purpose: Compile all iteration findings into review/review-report.md\n    steps:\n\n      step_fanout_merge:\n        description: \"Merge N lineage registries with strongest-restriction; bind p0/p1/p2 counts for step_derive_verdict; skip when single-executor\"\n        skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs \\\n            --loop-type review \\\n            --artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true\n        bind_from_output:\n          p0_count: \"active_p0\"\n          p1_count: \"active_p1\"\n          p2_count: \"active_p2\"\n\n      step_hydrate_summary_metrics:\n        action: \"Hydrate summary metrics before synthesis\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        extract:\n          - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n          - p0_count: \"Total P0 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n          - p1_count: \"Total P1 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n          - p2_count: \"Total P2 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n          - dimensions_covered: \"List of reviewed dimensions\"\n          - dimension_coverage: \"covered / total\"\n          - ac_coverage_signal: \"For spec-folder targets only: if level is 2+ and checklist.md exists and implementation-summary.md is in-progress or later, surface the AC_COVERAGE advisory status; otherwise mark exempt.\"\n          - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records\"\n          - reason: \"Use the latest stop reason if present, else the frozen default 'converged'. (Must be a member of the STOP_REASONS enum: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused.)\"\n\n      # H-1 verdict derivation: parse findings JSONL, map highest severity to verdict\n      # - PASS: no P0 or P1 findings (P2-only or clean)\n      # - CONDITIONAL: any P1 findings (no P0)\n      # - FAIL: any P0 findings\n      # Final line of iteration-NNN.md MUST be exactly: \"Review verdict: PASS\" / \"Review verdict: CONDITIONAL\" / \"Review verdict: FAIL\"\n      step_derive_verdict:\n        action: \"Derive review verdict from accumulated findings\"\n        algorithm: |\n          if p0_count > 0:\n            verdict = \"FAIL\"\n          elif p1_count > 0:\n            verdict = \"CONDITIONAL\"\n          else:\n            verdict = \"PASS\"\n          has_advisories = (verdict == \"PASS\" and p2_count > 0)\n          ac_coverage_signal is advisory while the validation rule is INFO/default-off; include it in synthesis traceability, but do not change the exact verdict enum from this signal alone.\n        outputs:\n          - verdict: \"PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL\"\n          - has_advisories: \"Boolean true when verdict is PASS and any active P2 findings exist\"\n          - ac_coverage_signal: \"exempt | disabled | pass | advisory-shortfall\"\n        contract: |\n          Every iteration-NNN.md must end with exactly: \"Review verdict: PASS\" (or CONDITIONAL or FAIL).\n          Downstream automation parses this final line via exact string match вҖ” do not vary the format.\n\n      step_read_all_iterations:\n        action: \"Read all iteration files and strategy\"\n        read_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n        read_also: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n      step_build_finding_registry:\n        action: \"Build deduplicated finding registry from all iterations\"\n        algorithm: |\n          1. Extract all findings from iteration JSONL delta files\n          2. Compute content_hash for each finding (emission requirement):\n             content_hash = sha256(file_path + \"\\u001f\" + line_range + \"\\u001f\" + finding_type + \"\\u001f\" + normalized_description_80chars)\n             Normalized description = whitespace-collapsed, lowercased, first 80 chars of the finding description.\n          3. Two-tier dedup:\n             PRIMARY: group by content_hash field\n               - Same content_hash, multiple dimensions вҶ’ single finding, merged `dimensions: [<all>]` array\n               - Keep highest severity on duplicates\n             FALLBACK (legacy records lacking content_hash): file:line + normalized_title\n               - Same file:line, multiple dimensions вҶ’ single finding, multiple dimension tags\n               - Keep highest severity on duplicates\n          4. Track finding lifecycle:\n             - status: active | duplicate | upgraded | downgraded | contested | resolved_false_positive\n             - Record first_seen, upgraded_in, previous_severity for severity changes\n             - Record dimensions array reflecting all dimensions that emitted this finding\n          5. Resolve contradictions:\n             - Findings marked contested across iterations вҶ’ referee pass\n             - Determine final severity and status\n          6. Count only 'active' findings for totals\n        outputs:\n          - finding_registry: \"Deduplicated list of all findings with metadata\"\n          - active_p0: \"Count of active P0 findings\"\n          - active_p1: \"Count of active P1 findings\"\n          - active_p2: \"Count of active P2 findings\"\n\n      step_adversarial_selfcheck:\n        action: \"Final adversarial self-check on all P0 and P1 findings\"\n        algorithm: |\n          For each active P0/P1 finding:\n            1. Hunter: Re-verify finding against source code (re-read file:line)\n            2. Skeptic: Challenge severity вҖ” is this really P0/P1? Could it be P2?\n            3. Referee: Final call вҖ” confirm, downgrade, or mark false_positive\n          Update finding_registry with adjudicated results.\n\n      step_emit_resource_map:\n        action: \"Emit {state_paths.resource_map_output} from converged review deltas unless config.resource_map.emit is false\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} --emit-resource-map\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.delta_dir}/iter-*.jsonl\"\n        write:\n          - \"{state_paths.resource_map_output}\"\n        guarantee: \"Reducer skips cleanly when config.resource_map.emit == false and writes a deterministic resource-map when enabled.\"\n\n      step_resource_map_coverage_gate:\n        action: \"If resource_map_present, compute the Resource Map Coverage Gate synthesis inputs; otherwise preserve the skip note\"\n        note: \"Cross-check target_files from {spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md against {spec_folder}/resource-map.md. Report touched entries, untouched entries split into expected-by-scope vs gap, and implementation paths absent from the map. Findings raised here use category resource-map-coverage with severity calibrated to the gate outcome.\"\n\n      step_compile_review_report:\n        action: \"Compile review/review-report.md with 9 core sections, a conditional Resource Map Coverage Gate section, and an embedded Planning Packet\"\n        instructions: |\n          Create review/review-report.md with the following sections:\n\n          1. **Executive Summary**\n             - Overall verdict: PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL\n             - hasAdvisories: true when PASS carries active P2 items\n             - P0/P1/P2 counts (active only)\n             - Review scope summary\n\n          2. **Planning Trigger**\n             - State whether `/speckit:plan` is required\n             - Include a fenced `json` block labeled `Planning Packet`\n             - The packet MUST include: `triggered`, `verdict`, `hasAdvisories`, `activeFindings`, `remediationWorkstreams`, `specSeed`, `planSeed`, `findingClasses`, `affectedSurfacesSeed`, `fixCompletenessRequired`\n             - Build `activeFindings`, `findingClasses`, and `affectedSurfacesSeed` from reducer-owned state plus iteration JSONL `findingDetails`; if a field is missing, mark it `UNKNOWN` instead of inferring it from prose\n\n          3. **Active Finding Registry**\n             - Unified registry for active P0/P1/P2 findings\n             - For each: ID, severity, title, dimension, file:line, evidence, impact, fix recommendation, disposition, findingClass, scopeProof, affectedSurfaceHints\n\n          4. **Remediation Workstreams**\n             - Ordered action groups: P0 first, then P1, with P2 advisories separated\n\n          5. **Spec Seed**\n             - Concrete seed bullets for follow-on spec updates\n\n          6. **Plan Seed**\n             - Concrete starter tasks for `/speckit:plan`\n\n           7. **Traceability Status**\n              - Summarize required core protocols first, then applicable overlay protocols\n              - Include status, evidence, and any unresolved drift per protocol\n              - Include `AC_COVERAGE` status for lifecycle-active spec-folder targets: exempt, disabled, pass, or advisory-shortfall, with covered/total and floor when available\n\n          If `resource_map_present` is true, insert **## Resource Map Coverage Gate** after `Traceability Status` with exactly three bullets:\n             - `Entries touched`: count of resource-map paths that appear in applied reports\n             - `Entries not touched`: paths in resource-map not in implementation, labeled `expected-by-scope` or `gap`\n             - `Implementation paths absent from resource-map`: `target_files` in applied reports not on the map\n\n          8. **Deferred Items**\n             - Advisory-only or backlog-worthy follow-ups that do not block the current verdict\n\n          9. **Search Ledger**\n             - Always include this section before the appendix.\n             - Render reducer-owned `searchCoverage`, `candidateCoverage`, `searchDebt`, `ruledOutCandidates`, and `cleanSearchProof`.\n             - If all arrays are empty or absent, include: `*No search-depth state captured (legacy v1 record)*`.\n             - When `searchDebt` is non-empty, state `hasSearchDebt: true` and carry the dashboard verdict as CONDITIONAL unless active P0 findings make it FAIL.\n\n          10. **Audit Appendix**\n             - Convergence summary, coverage summary, ruled-out claims, sources reviewed\n             - Cross-reference appendix MUST be split into `Core Protocols` and `Overlay Protocols`\n\n          Preserve machine-owned markers so the reducer-owned registry, dashboard, and strategy anchors can be refreshed on re-run without mutating prior synthesis. (Note: `completed-continue` lineage branch is deferred вҖ” see `deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md В§Lifecycle Branches`.)\n        output: \"{state_paths.review_output}\"\n\n      step_convergence_report:\n        action: \"Append convergence report to JSONL\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"synthesis_complete\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"totalIterations\":{iteration_count},\"activeP0\":{active_p0},\"activeP1\":{active_p1},\"activeP2\":{active_p2},\"dimensionCoverage\":{dimension_coverage},\"verdict\":\"{verdict}\",\"releaseReadinessState\":\"{release_readiness_state}\",\"stopReason\":\"{reason}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n        note: \"Emit as numeric ratio (e.g., 0.75), not quoted string. Compute: dimensions_covered / total_dimensions.\"\n\n      step_update_config_status:\n        action: \"Mark config as complete\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n        set_field: { status: \"complete\" }\n\n      step_stage_artifact_dir:\n        action: \"Stage all skill-owned artifacts under artifact_dir for the operator's next git commit\"\n        command: \"git add {state_paths.packet_dir}\"\n        note: \"Skill-owned contract fix (028): without this stage step, operators who do `git add review-report.md` lose the iteration trail (iterations/, deltas/, state.jsonl, strategy, findings-registry, etc.). Staging the whole artifact_dir keeps the audit trail intact. Operators retain commit authority and can `git restore --staged {path}` to unstage anything before commit. Failure is non-fatal вҖ” log warning and continue.\"\n        on_fail: \"Log warning. Do not block synthesis. The artifact_dir may be outside a git repo (e.g., temp test fixture) which is a valid case.\"\n\n  # в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ\n  # PHASE 4: SAVE\n  # в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ\n  phase_save:\n    purpose: Preserve review context to memory system\n    steps:\n\n      step_compose_save_payload:\n        action: \"Compose the structured JSON payload consumed by generate-context.js\"\n        output: \"/tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json\"\n        requirements:\n          - \"Write this file before invoking generate-context.js; the loader fails closed if the explicit JSON file is absent.\"\n          - \"Include `specFolder`, a concise `sessionSummary`, curated `observations`, `recent_context`, `toolCalls`, and `exchanges` from the completed review loop.\"\n          - \"Use a session-scoped temp filename; do not use the retired shared `/tmp/save-context-data.json` path.\"\n        example_payload: |\n          {\n            \"specFolder\": \"{spec_folder}\",\n            \"sessionSummary\": \"Deep review completed; see review/review-report.md for verdict, findings, and workstreams.\",\n            \"observations\": [\"Summarize the active findings, verdict, and remediation guidance.\"],\n            \"recent_context\": [\"Point to the generated review artifacts and next action.\"],\n            \"exchanges\": [],\n            \"toolCalls\": []\n          }\n\n      step_generate_context:\n        action: \"Route continuity content into the correct canonical spec document via generate-context.js\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json {spec_folder}\"\n        critical_rule: \"NEVER manually author files under retired memory/ paths (the runtime rejects them); use generate-context.js so the save routes into decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md\"\n\n      step_index_memory:\n        action: \"Index the routed canonical spec document with memory_save when immediate MCP visibility is required\"\n        mcp_tool: memory_save\n        invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"[routed-canonical-spec-doc-path]\" })'\n        note: \"Use the actual canonical spec-doc path returned by generate-context.js (decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md); memory_index_scan remains the bulk fallback\"\n\n      step_verify_save:\n        action: \"Verify canonical save routed content into the correct spec document\"\n        check: \"Does {spec_folder}/implementation-summary.md, {spec_folder}/decision-record.md, or {spec_folder}/handover.md carry the new continuity update?\"\n        on_fail: \"Log warning but do not block completion\"\n\n      step_release_lock:\n        action: \"Release the single-writer lock after save, skip-save, or cancellation cleanup has resolved\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"lock_released\",\"path\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"releasePhase\":\"save\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n  # в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ\n  # COMPLETION\n  # в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ\n  completion:\n    message: |\n      Deep review complete.\n      Iterations: {iteration_count} | Stop reason: {reason}\n      Findings: P0={active_p0} P1={active_p1} P2={active_p2}\n      Verdict: {verdict} | hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n\n      Artifacts:\n        - review/review-report.md (compiled from {iteration_count} iterations)\n        - {iteration_count} iteration files in review/iterations/\n        - State files in review/: deep-review-config.json, deep-review-state.jsonl, deep-review-findings-registry.json, deep-review-strategy.md, deep-review-dashboard.md\n        - Memory context saved\n\n      STATUS=OK PATH={spec_folder}\n    next_steps:\n      - \"/speckit:plan [remediation] (if FAIL or CONDITIONAL verdict)\"\n      - \"/create:changelog (if PASS, including PASS with hasAdvisories=true)\"\n      - \"/deep:review [target] (for another review)\"\n      - \"/memory:save {spec_folder} (refresh canonical continuity before the next session)\"\n\n# в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n# ERROR RECOVERY\n# в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\nerror_recovery:\n  agent_dispatch_timeout: \"Retry once with reduced scope (fewer files per iteration). If second timeout, mark as 'timeout' and continue.\"\n  state_file_missing: \"If JSONL missing during loop, reconstruct from iteration files. If strategy missing, create minimal version.\"\n  consecutive_failures: \"After 3 consecutive errors, halt loop and enter synthesis with partial findings.\"\n  memory_save_failure: \"Preserve the review packet in review/ as backup. Log warning.\"\n\n# в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n# RULES\n# в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\nrules:\n  ALWAYS:\n    - follow_workflow_phases_in_order\n    - dispatch_deep_review_agent_per_iteration\n    - check_convergence_before_each_iteration\n    - write_all_state_to_files\n    - save_memory_context_after_synthesis\n    - respect_max_iterations_cap\n    - treat_review_target_as_read_only\n    - deduplicate_findings_before_synthesis\n    - run_adversarial_selfcheck_on_p0_p1\n  NEVER:\n    - skip_convergence_check\n    - dispatch_non_leaf_agents\n    - hold_iteration_findings_in_memory_only\n    - modify_config_after_initialization\n    - overwrite_jsonl_state_log\n    - proceed_without_state_file_verification\n    - modify_files_under_review\n    - report_p0_without_file_line_evidence\n\n# в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n# REFERENCE-ONLY APPENDIX\n# в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\nreference_only_appendix:\n  checkpoint_commit:\n    note: \"Checkpoint commits are intentionally excluded from workflow.steps.\"\n    commands:\n      - \"git add {state_paths.iteration_pattern} {state_paths.state_log} {state_paths.findings_registry} {state_paths.strategy} {state_paths.review_output}\"\n      - 'git commit -m \"chore(deep-review): iteration {NNN} complete\"'\n  severity_weights:\n    note: \"Severity weights for newFindingsRatio calculation\"\n    weights:\n      P0: 10.0\n      P1: 5.0\n      P2: 1.0\n    p0_override: \"If ANY new P0 discovered вҶ’ newFindingsRatio = max(calculated, 0.50). A single new P0 blocks convergence.\"\n    clean_pass: \"If total_findings == 0 (clean pass) вҶ’ newFindingsRatio = 0.0\"\n  review_dimensions:\n    note: \"All 4 default review dimensions with priority ordering\"\n    dimensions:\n      - { priority: 1, name: \"correctness\", checks: \"Logic, state flow, edge cases, error handling\" }\n      - { priority: 2, name: \"security\", checks: \"Auth, input/output safety, data exposure, permissions\" }\n      - { priority: 3, name: \"traceability\", checks: \"Spec/checklist alignment, cross-reference integrity, evidence coverage\" }\n      - { priority: 4, name: \"maintainability\", checks: \"Patterns, documentation quality, safe follow-on change clarity\" }\n  cross_reference_protocols:\n    note: \"Cross-reference verification protocols split into core and overlay classes\"\n    core_protocols:\n      - { check: \"Spec vs Code\", source: \"spec.md claims\", target: \"implementation\" }\n      - { check: \"Checklist vs Evidence\", source: \"[x] items\", target: \"cited evidence\" }\n    overlay_protocols:\n      - { check: \"SKILL.md vs Agent\", source: \"Skill contracts\", target: \"agent files\" }\n      - { check: \"Agent Cross-Runtime\", source: \".claude\", target: \".codex/.opencode/.agents\" }\n      - { check: \"Feature Catalog vs Code\", source: \"Catalog claims\", target: \"implementation\" }","lineStart":635,"lineEnd":1440,"totalLines":1441,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1781764136308,"end":1781764136322}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_08d89cdc047971e6016a339027ed5881918f217e253bda6c69"}},"id":"prt_ed96b1c14001chW53Ar2N9hN99","sessionID":"ses_126960be2ffewGSaH1Z0io46OH","messageID":"msg_ed96b05b00010tZKTUOsOIOWCU"}}
