{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781764189648,"sessionID":"ses_126960be2ffewGSaH1Z0io46OH","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_2MNfQOFrXx7wXf6l1dfoPoJJ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/scopes/B-rest-of-002/spec.md","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/scopes/B-rest-of-002/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Audit Scope вҖ” Memory Store / Index / Lifecycle (002 non-search)\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Independent gpt-5.5 deep-review **audit** of the memory store, index, and write-lifecycle code of the system-spec-kit MCP server вҖ” the 002-memory-store-and-search surface OUTSIDE the search/retrieval pipeline and outside the 017-021 fixes. REVIEW-SCOPE target (no new implementation). Report real P0/P1/P2 findings with `file:line` evidence; clean PASS is valid.\n5: \n6: ## Code under review\n7: All paths under `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/`:\n8: - `handlers/memory-index.ts` and the write/index/scan handlers вҖ” memory write safety, index scan, causal write lifecycle\n9: - `lib/storage/` вҖ” maintenance markers, storage/index maintenance, retention\n10: - `lib/ops/` вҖ” job-store, batch-processor, scan-job orchestration, cancellation lifecycle\n11: - semantic trigger fallback, learning-feedback reducers, memclaw-derived memory hardening, OpenLTM retrieval/observability + continuity/resilience, provenance injection, idempotency flag-on correctness (the 002 store/index modules under `handlers/` and `lib/`)\n12: \n13: ## Review dimensions\n14: correctness, security (SQL/injection, path handling), data integrity (write safety, idempotency, causal lifecycle), concurrency/cancellation, performance, maintainability, spec-vs-code drift. Emphasize write-path safety, transaction boundaries, and cancellation/cleanup correctness.\n15: \n16: ## Notes\n17: This round BROADENS beyond 017-021. Focus on store/index/lifecycle code, not the search/retrieval pipeline (covered by scope A).\n18: \n19: ## If MCP tools hang or error\n20: The `mk-spec-memory` / `mk-code-index` daemons can flap. NEVER block this review on a wedged MCP call. If an `mcp__mk_spec_memory__*` or `mcp__mk_code_index__*` call hangs or errors, immediately fall back вҖ” use plain Grep/Read for the code, or the warm-daemon CLI front doors: `node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs <tool> --json '<args>' --format json --timeout-ms 5000` and `node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs <tool> --format json --timeout-ms 5000 --warm-only`. This is a code audit вҖ” direct Grep/Read of the cited files is sufficient on its own.\n\n(End of file - total 20 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Audit Scope вҖ” Memory Store / Index / Lifecycle (002 non-search)\n\n## Purpose\nIndependent gpt-5.5 deep-review **audit** of the memory store, index, and write-lifecycle code of the system-spec-kit MCP server вҖ” the 002-memory-store-and-search surface OUTSIDE the search/retrieval pipeline and outside the 017-021 fixes. REVIEW-SCOPE target (no new implementation). Report real P0/P1/P2 findings with `file:line` evidence; clean PASS is valid.\n\n## Code under review\nAll paths under `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/`:\n- `handlers/memory-index.ts` and the write/index/scan handlers вҖ” memory write safety, index scan, causal write lifecycle\n- `lib/storage/` вҖ” maintenance markers, storage/index maintenance, retention\n- `lib/ops/` вҖ” job-store, batch-processor, scan-job orchestration, cancellation lifecycle\n- semantic trigger fallback, learning-feedback reducers, memclaw-derived memory hardening, OpenLTM retrieval/observability + continuity/resilience, provenance injection, idempotency flag-on correctness (the 002 store/index modules under `handlers/` and `lib/`)\n\n## Review dimensions\ncorrectness, security (SQL/injection, path handling), data integrity (write safety, idempotency, causal lifecycle), concurrency/cancellation, performance, maintainability, spec-vs-code drift. Emphasize write-path safety, transaction boundaries, and cancellation/cleanup correctness.\n\n## Notes\nThis round BROADENS beyond 017-021. Focus on store/index/lifecycle code, not the search/retrieval pipeline (covered by scope A).\n\n## If MCP tools hang or error\nThe `mk-spec-memory` / `mk-code-index` daemons can flap. NEVER block this review on a wedged MCP call. If an `mcp__mk_spec_memory__*` or `mcp__mk_code_index__*` call hangs or errors, immediately fall back вҖ” use plain Grep/Read for the code, or the warm-daemon CLI front doors: `node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs <tool> --json '<args>' --format json --timeout-ms 5000` and `node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs <tool> --format json --timeout-ms 5000 --warm-only`. This is a code audit вҖ” direct Grep/Read of the cited files is sufficient on its own.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/scopes/B-rest-of-002/spec.md","text":"# Audit Scope вҖ” Memory Store / Index / Lifecycle (002 non-search)\n\n## Purpose\nIndependent gpt-5.5 deep-review **audit** of the memory store, index, and write-lifecycle code of the system-spec-kit MCP server вҖ” the 002-memory-store-and-search surface OUTSIDE the search/retrieval pipeline and outside the 017-021 fixes. REVIEW-SCOPE target (no new implementation). Report real P0/P1/P2 findings with `file:line` evidence; clean PASS is valid.\n\n## Code under review\nAll paths under `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/`:\n- `handlers/memory-index.ts` and the write/index/scan handlers вҖ” memory write safety, index scan, causal write lifecycle\n- `lib/storage/` вҖ” maintenance markers, storage/index maintenance, retention\n- `lib/ops/` вҖ” job-store, batch-processor, scan-job orchestration, cancellation lifecycle\n- semantic trigger fallback, learning-feedback reducers, memclaw-derived memory hardening, OpenLTM retrieval/observability + continuity/resilience, provenance injection, idempotency flag-on correctness (the 002 store/index modules under `handlers/` and `lib/`)\n\n## Review dimensions\ncorrectness, security (SQL/injection, path handling), data integrity (write safety, idempotency, causal lifecycle), concurrency/cancellation, performance, maintainability, spec-vs-code drift. Emphasize write-path safety, transaction boundaries, and cancellation/cleanup correctness.\n\n## Notes\nThis round BROADENS beyond 017-021. Focus on store/index/lifecycle code, not the search/retrieval pipeline (covered by scope A).\n\n## If MCP tools hang or error\nThe `mk-spec-memory` / `mk-code-index` daemons can flap. NEVER block this review on a wedged MCP call. If an `mcp__mk_spec_memory__*` or `mcp__mk_code_index__*` call hangs or errors, immediately fall back вҖ” use plain Grep/Read for the code, or the warm-daemon CLI front doors: `node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs <tool> --json '<args>' --format json --timeout-ms 5000` and `node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs <tool> --format json --timeout-ms 5000 --warm-only`. This is a code audit вҖ” direct Grep/Read of the cited files is sufficient on its own.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":20,"totalLines":20,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/scopes/B-rest-of-002/spec.md","time":{"start":1781764189643,"end":1781764189647}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_05e674bd00f39964016a339059eebc819180435ca35