{"type":"text","timestamp":1781764440466,"sessionID":"ses_126960be2ffewGSaH1Z0io46OH","part":{"id":"prt_ed96fc10b001eMDC0CtFk9KfUc","messageID":"msg_ed96faf36001WYoZ41gL9FLlFW","sessionID":"ses_126960be2ffewGSaH1Z0io46OH","type":"text","text":"The async ingest issue is confirmed at the control-flow level: the queue treats only thrown exceptions as per-file failures, but `indexSingleFile` returns `status: rejected/error` for validation and save failures without throwing. IвҖҷm checking whether another layer maps those returned statuses before I record it as a finding.","time":{"start":1781764440332,"end":1781764440465},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0e379d9a031ef0a9016a3391584e14819183321f2f95fd8da2","phase":"commentary"}}}}
