{"type":"text","timestamp":1781764555503,"sessionID":"ses_126960be2ffewGSaH1Z0io46OH","part":{"id":"prt_ed97168a4001rcE7nsQa5yaMlx","messageID":"msg_ed9715989001GEBm8XXskybU1Q","sessionID":"ses_126960be2ffewGSaH1Z0io46OH","type":"text","text":"Search paths share the same leak: vector, multi-concept, trigger, and FTS SQL all join active rows/projections but omit `deleted_at IS NULL`; FTS and graph-FTS additionally read rowids from `memory_fts`. IвҖҷm doing a short pass over remaining lifecycle areas for any equally severe issue before writing the report.","time":{"start":1781764548773,"end":1781764555502},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_081032ee8def50e2016a3391c4bf808191b8fd6aa7d8535753","phase":"commentary"}}}}
